Rule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Windows Components/Internet Explorer/Internet Control Panel/Security Page/Restricted Sites Zone/Enable dragging of content from different domains within a window)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:550"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Dragging of content from different domains within a window must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Security Page-&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains within a window' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disabled' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59863","V-46997"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F88F98F7-6C08-1014-A07E-C05FEBE26A78","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223037","title":"SRG-APP-000207"},"rule_version":"DTBI1046-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223037r961086_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223037","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223037","rule_id":"SV-223037r961086","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:565"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Internet zone.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59871","V-47005"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F88FA612-6C08-1014-857D-CD10C11A3F56","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223038","title":"SRG-APP-000207"},"rule_version":"DTBI1051-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223038r961086_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223038","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223038","rule_id":"SV-223038r961086","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:568"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Restricted Sites zone.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-79201","V-64711"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F88FAE0A-6C08-1014-8659-D67475C25021","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warningsâ must be âEnabledâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"PreventOverride\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223039","title":"SRG-APP-000278"},"rule_version":"DTBI1060-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223039r961194_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223039","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether the user can bypass warnings from SmartScreen Filter. SmartScreen Filter prevents the user from browsing to or downloading from sites that are known to host malicious content. SmartScreen Filter also prevents the execution of files that are known to be malicious. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter warnings block the user. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user can bypass SmartScreen Filter warnings.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223039","rule_id":"SV-223039r961194","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter\\PreventOverride is a REG_DWORD equal to 1)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:578"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Prevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings must be enabled.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warningsâ to âEnabledâ.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-79203","V-64713"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F88FB2A9-6C08-1014-ABB0-C2E9B82F7940","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings about files that are not commonly downloaded from the internetâ must be âEnabledâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter.\n\nCriteria: If the value \"PreventOverrideAppRepUnknown\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223040","title":"SRG-APP-000209"},"rule_version":"DTBI1065-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223040r961089_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223040","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether the user can bypass warnings from SmartScreen Filter. SmartScreen Filter warns the user about executable files that Internet Explorer users do not commonly download from the internet. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter warnings block the user. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user can bypass SmartScreen Filter warnings.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223040","rule_id":"SV-223040r961089","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter\\PreventOverrideAppRepUnknown is a REG_DWORD equal to 1)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:572"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Prevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings about files that are not commonly downloaded from the internet must be enabled.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent bypassing SmartScreen Filter warnings about files that are not commonly downloaded from the internetâ to âEnabledâ.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-79205","V-64715"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F88FB8C0-6C08-1014-9D9A-CBFFC861B41B","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent per-user installation of ActiveX controlsâ must be âEnabledâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Security\\ActiveX. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"BlockNonAdminActiveXInstall\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223041","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"rule_version":"DTBI1070-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223041r961092_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223041","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to prevent the installation of ActiveX controls on a per-user basis. If you enable this policy setting, ActiveX controls cannot be installed on a per-user basis. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, ActiveX controls can be installed on a per-user basis.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223041","rule_id":"SV-223041r961092","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Security\\ActiveX\\BlockNonAdminActiveXInstall is a REG_DWORD equal to 1)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:574"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Prevent per-user installation of ActiveX controls must be enabled.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; âPrevent per-user installation of ActiveX controlsâ to âEnabledâ.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-79207","V-64717"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F88FC001-6C08-1014-94FC-E160F92A84EF","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; âPrevent ignoring certificate errorsâ must be âEnabledâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"PreventIgnoreCertErrors\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223042","title":"SRG-APP-000427"},"rule_version":"DTBI1075-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223042r961596_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223042","discussion":"This policy setting prevents the user from ignoring Secure Sockets Layer/Transport Layer Security (SSL/TLS) certificate errors that interrupt browsing (such as âexpiredâ, ârevokedâ, or âname mismatchâ errors) in Internet Explorer. If you enable this policy setting, the user cannot continue browsing. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose to ignore certificate errors and continue browsing.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223042","rule_id":"SV-223042r961596","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\PreventIgnoreCertErrors is a REG_DWORD equal to 1)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001954"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:575"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Prevent ignoring certificate errors option must be enabled.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000427","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; âPrevent ignoring certificate errorsâ to âEnabledâ.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-79209","V-64719"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F88FC4AD-6C08-1014-AEA4-D09B326E4021","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone &gt;&gt; âTurn on SmartScreen Filter scanâ must be âEnabledâ and âEnableâ selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"2301\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223043","title":"SRG-APP-000278"},"rule_version":"DTBI1080-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223043r961194_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223043","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you disable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter does not scan pages in this zone for malicious content. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223043","rule_id":"SV-223043r961194","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\\2301 is a REG_DWORD equal to 0)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:577"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Turn on SmartScreen Filter scan option for the Internet Zone must be enabled.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone &gt;&gt; âTurn on SmartScreen Filter scanâ to âEnabledâ, and select âEnableâ from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-79211","V-64721"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F88FC88A-6C08-1014-ACAD-83EB81F0AB43","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; âTurn on SmartScreen Filter scanâ must be âEnabledâ and âEnableâ selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"2301\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.\n","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223044","title":"SRG-APP-000278"},"rule_version":"DTBI1085-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223044r961194_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223044","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you enable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content. If you disable this policy setting, SmartScreen Filter does not scan pages in this zone for malicious content. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether SmartScreen Filter scans pages in this zone for malicious content.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223044","rule_id":"SV-223044r961194","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\\2301 is a REG_DWORD equal to 0)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001242"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:576"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Turn on SmartScreen Filter scan option for the Restricted Sites Zone must be enabled.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000278","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; âTurn on SmartScreen Filter scanâ to âEnabledâ, and select âEnableâ from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-79213","V-64723"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F88FCCDA-6C08-1014-B243-9F4CD1479DD9","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Intranet Zone &gt;&gt; âInitialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safeâ must be âEnabledâ and âDisableâ selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"1201\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.\n","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223045","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"rule_version":"DTBI1090-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223045r961092_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223045","discussion":"ActiveX controls that are not marked safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed. This setting causes both unsafe and safe controls to be initialized and scripted, ignoring the Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting option. This increases the risk of malicious code being loaded and executed by the browser. If you enable this policy setting, ActiveX controls are run, loaded with parameters and scripted without setting object safety for untrusted data or scripts. If you disable this policy setting, ActiveX controls that cannot be made safe are not loaded with parameters or scripted. This setting is not recommended, except for secure and administered zones.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223045","rule_id":"SV-223045r961092","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\1\\1201 is a REG_DWORD equal to 3)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:579"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe must be disallowed (Intranet Zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Intranet Zone &gt;&gt; âInitialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safeâ to âEnabledâ, and select âDisableâ from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-79215","V-64725"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F88FD0EB-6C08-1014-8065-F98417CC6FE6","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Trusted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; âInitialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safeâ must be âEnabledâ and âDisableâ selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"1201\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.\n","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223046","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"rule_version":"DTBI1095-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223046r961092_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223046","discussion":"ActiveX controls that are not marked safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed. This setting causes both unsafe and safe controls to be initialized and scripted, ignoring the Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting option. This increases the risk of malicious code being loaded and executed by the browser. If you enable this policy setting, ActiveX controls are run, loaded with parameters and scripted without setting object safety for untrusted data or scripts. If you disable this policy setting, ActiveX controls that cannot be made safe are not loaded with parameters or scripted. This setting is not recommended, except for secure and administered zones.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223046","rule_id":"SV-223046r961092","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\2\\1201 is a REG_DWORD equal to 3)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:573"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe must be disallowed (Trusted Sites Zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Trusted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; âInitialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safeâ to âEnabledâ, and select âDisableâ from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-87395","V-72757"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F88FD4D6-6C08-1014-9F83-B152DDD5E94B","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; Add-on Management, verify \"Remove the Run this time button for outdated ActiveX controls in IE\" is set to âEnabledâ. \n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext \n\nIf the value \"RunThisTimeEnabled\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223048","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI1105-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223048r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223048","discussion":"This feature keeps ActiveX controls up to date and helps make them safer to use in Internet Explorer. Many ActiveX controls are not automatically updated as new versions are released. It is very important to keep ActiveX controls up to date because malicious or compromised webpages can target security flaws in out-of-date ActiveX controls.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223048","rule_id":"SV-223048r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Check if HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext\\RunThisTimeEnabled is set to 0)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:585"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Run once selection for running outdated ActiveX controls must be disabled.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; Add-on Management, set \"Remove the Run this time button for outdated ActiveX controls in IE\" to \"Enabled\"."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-87397","V-72759"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F88FD8A6-6C08-1014-B30A-DBC94FDDD7CA","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; Add-on Management, verify \"Turn off blocking of outdated ActiveX controls for Internet Explorer\" is set to âDisabledâ. \n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext \n\nIf the value \"VersionCheckEnabled\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223049","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI1110-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223049r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223049","discussion":"This feature keeps ActiveX controls up to date and helps make them safer to use in Internet Explorer. Many ActiveX controls are not automatically updated as new versions are released. It is very important to keep ActiveX controls up to date because malicious or compromised webpages can target security flaws in out-of-date ActiveX controls.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223049","rule_id":"SV-223049r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Check if HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SOFTWARE\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Policies\\Ext\\VersionCheckEnabled is set to 1)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:586"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Enabling outdated ActiveX controls for Internet Explorer must be blocked.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; Add-on Management, set \"Turn off blocking of outdated ActiveX controls for Internet Explorer\" to \"Disabled\"."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-87399","V-72761"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F88FDDC3-6C08-1014-BD80-A19EEC0E9857","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone, verify \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" is âEnabledâ. \n\nIn the Options window, verify the âOnly allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box is set to âEnableâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 \n\nCriteria: \n\nIf the value \"120c\" is REG_DWORD = â3â, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223050","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI1115-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223050r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223050","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users can run the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control, based on security zone. By default, the TDC ActiveX Control is disabled in the Internet and Restricted Sites security zones. If you enable this policy setting, users will not be able to run the TDC ActiveX control from all sites in the specified zone.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223050","rule_id":"SV-223050r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control)\nCriteria        :     true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :       true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :       true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 14393)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :       true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :       true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 14393)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:583"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Use of the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control must be disabled for the Internet Zone.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Pane &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone, set the \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" to âEnabledâ. \n\nIn the Options window, select \"Enable\" from the âOnly allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59437","V-46573"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F88FE245-6C08-1014-87F0-D9DDD90295A2","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Download signed ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1001\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223051","title":"SRG-APP-000209"},"rule_version":"DTBI112-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223051r961089_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223051","discussion":"ActiveX controls can contain potentially malicious code and must only be allowed to be downloaded from trusted sites. Signed code is better than unsigned code in that it may be easier to determine its author, but it is still potentially harmful, especially when coming from an untrusted zone.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223051","rule_id":"SV-223051r961089","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Download signed ActiveX controls)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:436"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The Download signed ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Download signed ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-87401","V-72763"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F88FE638-6C08-1014-8055-EE7FDCE988F1","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone, verify \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" is âEnabledâ. \n\nIn the Options window, verify the âOnly allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box is set to âEnableâ. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 \n\nCriteria: \n\nIf the value \"120c\" is REG_DWORD = â3â, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223052","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI1120-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223052r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223052","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users can run the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control, based on security zone. By default, the TDC ActiveX Control is disabled in the Internet and Restricted Sites security zones. If you enable this policy setting, users wonât be able to run the TDC ActiveX control from all sites in the specified zone.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223052","rule_id":"SV-223052r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nCriteria        :   true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :     true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control)\nCriteria        :     true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :       true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :       true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 14393)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :     false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :       true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :       true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 14393)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:584"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Use of the Tabular Data Control (TDC) ActiveX control must be disabled for the Restricted Sites Zone.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"In the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone, set the \"Allow only approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" to âEnabledâ.\n\nIn the Options windows, select \"Enable\" from the âOnly allow approved domains to use the TDC ActiveX control\" drop-down box.\n \n"},{"legacy_ids":["SV-89849","V-75169"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F88FEA42-6C08-1014-9078-CFF47FDA975E","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone &gt;&gt; \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"Disable\" must be selected from the drop-down box. \n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3\n\nIf the value for \"140C\" is not REG_DWORD = 3, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223053","title":"SRG-APP-000209"},"rule_version":"DTBI1125-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223053r961089_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223053","discussion":"This policy setting allows the management of whether VBScript can be run on pages from the specified zone in Internet Explorer. By selecting \"Enable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript can run without user intervention. By selecting \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, users are asked to choose whether to allow VBScript to run. By selecting \"Disable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript is prevented from running. If this policy setting is not configured or disabled, VBScript will run without user intervention.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223053","rule_id":"SV-223053r961089","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer' setting is set to 'Enable' and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box in Group Policy.)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :     true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 15063)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:588"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"VBScript must not be allowed to run in Internet Explorer (Internet zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Internet Zone &gt;&gt; \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Disable\" from the drop-down box."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59439","V-46575"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F88FEE45-6C08-1014-B2CF-960B90522D0C","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Download unsigned ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1004\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223054","title":"SRG-APP-000209"},"rule_version":"DTBI113-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223054r961089_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223054","discussion":"Unsigned code is potentially harmful, especially when coming from an untrusted zone. ActiveX controls can contain potentially malicious code and must only be allowed to be downloaded from trusted sites. They must also be digitally signed.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223054","rule_id":"SV-223054r961089","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Download unsigned ActiveX controls)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:437"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The Download unsigned ActiveX controls property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Download unsigned ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-89851","V-75171"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F88FF248-6C08-1014-9778-85A2757FE89C","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"Disable\" must be selected from the drop-down box.\n\nUse the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4\n\nIf the value for \"140C\" is not REG_DWORD = 3, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223055","title":"SRG-APP-000209"},"rule_version":"DTBI1130-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223055r961089_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223055","discussion":"This policy setting allows the management of whether VBScript can be run on pages from the specified zone in Internet Explorer. By selecting \"Enable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript can run without user intervention. By selecting \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, users are asked to choose whether to allow VBScript to run. By selecting \"Disable\" in the drop-down box, VBScript is prevented from running. If this policy setting is not configured or disabled, VBScript will run without user intervention.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223055","rule_id":"SV-223055r961089","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone-&gt;'Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer' setting is set to 'Enable' and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box in Group Policy.)\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (The OS Version is equal to or greater than 6.3)\nTest            :     true (The OS Build is equal to or greater than 15063)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001169"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:589"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"VBScript must not be allowed to run in Internet Explorer (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000209","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Security Page &gt;&gt; Restricted Sites Zone &gt;&gt; \"Allow VBScript to run in Internet Explorer\" to \"Enabled\" and select \"Disable\" from the drop-down box."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-106631","V-97527"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F88FF5FD-6C08-1014-BAA1-D5B69EAF51E1","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Toolbars &gt;&gt; âTurn off Developer Toolsâ must be âEnabledâ. \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKEY_LOCAL_Machine\\SOFTWARE\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\IEDevTools\nCriteria: If the value \"Disabled\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223056","title":"SRG-APP-000266"},"rule_version":"DTBI1135-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223056r961167_rule","severity":"low","group_id_src":"V-223056","discussion":"While the risk associated with browser development tools is more related to the proper design of a web application, a risk vector remains within the browser. The developer tools allow end users and application developers to view and edit all types of web application related data via the browser. Page elements, source code, javascript, API calls, application data, etc. may all be viewed and potentially manipulated. Manipulation could be useful for troubleshooting legitimate issues, and this may be performed in a development environment. Manipulation could also be malicious and must be addressed.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223056","rule_id":"SV-223056r961167","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Developer Tools are disabled)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001312"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:591"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Development Tools Must Be Disabled.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000266","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Toolbars &gt;&gt; âTurn off Developer Toolsâ to âEnabledâ."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59441","V-46577"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F88FFA0F-6C08-1014-812F-B43955740362","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1201\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223057","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"rule_version":"DTBI114-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223057r961092_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223057","discussion":"ActiveX controls not marked safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223057","rule_id":"SV-223057r961092","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:438"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Initialize and script ActiveX controls not marked as safe' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59443","V-46579"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F88FFDB4-6C08-1014-B318-87095744D327","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run ActiveX controls and plugins' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1200\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223058","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"rule_version":"DTBI115-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223058r961863_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223058","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether ActiveX controls and plug-ins can be run on pages from the specified zone. ActiveX controls not marked as safe should not be executed. If you enable this policy setting, controls and plug-ins can run without user intervention. If you disable this policy setting, controls and plug-ins are prevented from running.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223058","rule_id":"SV-223058r961863","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Run ActiveX controls and plugins)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:439"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"ActiveX controls and plug-ins must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run ActiveX controls and plugins' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59445","V-46581"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890055B-6C08-1014-8B93-DDCDAEC8E35E","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1405\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223059","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"rule_version":"DTBI116-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223059r961092_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223059","discussion":"This policy setting allows management of whether ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting can interact with a script. If you enable this policy setting, script interaction can occur automatically without user intervention. ActiveX controls not marked as safe for scripting should not be executed. Although this is not a complete security measure for a control to be marked safe for scripting, if a control is not marked safe, it should not be initialized and executed.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223059","rule_id":"SV-223059r961092","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:440"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Script ActiveX controls marked safe for scripting' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59447","V-46583"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8900A45-6C08-1014-BAAC-F395E932A531","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow file downloads' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1803\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223060","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI119-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223060r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223060","discussion":"Sites located in the Restricted Sites Zone are more likely to contain malicious payloads and therefore downloads from this zone should be blocked. Files should not be able to be downloaded from sites that are considered restricted. This policy setting allows you to manage whether file downloads are permitted from the zone. This option is determined by the zone of the page with the link causing the download, not the zone from which the file is delivered.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223060","rule_id":"SV-223060r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow file downloads)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:441"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"File downloads must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow file downloads' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59451","V-46587"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8900E66-6C08-1014-BA32-D13FFB8E2C6B","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223061","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI121-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223061r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223061","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code; sites located in this security zone are more likely to be hosted by malicious individuals. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223061","rule_id":"SV-223061r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Java permissions)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:453"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.  "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59453","V-46589"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8901230-6C08-1014-B1E0-BE7F196575C9","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Access data sources across domains' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1406\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223062","title":"SRG-APP-000039"},"rule_version":"DTBI122-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223062r1117169_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223062","discussion":"The ability to access data zones across domains could cause the user to unknowingly access content hosted on an unauthorized server. This policy setting allows you to manage whether Internet Explorer can access data from another security zone using the Microsoft XML Parser (MSXML) or ActiveX Data Objects (ADO).","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223062","rule_id":"SV-223062r1117169","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Access data sources across domains)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:443"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Accessing data sources across domains must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Access data sources across domains' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59455","V-46591"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F89015D6-6C08-1014-9203-FBAE32D8142A","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow META REFRESH' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1608\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223063","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"rule_version":"DTBI123-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223063r961863_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223063","discussion":"It is possible that users will unknowingly be redirected to a site hosting malicious content. 'Allow META REFRESH' must have a level of protection based upon the site being browsed. This policy setting allows you to manage whether a user's browser can be redirected to another web page if the author of the web page uses the Meta Refresh setting to redirect browsers to another web page.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223063","rule_id":"SV-223063r961863","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow META REFRESH)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:444"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The Allow META REFRESH property must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow META REFRESH' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59457","V-46593"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8901979-6C08-1014-9E4A-B0F18588372F","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1802\" is REG_DWORD=3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223064","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI126-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223064r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223064","discussion":"Content hosted on sites located in the Restricted Sites zone are more likely to contain malicious payloads and therefore this feature should be blocked for this zone. Drag and drop or copy and paste files must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223064","rule_id":"SV-223064r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:445"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Functionality to drag and drop or copy and paste files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow drag and drop or copy and paste files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59461","V-46597"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8901D29-6C08-1014-ACD5-DDFE6349CC89","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Launching applications and files in an IFRAME' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1804\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223065","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI128-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223065r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223065","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether applications may be run and files may be downloaded from an IFRAME reference in the HTML of the pages in this zone. Launching of programs in IFRAME must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. If you enable this policy setting, applications can run and files can be downloaded from IFRAMEs on the pages in this zone without user intervention. If you disable this setting, users are prevented from running applications and downloading files from IFRAMEs on the pages in this zone.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223065","rule_id":"SV-223065r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Launching applications and files in an IFRAME)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:447"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Launching programs and files in IFRAME must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Launching applications and files in an IFRAME' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59463","V-46599"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890208C-6C08-1014-BABF-939486BBF591","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Navigate windows and frames across different domains' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1607\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223066","title":"SRG-APP-000039"},"rule_version":"DTBI129-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223066r1117169_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223066","discussion":"Frames navigating across different domains are a security concern, because the user may think they are accessing pages on one site while they are actually accessing pages on another site. It is possible that a website hosting malicious content could use this feature in a manner similar to cross-site scripting (XSS). This policy setting allows you to manage the opening of sub-frames and access of applications across different domains.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223066","rule_id":"SV-223066r1117169","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Navigate windows and frames across different domains)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:448"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Navigating windows and frames across different domains must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Navigate windows and frames across different domains' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59465","V-46601"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890240E-6C08-1014-A94D-97A74976E556","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Userdata persistence' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1606\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223067","title":"SRG-APP-000231"},"rule_version":"DTBI132-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223067r961128_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223067","discussion":"Userdata persistence must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. This policy setting allows you to manage the preservation of information in the browser's history, in Favorites, in an XML store, or directly within a web page saved to disk. When a user returns to a persisted page, the state of the page can be restored if this policy setting is not appropriately configured.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223067","rule_id":"SV-223067r961128","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Userdata persistence)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001199"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:449"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Userdata persistence must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000231","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Userdata persistence' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box"},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59467","V-46603"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F89027B0-6C08-1014-85F4-F7919E41724B","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow active scripting' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1400\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223068","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI133-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223068r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223068","discussion":"Active scripts hosted on sites located in this zone are more likely to contain malicious code. Active scripting must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed. This policy setting allows you to manage whether script code on pages in the zone are run.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223068","rule_id":"SV-223068r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow active scripting)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:450"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Active scripting must be disallowed (Restricted Sites Zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow active scripting' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59469","V-46605"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8902B52-6C08-1014-A37D-B3BDF077BFAC","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow cut, copy or paste operations from the clipboard via script' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1407\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223069","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI134-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223069r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223069","discussion":"A malicious script could use the clipboard in an undesirable manner, for example, if the user had recently copied confidential information to the clipboard while editing a document, a malicious script could harvest that information. It might be possible to exploit other vulnerabilities in order to send the harvested data to the attacker. Allow paste operations via script must have a level of protection based upon the site being accessed.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223069","rule_id":"SV-223069r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow cut, copy, or paste operations from the clipboard via script)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:451"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Clipboard operations via script must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow cut, copy or paste operations from the clipboard via script' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59471","V-46607"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8902F36-6C08-1014-AB14-F3314879F173","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Logon options' must be 'Enabled', and 'Anonymous logon' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1A00\" is REG_DWORD = 196608 (decimal), this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223070","title":"SRG-APP-000219"},"rule_version":"DTBI136-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223070r1043178_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223070","discussion":"Users could submit credentials to servers operated by malicious individuals who could then attempt to connect to legitimate servers with those captured credentials. Care must be taken with user credentials, automatic logon performance, and how default Windows credentials are passed to the websites. This policy setting allows management of settings for logon options. If you enable this policy setting, you can choose from varying logon options. âAnonymous logonâ disables HTTP authentication and uses the guest account only for the Common Internet File System (CIFS) protocol. âPrompt for user name and passwordâ queries users for user IDs and passwords. After a user is queried, these values can be used silently for the remainder of the session. âAutomatic logon only in Intranet zoneâ queries users for user IDs and passwords in other zones. After a user is queried, these values can be used silently for the remainder of the session. âAutomatic logon with current user name and passwordâ attempts logon using Windows NT Challenge Response. If Windows NT Challenge Response is supported by the server, the logon uses the user's network user name and password for login. If Windows NT Challenge Response is not supported by the server, the user is queried to provide the user name and password. If you disable this policy setting, logon is set to âAutomatic logon only in Intranet zoneâ. If you do not configure this policy setting, logon is set to âAutomatic logon only in Intranet zoneâ. The most secure option is to configure this setting to âEnabledâ; âAnonymous logonâ. This will prevent users from submitting credentials to servers in this security zone.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223070","rule_id":"SV-223070r1043178","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Logon options)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001184"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:452"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Logon options must be configured and enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000219","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Logon options' to 'Enabled', and select 'Anonymous logon' from the drop-down box."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59473","V-46609"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F89032B8-6C08-1014-83A7-EF763046FA82","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Disable Configuring History' must be 'Enabled', and '40' entered in 'Days to keep pages in History'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Control Panel Criteria: If the value \"History\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding. AND  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Url History Criteria: If the value \"DaysToKeep\" is REG_DWORD = 40 (decimal), this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223071","title":"SRG-APP-000089"},"rule_version":"DTBI300-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223071r960879_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223071","discussion":"This setting specifies the number of days that Internet Explorer keeps track of the pages viewed in the History List. The delete Browsing History option can be accessed using Tools, Internet Options, \"General\" tab, and then click Settings under Browsing History. If you enable this policy setting, a user cannot set the number of days that Internet Explorer keeps track of the pages viewed in the History List. The number of days that Internet Explorer keeps track of the pages viewed in the History List must be specified. Users will not be able to delete browsing history. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, a user can set the number of days that Internet Explorer tracks views of pages in the History List. Users can delete browsing history.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223071","rule_id":"SV-223071r960879","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Delete Browsing History\\Disable Configuring History must be Enabled)\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Delete Browsing History\\40 entered in Days to keep pages in History)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:513"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Configuring History setting must be set to 40 days.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Disable Configuring History' to 'Enabled', and enter '40' in 'Days to keep pages in History'."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59479","V-46615"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8903656-6C08-1014-BC1B-A59EA1288B81","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to add/delete sites' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"Security_zones_map_edit\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223072","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI318-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223072r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223072","discussion":"This setting prevents users from adding sites to various security zones. Users should not be able to add sites to different zones, as this could allow them to bypass security controls of the system. If you do not configure this policy setting, users will be able to add or remove sites from the Trusted Sites and Restricted Sites zones at will and change settings in the Local Intranet zone. This configuration could allow sites that host malicious mobile code to be added to these zones, and users could execute the code.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223072","rule_id":"SV-223072r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Security Zones: Do Not Allow Users to Add/Delete Sites)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:419"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer must be set to disallow users to add/delete sites.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to add/delete sites' to 'Enabled'."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59481","V-46617"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F89039E6-6C08-1014-9BA8-E3DCCEBAF867","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to change policies' must be 'Enabled'.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"Security_options_edit\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223073","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"rule_version":"DTBI319-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223073r961863_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223073","discussion":"Users who change their Internet Explorer security settings could enable the execution of dangerous types of code from the Internet and websites listed in the Restricted Sites zone in the browser. This setting prevents users from changing the Internet Explorer policies on the machine. Policy changes should be made by administrators only, so this setting should be enabled. If you enable this policy setting, you disable the \"Custom level\" button and \"Security\" level for this zone slider on the Security tab in the Internet Options dialog box. If this policy setting is disabled or not configured, users will be able to change the settings for security zones. It prevents users from changing security zone policy settings that are established by the administrator.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223073","rule_id":"SV-223073r961863","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Security Zones: Do Not Allow Users to Change Policies)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:418"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer must be configured to disallow users to change policies.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Do not allow users to change policies' to 'Enabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59483","V-46619"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8903D60-6C08-1014-B3F7-B8D474CAB0E2","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Use only machine settings' must be 'Enabled'.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"Security_HKLM_only\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223074","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"rule_version":"DTBI320-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223074r961863_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223074","discussion":"Users who change their Internet Explorer security settings could enable the execution of dangerous types of code from the Internet and websites listed in the Restricted Sites zone in the browser. This setting enforces consistent security zone settings to all users of the computer. Security zones control browser behavior at various websites and it is desirable to maintain a consistent policy for all users of a machine. This policy setting affects how security zone changes apply to different users. If you enable this policy setting, changes that one user makes to a security zone will apply to all users of that computer. If this policy setting is disabled or not configured, users of the same computer are allowed to establish their own security zone settings.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223074","rule_id":"SV-223074r961863","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Security Zones: Use Only Machine Settings)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:417"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer must be configured to use machine settings.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer 'Security Zones: Use only machine settings' to 'Enabled'. "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59485","V-46621"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F89041DD-6C08-1014-9117-E2971C67C7A3","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn off the Security Settings Check feature' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Security Criteria: If the value \"DisableSecuritySettingsCheck\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223075","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"rule_version":"DTBI325-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223075r961863_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223075","discussion":"This policy setting turns off the Security Settings Check feature, which checks Internet Explorer security settings to determine when the settings put Internet Explorer at risk. If you enable this policy setting, the security settings check will not be performed. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the security settings check will be performed.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223075","rule_id":"SV-223075r961863","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Turn off the Security Settings Check feature)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:457"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Security checking features must be enforced.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn off the Security Settings Check feature' to 'Disabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59489","V-46625"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F89045D4-6C08-1014-A6BC-BBA0D3E5DE71","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: Some legitimate software and controls may have an invalid signature. You should carefully test such software in isolation before it is allowed to be used on an organization's network.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Allow software to run or install even if the signature is invalid' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Download Criteria: If the value \"RunInvalidSignatures\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223076","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"rule_version":"DTBI350-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223076r961092_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223076","discussion":"Microsoft ActiveX controls and file downloads often have digital signatures attached that certify the file's integrity and the identity of the signer (creator) of the software. Such signatures help ensure unmodified software is downloaded and the user can positively identify the signer to determine whether you trust them enough to run their software.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223076","rule_id":"SV-223076r961092","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Advanced Page \\Allow Software to Run or Install Even if the Signature is Invalid)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:459"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Software must be disallowed to run or install with invalid signatures.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Allow software to run or install even if the signature is invalid' to 'Disabled'. "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59861","V-46995"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8904B0D-6C08-1014-812D-953DD24C00EA","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If McAfee ENS Web Control is being used, this is Not Applicable.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page 'Turn on 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"Isolation64Bit\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223077","title":"SRG-APP-000233"},"rule_version":"DTBI356-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223077r961131_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223077","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer 11 uses 64-bit processes (for greater security) or 32-bit processes (for greater compatibility) when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows.Important: Some ActiveX controls and toolbars may not be available when 64-bit processes are used. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer 11 will use 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer 11 will use 32-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows. If you don't configure this policy setting, users can turn this feature on or off using Internet Explorer settings. This feature is turned off by default.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223077","rule_id":"SV-223077r961131","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Advanced Page Turn on 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:564"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The 64-bit tab processes, when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows, must be turned on.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page 'Turn on 64-bit tab processes when running in Enhanced Protected Mode on 64-bit versions of Windows' to 'Enabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59493","V-46629"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8904F27-6C08-1014-B86F-B25DAB3D9F65","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Check for server certificate revocation' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings Criteria: If the value \"CertificateRevocation\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223078","title":"SRG-APP-000175"},"rule_version":"DTBI365-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223078r961038_rule","severity":"low","group_id_src":"V-223078","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether Internet Explorer will check revocation status of servers' certificates. Certificates are revoked when they have been compromised or are no longer valid, and this option protects users from submitting confidential data to a site that may be fraudulent or not secure. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will check to see if server certificates have been revoked. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not check server certificates to see if they have been revoked. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not check server certificates to see if they have been revoked.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000605","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223078","rule_id":"SV-223078r961038","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Advanced Page \\Check for Server Certificate Revocation)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000185"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:461"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Checking for server certificate revocation must be enforced.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000175","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Check for server certificate revocation' to 'Enabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59497","V-46633"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8905312-6C08-1014-B4DA-8B21A9DB56B4","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Check for signatures on downloaded programs' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Download Criteria: If the value \"CheckExeSignatures\" is REG_SZ = yes, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223079","title":"SRG-APP-000131"},"rule_version":"DTBI370-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223079r960954_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223079","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether Internet Explorer checks for digital signatures (which identifies the publisher of signed software and verifies it has not been modified or tampered with) on user computers before downloading executable programs. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will check the digital signatures of executable programs and display their identities before downloading them to the user computers. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not check the digital signatures of executable programs or display their identities before downloading them to the user computers. If you do not configure this policy, Internet Explorer will not check the digital signatures of executable programs or display their identities before downloading them to the user computers.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223079","rule_id":"SV-223079r960954","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Advanced Page \\Check for Signature on Downloaded Programs)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001749"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:462"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Checking for signatures on downloaded programs must be enforced.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000131","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Advanced Page -&gt; 'Check for signatures on downloaded programs' to 'Enabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59499","V-46635"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F89056F3-6C08-1014-B735-F2E523F6C008","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; 'Intranet Sites: Include all network paths (UNCs)' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\ZoneMap Criteria: If the value \"UNCAsIntranet\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223080","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"rule_version":"DTBI375-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223080r961863_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223080","discussion":"Some UNC paths could refer to servers not managed by the organization, which means they could host malicious content; and therefore, it is safest to not include all UNC paths in the Intranet Sites zone. This policy setting controls whether URLs representing UNCs are mapped into the local Intranet security zone. If you enable this policy setting, all network paths are mapped into the Intranet Zone. If you disable this policy setting, network paths are not necessarily mapped into the Intranet Zone (other rules might map one there). If you do not configure this policy setting, users choose whether network paths are mapped into the Intranet Zone.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223080","rule_id":"SV-223080r961863","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Intranet Sites: Include all network paths (UNCs))\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:463"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"All network paths (UNCs) for Intranet sites must be disallowed.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; 'Intranet Sites: Include all network paths (UNCs)' to 'Disabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59501","V-46637"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8905B1D-6C08-1014-AEC4-DBDCFC9B6F8B","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2102\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223081","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI385-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223081r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223081","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage restrictions on script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars. If you enable this policy setting, Windows Restrictions security will not apply in this zone. The security zone runs without the added layer of security provided by this feature. If you disable this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process. If you do not configure this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223081","rule_id":"SV-223081r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:464"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Script-initiated windows without size or position constraints must be disallowed (Internet zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59503","V-46639"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8905EF3-6C08-1014-9BE5-B317548D5B8F","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2102\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223082","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI390-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223082r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223082","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage restrictions on script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars. If you enable this policy setting, Windows Restrictions security will not apply in this zone. The security zone runs without the added layer of security provided by this feature. If you disable this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process. If you do not configure this policy setting, the possible harmful actions contained in script-initiated pop-up windows and windows including the title and status bars cannot be run. This Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as dictated by the Scripted Windows Security Restrictions feature control setting for the process.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223082","rule_id":"SV-223082r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:465"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Script-initiated windows without size or position constraints must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow script-initiated windows without size or position constraints' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.  "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59505","V-46641"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890628F-6C08-1014-AA03-864DF9418E31","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow Scriptlets' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1209\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223083","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI395-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223083r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223083","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether scriptlets can be allowed. Scriptlets hosted on sites located in this zone are more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, users will be able to run scriptlets. If you disable this policy setting, users will not be able to run scriptlets. If you do not configure this policy setting, a scriptlet can be enabled or disabled by the user.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223083","rule_id":"SV-223083r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Allow Scriptlets)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:466"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Scriptlets must be disallowed (Internet zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow Scriptlets' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59507","V-46643"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8906604-6C08-1014-8C57-D63D0C72A752","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2200\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223084","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI415-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223084r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223084","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users will be prompted for non user-initiated file downloads. Regardless of this setting, users will receive file download dialogs for user-initiated downloads. Users may accept downloads that they did not request, and those downloaded files may include malicious code. If you enable this setting, users will receive a file download dialog for automatic download attempts. If you disable or do not configure this setting, file downloads that are not user-initiated will be blocked, and users will see the information bar instead of the file download dialog. Users can then click the information bar to allow the file download prompt.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223084","rule_id":"SV-223084r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Automatic prompting for file downloads)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:467"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Automatic prompting for file downloads must be disallowed (Internet zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59509","V-46645"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890699C-6C08-1014-97C8-D61B9A69C67D","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Local Machine Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\0 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223085","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI425-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223085r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223085","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.  ","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223085","rule_id":"SV-223085r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Local Machine Zone\\Java permissions)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:468"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Local Machine zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Local Machine Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59869","V-47003"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8906D3E-6C08-1014-94D9-EC733B2C34BE","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt;Local Machine Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' must be 'Enabled' and 'Disable' selected in the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\0  Criteria: If the value \"270C\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223086","title":"SRG-APP-000207"},"rule_version":"DTBI426-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223086r961086_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223086","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer runs Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls, to check if they're safe to load on pages.      If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer always checks with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. If you don't configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer won't check with your Anti-Malware program to see if it's safe to create an instance of the ActiveX control. Users can turn this behavior on or off, using Internet Explorer Security settings.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223086","rule_id":"SV-223086r961086","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Local Machine Zone Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001662"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:567"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Anti-Malware programs against ActiveX controls must be run for the Local Machine zone.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000207","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Local Machine Zone 'Don't run antimalware programs against ActiveX controls' to 'Enabled' and select 'Disable' in the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59511","V-46647"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F89070BB-6C08-1014-9B64-B58CB845A0C3","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Local Machine Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\0 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223087","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI430-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223087r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223087","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223087","rule_id":"SV-223087r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Locked Down Local Machine Zone\\Java permissions)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:469"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Local Machine zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Local Machine Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59513","V-46649"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890742C-6C08-1014-BABC-8654708EB98F","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Intranet Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\1 Criteria: If the value\" 1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223088","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI435-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223088r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223088","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223088","rule_id":"SV-223088r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Locked Down Intranet Zone\\Java permissions)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:470"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Intranet zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Intranet Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59517","V-46653"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8907838-6C08-1014-BF3C-A661274AB485","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Trusted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\2 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223089","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI440-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223089r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223089","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code; sites located in this security zone are more likely to be hosted by malicious individuals. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety. ","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223089","rule_id":"SV-223089r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Locked Down Trusted Sites Zone\\Java permissions)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:471"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Trusted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Trusted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59527","V-46663"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8907BE5-6C08-1014-97D4-B9828403BFC6","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable Java' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following keys: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Lockdown_Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1C00\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223090","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI450-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223090r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223090","discussion":"Java applications could contain malicious code. This policy setting allows you to manage permissions for Java applets. If you enable this policy setting, options can be chosen from the drop-down box. Use of the Custom permission will control permissions settings individually. Use of the Low Safety permission enables applets to perform all operations. Use of the Medium Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox (an area in memory outside of which the program cannot make calls), plus adds capabilities like scratch space (a safe and secure storage area on the client computer) and a user-controlled file I/O. Use of the High Safety permission enables applets to run in their sandbox. If you disable this policy setting, Java applets cannot run. If you do not configure this policy setting, the permission is set to High Safety. ","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223090","rule_id":"SV-223090r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Locked Down restricted Sites Zone\\Java permissions)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:473"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Java permissions must be disallowed (Locked Down Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Locked-Down Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Java permissions' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable Java' from the drop-down box.  "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59529","V-46665"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8907F81-6C08-1014-B2B1-EDB0600D835C","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow loading of XAML files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2402\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223091","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"rule_version":"DTBI455-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223091r961863_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223091","discussion":"These are eXtensible Application Markup Language (XAML) files. XAML is an XML-based declarative markup language commonly used for creating rich user interfaces and graphics that leverage the Windows Presentation Foundation. If you enable this policy setting and the drop-down box is set to Enable, XAML files will be automatically loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If the drop-down box is set to Prompt, users will receive a prompt for loading XAML files. If you disable this policy setting, XAML files will not be loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If you do not configure this policy setting, users will have the freedom to decide whether to load XAML files inside Internet Explorer.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223091","rule_id":"SV-223091r961863","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Loose or un-compiled XAML files)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:474"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"XAML files must be disallowed (Internet zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow loading of XAML files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59533","V-46669"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8908330-6C08-1014-AF5A-A4E2B9806A74","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow loading of XAML files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2402\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223092","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"rule_version":"DTBI460-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223092r961863_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223092","discussion":"These are eXtensible Application Markup Language (XAML) files. XAML is an XML-based declarative markup language commonly used for creating rich user interfaces and graphics that leverage the Windows Presentation Foundation. If you enable this policy setting and the drop-down box is set to Enable, XAML files will be automatically loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If the drop-down box is set to Prompt, users will receive a prompt for loading XAML files. If you disable this policy setting, XAML files will not be loaded inside Internet Explorer. Users will not be able to change this behavior. If you do not configure this policy setting, users will have the freedom to decide whether to load XAML files inside Internet Explorer.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223092","rule_id":"SV-223092r961863","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Loose XAML files)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:475"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"XAML files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow loading of XAML files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59545","V-46681"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890881E-6C08-1014-A00D-DDFD1A6469C1","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Protected Mode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2500\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223093","title":"SRG-APP-000233"},"rule_version":"DTBI485-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223093r961131_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223093","discussion":"Protected Mode protects Internet Explorer from exploited vulnerabilities by reducing the locations Internet Explorer can write to in the registry and the file system. If you enable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned on. Users will not be able to turn off Protected Mode. If you disable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned off. It will revert to Internet Explorer 6 behavior that allows for Internet Explorer to write to the registry and the file system. Users will not be able to turn on Protected Mode. If you do not configure this policy, users will be able to turn on or off Protected Mode.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223093","rule_id":"SV-223093r961131","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Turn On Protected Mode)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:480"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Protected Mode must be enforced (Internet zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Protected Mode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59549","V-46685"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8908BA0-6C08-1014-AE9E-8D372E9C2E77","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Protected Mode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2500\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223094","title":"SRG-APP-000233"},"rule_version":"DTBI490-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223094r961131_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223094","discussion":"Protected Mode protects Internet Explorer from exploited vulnerabilities by reducing the locations Internet Explorer can write to in the registry and the file system. If you enable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned on. Users will not be able to turn off Protected Mode. If you disable this policy setting, Protected Mode will be turned off. It will revert to Internet Explorer 6 behavior that allows for Internet Explorer to write to the registry and the file system. Users will not be able to turn on Protected Mode. If you do not configure this policy, users will be able to turn on or off Protected Mode.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223094","rule_id":"SV-223094r961131","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Turn On Protected Mode)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:481"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Protected Mode must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Protected Mode' to 'Enabled' and select 'Enable', from the drop-down box.  "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59553","V-46689"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8908F1A-6C08-1014-A2E3-C73FB802A25B","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Use Pop-up Blocker' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1809\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223095","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI495-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223095r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223095","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether unwanted pop-up windows appear. Pop-up windows that are opened when the end user clicks a link are not blocked. If you enable this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing. If you disable this policy setting, pop-up windows are not prevented from appearing. If you do not configure this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223095","rule_id":"SV-223095r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Use Pop-up Blocker)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:482"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Pop-up Blocker must be enforced (Internet zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Use Pop-up Blocker' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.  "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59555","V-46691"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8909275-6C08-1014-A059-84ADBEDD77EC","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Use Pop-up Blocker' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1809\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223096","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI500-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223096r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223096","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether unwanted pop-up windows appear. Pop-up windows that are opened when the end user clicks a link are not blocked. If you enable this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing. If you disable this policy setting, pop-up windows are not prevented from appearing. If you do not configure this policy setting, most unwanted pop-up windows are prevented from appearing.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223096","rule_id":"SV-223096r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Use Pop-up Blocker)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:483"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Pop-up Blocker must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Use Pop-up Blocker' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box. "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59557","V-46693"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F89099A2-6C08-1014-AA96-BB3E3D6B56EB","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2101\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223097","title":"SRG-APP-000039"},"rule_version":"DTBI515-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223097r1117169_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223097","discussion":"This policy setting allows a user to manage whether websites from less privileged zones, such as Restricted Sites, can navigate into the Internet zone. If this policy setting is enabled, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone. The security zone will run without the added layer of security that is provided by the Protection from Zone Elevation security feature. If \"Prompt\" is selected in the drop-down box, a warning is issued to the user that potentially risky navigation is about to occur. If this policy setting is disabled, the potentially risky navigation is prevented. The Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as set by the Protection from Zone Elevation feature control. If this policy setting is not configured, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223097","rule_id":"SV-223097r1117169","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:484"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Websites in less privileged web content zones must be prevented from navigating into the Internet zone.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59559","V-46695"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8909D99-6C08-1014-8FB0-A3413DB103D3","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2101\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223098","title":"SRG-APP-000039"},"rule_version":"DTBI520-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223098r1117169_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223098","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether websites from less privileged zones, such as Restricted Sites, can navigate into the Restricted zone. If this policy setting is enabled, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone. The security zone will run without the added layer of security that is provided by the Protection from Zone Elevation security feature. If Prompt is selected in the drop-down box, a warning is issued to the user that potentially risky navigation is about to occur. If this policy setting is disabled, the potentially risky navigation is prevented. The Internet Explorer security feature will be on in this zone as set by the Protection from Zone Elevation feature control. If this policy setting is not configured, websites from less privileged zones can open new windows in, or navigate into, this zone.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223098","rule_id":"SV-223098r1117169","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:485"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Websites in less privileged web content zones must be prevented from navigating into the Restricted Sites zone.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Web sites in less privileged Web content zones can navigate into this zone' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59565","V-46701"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890A176-6C08-1014-B1DB-9BCEE6EFFE04","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow binary and script behaviors' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2000\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223099","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI575-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223099r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223099","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage dynamic binary and script behaviors of components that encapsulate specific functionality for HTML elements, to which they were attached. If you enable this policy setting, binary and script behaviors are available.   If you select \"Administrator approved\" in the drop-down box, only the behaviors listed in the Admin-approved Behaviors under Binary Behaviors Security Restriction policy are available.    If you disable this policy setting, binary and script behaviors are not available unless applications have implemented a custom security manager. If you do not configure this policy setting, binary and script behaviors are available.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223099","rule_id":"SV-223099r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow binary and script behaviors)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:486"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Allow binary and script behaviors must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow binary and script behaviors' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59569","V-46705"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890A51B-6C08-1014-8022-8439C9DA7893","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2200\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223100","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI580-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223100r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223100","discussion":"This policy setting determines whether users will be prompted for non user-initiated file downloads. Regardless of this setting, users will receive file download dialogs for user-initiated downloads. Users may accept downloads that they did not request, and those downloaded files may include malicious code. If you enable this setting, users will receive a file download dialog for automatic download attempts. If you disable or do not configure this setting, file downloads that are not user-initiated will be blocked, and users will see the information bar instead of the file download dialog. Users can then click the information bar to allow the file download prompt.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223100","rule_id":"SV-223100r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Automatic prompting for file downloads)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:487"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Automatic prompting for file downloads must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Automatic prompting for file downloads' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59573","V-46709"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890A8DF-6C08-1014-BB69-E4D2D2EA6993","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223101","title":"SRG-APP-000206"},"rule_version":"DTBI590-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223101r961083_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223101","discussion":"Internet Explorer uses Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) data to determine file handling procedures for files received through a web server. The Consistent MIME Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer requires all file-type information provided by web servers to be consistent. For example, if the MIME type of a file is text/plain but the MIME data indicates the file is really an executable file, Internet Explorer changes its extension to reflect this executable status. This capability helps ensure executable code cannot masquerade as other types of data that may be trusted. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer examines all received files and enforces consistent MIME data for them. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer does not require consistent MIME data for all received files and will use the MIME data provided by the file. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistent and properly labeled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting your network.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223101","rule_id":"SV-223101r961083","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Consistent Mime Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:488"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced. (Reserved)","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.  "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59575","V-46711"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890AC8A-6C08-1014-89EC-8557920382B8","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223102","title":"SRG-APP-000206"},"rule_version":"DTBI592-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223102r961083_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223102","discussion":"Internet Explorer uses Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) data to determine file handling procedures for files received through a web server. The Consistent MIME Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer requires all file-type information provided by web servers to be consistent. For example, if the MIME type of a file is text/plain but the MIME data indicates the file is really an executable file, Internet Explorer changes its extension to reflect this executable status. This capability helps ensure executable code cannot masquerade as other types of data that may be trusted. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer examines all received files and enforces consistent MIME data for them. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer does not require consistent MIME data for all received files and will use the MIME data provided by the file. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to the organization. Ensuring these files are consistent and properly labeled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223102","rule_id":"SV-223102r961083","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Consistent Mime Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:502"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced (Explorer).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59577","V-46713"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890B014-6C08-1014-8548-D5DA291F7D1B","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_HANDLING Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223103","title":"SRG-APP-000206"},"rule_version":"DTBI594-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223103r961083_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223103","discussion":"Internet Explorer uses Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) data to determine file handling procedures for files received through a web server. The Consistent MIME Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer requires all file-type information provided by web servers to be consistent. For example, if the MIME type of a file is text/plain but the MIME data indicates that the file is really an executable file, Internet Explorer changes its extension to reflect this executable status. This capability helps ensure that executable code cannot masquerade as other types of data that may be trusted. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer examines all received files and enforces consistent MIME data for them. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer does not require consistent MIME data for all received files and will use the MIME data provided by the file. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistent and properly labeled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223103","rule_id":"SV-223103r961083","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Consistent Mime Handling\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:503"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME handling must be enforced (iexplore).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Consistent Mime Handling -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59579","V-46715"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890B3F5-6C08-1014-A6B9-CE5539B10937","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223104","title":"SRG-APP-000206"},"rule_version":"DTBI595-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223104r961083_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223104","discussion":"MIME sniffing is the process of examining the content of a MIME file to determine its context - whether it is a data file, an executable file, or some other type of file. This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer MIME sniffing will prevent promotion of a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. When set to \"Enabled\", MIME sniffing will never promote a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. Disabling MIME sniffing configures Internet Explorer processes to allow a MIME sniff that promotes a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. For example, promoting a text file to an executable file is a dangerous promotion because any code in the supposed text file would be executed. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistently handled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends you configure this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide. Note: This setting works in conjunction with, but does not replace, the Consistent MIME Handling settings.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223104","rule_id":"SV-223104r961083","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Mime Sniffing Safety Feature\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:489"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME sniffing must be enforced (Reserved).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59581","V-46717"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890B77D-6C08-1014-AF4D-F06CF93980F7","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223105","title":"SRG-APP-000206"},"rule_version":"DTBI596-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223105r961083_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223105","discussion":"MIME sniffing is the process of examining the content of a MIME file to determine its context - whether it is a data file, an executable file, or some other type of file. This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer MIME sniffing will prevent promotion of a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. When set to \"Enabled\", MIME sniffing will never promote a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. Disabling MIME sniffing configures Internet Explorer processes to allow a MIME sniff that promotes a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. For example, promoting a text file to an executable file is a dangerous promotion because any code in the supposed text file would be executed. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistently handled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide. Note: This setting works in conjunction with, but does not replace, the Consistent MIME Handling settings.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223105","rule_id":"SV-223105r961083","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Mime Sniffing Safety Feature\\Internet Explorer Processes must be Enabled)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:510"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME sniffing must be enforced (Explorer).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.  "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59583","V-46719"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890BB1D-6C08-1014-988C-CC6C127C3246","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_MIME_SNIFFING Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223106","title":"SRG-APP-000206"},"rule_version":"DTBI597-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223106r961083_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223106","discussion":"MIME sniffing is the process of examining the content of a MIME file to determine its context - whether it is a data file, an executable file, or some other type of file. This policy setting determines whether Internet Explorer MIME sniffing will prevent promotion of a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. When set to \"Enabled\", MIME sniffing will never promote a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. Disabling MIME sniffing configures Internet Explorer processes to allow a MIME sniff that promotes a file of one type to a more dangerous file type. For example, promoting a text file to an executable file is a dangerous promotion because any code in the supposed text file would be executed. MIME file-type spoofing is a potential threat to an organization. Ensuring these files are consistently handled helps prevent malicious file downloads from infecting the network. This guide recommends configuring this policy as \"Enabled\" for all environments specified in this guide. Note: This setting works in conjunction with, but does not replace, the Consistent MIME Handling settings.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223106","rule_id":"SV-223106r961083","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Mime Sniffing Safety Feature\\Internet Explorer Processes must be Enabled)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:511"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MIME sniffing must be enforced (iexplore).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Mime Sniffing Safety Feature -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59585","V-46721"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890BEC9-6C08-1014-B6CA-DBAE4E52A808","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223107","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI599-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223107r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223107","discussion":"The MK Protocol Security Restriction policy setting reduces attack surface area by blocking the seldom used MK protocol. Some older web applications use the MK protocol to retrieve information from compressed files. Because the MK protocol is not widely used, it should be blocked wherever it is not needed. Setting this policy to \"Enabled\"; blocks the MK protocol for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer, which causes resources that use the MK protocol to fail. Disabling this setting allows applications to use the MK protocol API. This guide recommends configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to block the MK protocol unless it is specifically needed in the environment. Note: Because resources that use the MK protocol will fail when deploying this setting, ensure none of the applications use the MK protocol.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223107","rule_id":"SV-223107r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\MK Protocol Security Restriction\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:504"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (Reserved).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59587","V-46723"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890C28A-6C08-1014-A54C-A137C7F284D8","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223108","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI600-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223108r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223108","discussion":"The MK Protocol Security Restriction policy setting reduces attack surface area by blocking the seldom used MK protocol. Some older web applications use the MK protocol to retrieve information from compressed files. Because the MK protocol is not widely used, it should be blocked wherever it is not needed. Setting this policy to \"Enabled\"; blocks the MK protocol for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer, which causes resources that use the MK protocol to fail. Disabling this setting allows applications to use the MK protocol API. This guide recommends you configure this setting to \"Enabled\" to block the MK protocol unless it is specifically needed in the environment. Note: Because resources that use the MK protocol will fail when deploying this setting, ensure none of the applications use the MK protocol.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223108","rule_id":"SV-223108r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\MK Protocol Security Restriction\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:490"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (Explorer).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59589","V-46725"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890C656-6C08-1014-B883-C585736935E1","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_DISABLE_MK_PROTOCOL Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223109","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI605-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223109r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223109","discussion":"The MK Protocol Security Restriction policy setting reduces attack surface area by blocking the seldom used MK protocol. Some older web applications use the MK protocol to retrieve information from compressed files. Because the MK protocol is not widely used, it should be blocked wherever it is not needed. Setting this policy to \"Enabled\"; blocks the MK protocol for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer, which causes resources that use the MK protocol to fail. Disabling this setting allows applications to use the MK protocol API. This guide recommends you configure this setting to \"Enabled\" to block the MK protocol unless specifically needed in the environment. Note: Because resources that use the MK protocol will fail when deploying this setting, ensure none of the applications use the MK protocol.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223109","rule_id":"SV-223109r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\MK Protocol Security Restriction\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:491"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for MK protocol must be enforced (iexplore).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; MK Protocol Security Restriction -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'. "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59591","V-46727"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890C9FE-6C08-1014-B359-C4F9B9D0343B","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223110","title":"SRG-APP-000233"},"rule_version":"DTBI610-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223110r961131_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223110","discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page it opens that are dependent upon the location of the web page (such as Internet Zone, Intranet Zone, or Local Machine Zone). Web pages on a local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine Zone, which makes the Local Machine Security Zone a prime target for malicious attackers. If you enable this policy setting, any zone can be protected from zone elevation by Internet Explorer processes. This approach stops content running in one zone from gaining the elevated privileges of another zone. If you disable this policy setting, no zone receives such protection from Internet Explorer processes. Because of the severity and relative frequency of zone elevation attacks, this guide recommends that you configure this setting as \"Enabled\" in all environments.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223110","rule_id":"SV-223110r961131","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Protection From Zone Elevation\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:492"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (Reserved).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59593","V-46729"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890CD6F-6C08-1014-B358-BAE85F353FDA","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223111","title":"SRG-APP-000233"},"rule_version":"DTBI612-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223111r961131_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223111","discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page it opens that are dependent upon the location of the web page (such as Internet Zone, Intranet Zone, or Local Machine Zone). Web pages on a local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine Zone, which makes the Local Machine Security Zone a prime target for malicious attackers. If you enable this policy setting, any zone can be protected from zone elevation by Internet Explorer processes. This approach stops content running in one zone from gaining the elevated privileges of another zone. If you disable this policy setting, no zone receives such protection from Internet Explorer processes. Because of the severity and relative frequency of zone elevation attacks, this guide recommends configuring this setting as \"Enabled\" in all environments.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223111","rule_id":"SV-223111r961131","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Protection From Zone Elevation\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:505"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (Explorer).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59595","V-46731"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890D0BB-6C08-1014-B80C-97C3044B9C66","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_ZONE_ELEVATION Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223112","title":"SRG-APP-000233"},"rule_version":"DTBI614-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223112r961131_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223112","discussion":"Internet Explorer places restrictions on each web page it opens that are dependent upon the location of the web page (such as Internet Zone, Intranet Zone, or Local Machine Zone). Web pages on a local computer have the fewest security restrictions and reside in the Local Machine Zone, which makes the Local Machine Security Zone a prime target for malicious attackers. If you enable this policy setting, any zone can be protected from zone elevation by Internet Explorer processes. This approach stops content running in one zone from gaining the elevated privileges of another zone. If you disable this policy setting, no zone receives such protection from Internet Explorer processes. Because of the severity and relative frequency of zone elevation attacks, this guide recommends that you configure this setting as \"Enabled\" in all environments.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223112","rule_id":"SV-223112r961131","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Protection From Zone Elevation\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:506"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Zone Elevation must be enforced (iexplore).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Protection From Zone Elevation -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59597","V-46733"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890D5C1-6C08-1014-994E-C65F5B319DF8","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223113","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI630-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223113r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223113","discussion":"In certain circumstances, websites can initiate file download prompts without interaction from users. This technique can allow websites to put unauthorized files on users' hard drives if they click the wrong button and accept the download. If you configure the Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting to \"Enabled\", file download prompts that are not user-initiated are blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you configure this policy setting as \"Disabled\", prompting will occur for file downloads that are not user-initiated for Internet Explorer processes. Note: This setting is configured as \"Enabled\" in all environments specified in this guide to help prevent attackers from placing arbitrary code on users' computers.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223113","rule_id":"SV-223113r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\ Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:493"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (Reserved).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59645","V-46779"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890D96C-6C08-1014-AF1D-CAFA6D329ACA","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223114","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI635-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223114r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223114","discussion":"In certain circumstances, websites can initiate file download prompts without interaction from users. This technique can allow websites to put unauthorized files on users' hard drives if they click the wrong button and accept the download. If you configure the Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting to \"Enabled\", file download prompts that are not user-initiated are blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you configure this policy setting as \"Disabled\", prompting will occur for file downloads that are not user-initiated for Internet Explorer processes. Note: This setting is configured as \"Enabled\" in all environments specified in this guide to help prevent attackers from placing arbitrary code on users' computers.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223114","rule_id":"SV-223114r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:494"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (Explorer).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.  "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59647","V-46781"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890DCB9-6C08-1014-A9DF-98C696A1D22B","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_FILEDOWNLOAD Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223115","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI640-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223115r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223115","discussion":"In certain circumstances, websites can initiate file download prompts without interaction from users. This technique can allow websites to put unauthorized files on users' hard drives if they click the wrong button and accept the download. If you configure the Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting to \"Enabled\", file download prompts that are not user-initiated are blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you configure this policy setting as \"Disabled\", prompting will occur for file downloads that are not user-initiated for Internet Explorer processes. Note: This setting is configured as \"Enabled\" in all environments specified in this guide to help prevent attackers from placing arbitrary code on users' computers.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223115","rule_id":"SV-223115r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Restrict File Download\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:495"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Restrict File Download must be enforced (iexplore).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict File Download -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59653","V-46787"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890E043-6C08-1014-8A3B-95D7E318A043","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223116","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI645-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223116r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223116","discussion":"Internet Explorer allows scripts to programmatically open, resize, and reposition various types of windows. Often, disreputable websites will resize windows to either hide other windows or force the user to interact with a window containing malicious code. The Scripted Window Security Restrictions security feature restricts pop-up windows and prohibits scripts from displaying windows in which the title and status bars are not visible to the user, or which hide other windows' title and status bars. If you enable the Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting, pop-up windows and other restrictions apply for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer processes. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, scripts can continue to create pop-up windows, and create windows that hide other windows. Recommend configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to help prevent malicious websites from controlling the Internet Explorer windows or fooling users into clicking on the wrong window.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223116","rule_id":"SV-223116r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:496"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (Reserved).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'. "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59655","V-46789"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890E414-6C08-1014-A7B2-8D19EEEAE056","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223117","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI647-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223117r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223117","discussion":"Internet Explorer allows scripts to programmatically open, resize, and reposition various types of windows. Often, disreputable websites will resize windows to either hide other windows or force a user to interact with a window that contains malicious code. The Scripted Window Security Restrictions security feature restricts pop-up windows and prohibits scripts from displaying windows in which the title and status bars are not visible to the user, or which hide other windows' title and status bars. If you enable the Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting, pop-up windows and other restrictions apply for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer processes. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, scripts can continue to create pop-up windows and create windows that hide other windows. This guide recommends configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to help prevent malicious websites from controlling the Internet Explorer windows or fooling users into clicking on the wrong window.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223117","rule_id":"SV-223117r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:507"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (Explorer).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.  "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59657","V-46791"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890E7F3-6C08-1014-825A-9CE4F89EB43E","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_WINDOW_RESTRICTIONS Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223118","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI649-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223118r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223118","discussion":"Internet Explorer allows scripts to programmatically open, resize, and reposition various types of windows. Often, disreputable websites will resize windows to either hide other windows or force a user to interact with a window that contains malicious code. The Scripted Window Security Restrictions security feature restricts pop-up windows and prohibits scripts from displaying windows in which the title and status bars are not visible to the user, or which hide other windows' title and status bars. If you enable the Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes policy setting, pop-up windows and other restrictions apply for Windows Explorer and Internet Explorer processes. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, scripts can continue to create pop-up windows and create windows that hide other windows. This guide recommends configuring this setting to \"Enabled\" to help prevent malicious websites from controlling the Internet Explorer windows or fooling users into clicking on the wrong window.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223118","rule_id":"SV-223118r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Scripted Window Security Restrictions\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:508"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for restricting pop-up windows must be enforced (iexplore).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Scripted Window Security Restrictions -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59663","V-46797"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890EB9A-6C08-1014-8D2B-E01CBC8D00B1","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2004\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223119","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"rule_version":"DTBI650-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223119r961863_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223119","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework-reliant components that are not signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute unsigned managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute unsigned managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute unsigned managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute unsigned managed components.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223119","rule_id":"SV-223119r961863","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:497"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Restricted Sites Zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59665","V-46799"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890EF49-6C08-1014-8086-DA8695CCB635","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2001\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223120","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"rule_version":"DTBI655-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223120r961863_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223120","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework-reliant components that are signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. It may be possible for malicious content hosted on a website to take advantage of these components. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute signed managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute signed managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute signed managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute signed managed components.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223120","rule_id":"SV-223120r961863","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:498"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Restricted Sites Zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59667","V-46801"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890F302-6C08-1014-BE7B-C14BB2D0839C","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Scripting of Java applets' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1402\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223121","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI670-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223121r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223121","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether applets are exposed to scripts within the zone. If you enable this policy setting, scripts can access applets automatically without user intervention. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, users are queried to choose whether to allow scripts to access applets. If you disable this policy setting, scripts are prevented from accessing applets. If you do not configure this policy setting, scripts can access applets automatically without user intervention. ","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223121","rule_id":"SV-223121r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Scripting of Java applets)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:499"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Scripting of Java applets must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Scripting of Java applets' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59673","V-46807"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890F693-6C08-1014-823C-94D978D941A5","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for User Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Disable AutoComplete for forms' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"Use FormSuggest\" is REG_SZ = no, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223122","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI690-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223122r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223122","discussion":"This AutoComplete feature suggests possible matches when users are filling in forms. It is possible that this feature will cache sensitive data and store it in the user's profile, where it might not be protected as rigorously as required by organizational policy. If you enable this setting, the user is not presented with suggested matches when filling in forms. If you disable this setting, the user is presented with suggested possible matches when filling forms. If you do not configure this setting, the user has the freedom to turn on the auto-complete feature for forms. To display this option, the user opens the Internet Options dialog box, clicks the \"Contents\" tab, and clicks the \"Settings\" button.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223122","rule_id":"SV-223122r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (AutoComplete feature for forms must be disallowed.)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ie:def:223122"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"AutoComplete feature for forms must be disallowed.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Disable AutoComplete for forms' to 'Enabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59677","V-46811"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890FA06-6C08-1014-AD0B-D242BE415AD4","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn off Crash Detection' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Restrictions Criteria: If the value \"NoCrashDetection\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223123","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI715-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223123r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223123","discussion":"The 'Turn off Crash Detection' policy setting allows you to manage the crash detection feature of add-on management in Internet Explorer. A crash report could contain sensitive information from the computer's memory. If you enable this policy setting, a crash in Internet Explorer will be similar to one on a computer running Windows XP Professional Service Pack 1 and earlier, where Windows Error Reporting will be invoked. If you disable this policy setting, the crash detection feature in add-on management will be functional. ","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223123","rule_id":"SV-223123r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Turn Off Crash Detection)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:509"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Crash Detection management must be enforced.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn off Crash Detection' to 'Enabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59681","V-46815"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F890FDA2-6C08-1014-BD96-FB28073A71A0","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for User Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms' must be 'Disabled'. \nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"FormSuggest Passwords\" is REG_SZ = 'no', this is not a finding. AND Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKCU\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"FormSuggest PW Ask\" is REG_SZ = 'no', this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223124","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI725-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223124r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223124","discussion":"This policy setting controls automatic completion of fields in forms on web pages. It is possible that malware could be developed which would be able to extract the cached user names and passwords from the currently logged on user, which an attacker could then use to compromise that user's online accounts.  If you enable this setting, the user cannot change the 'User name and passwords on forms' or 'prompt me to save passwords'. The Auto Complete feature for\" User names and passwords on forms\" will be turned on. If you disable this setting, the user cannot change the 'User name and passwords on forms' or 'prompt me to save passwords'. The Auto Complete feature for \"User names and passwords on forms\" is turned off. The user also cannot opt to be prompted to save passwords. If you do not configure this setting, the user has the freedom of turning on Auto Complete for \"User name and passwords on forms\", and the option of prompting to save passwords.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223124","rule_id":"SV-223124r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms must be disabled.)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ie:def:223124"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms must be disabled.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for User Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; 'Turn on the auto-complete feature for user names and passwords on forms' to 'Disabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59685","V-46819"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8910124-6C08-1014-BF81-9F03C9911995","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; \"Prevent Managing SmartScreen Filter\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"On\" selected from the drop-down box. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key:\n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\PhishingFilter \n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnabledV9\" is \"REG_DWORD = 1\", this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223125","title":"SRG-APP-000206"},"rule_version":"DTBI740-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223125r961083_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223125","discussion":"This setting is important from a security perspective because Microsoft has extensive data illustrating the positive impact the SmartScreen filter has had on reducing the risk of malware infection via visiting malicious websites. This policy setting allows users to enable the SmartScreen Filter, which will warn if the website being visited is known for fraudulent attempts to gather personal information through 'phishing' or is known to host malware. If you enable this setting the user will not be prompted to enable the SmartScreen Filter. It must be specified which mode the SmartScreen Filter uses: On or Off. If the feature is On, all website addresses not contained on the filters allow list, will be sent automatically to Microsoft without prompting the user. If this feature is set to Off, the feature will not run. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, the user is prompted to decide whether to turn on SmartScreen Filter during the first-run experience.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223125","rule_id":"SV-223125r961083","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Prevent Managing SmartScreen Filter)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:514"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Managing SmartScreen Filter use must be enforced.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"If the system is on the SIPRNet, this requirement is NA.\n\nSet the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; \"Prevent Managing SmartScreen Filter\" to \"Enabled\", and select \"On\" from the drop-down box."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59695","V-46829"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8910499-6C08-1014-ABCD-863DBDD19CDD","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Allow deleting browsing history on exit' must be 'Disabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy Criteria: If the value \"ClearBrowsingHistoryOnExit\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223126","title":"SRG-APP-000089"},"rule_version":"DTBI760-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223126r960879_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223126","discussion":"Delete Browsing History on exit automatically deletes specified items when the last browser window closes.  Disabling this function will prevent users from deleting their browsing history, which could be used to identify malicious websites and files that could later be used for anti-virus and Intrusion Detection System (IDS) signatures.  Furthermore, preventing users from deleting browsing history could be used to identify abusive web surfing on government systems.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223126","rule_id":"SV-223126r960879","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Delete Browsing History\\Configure Delete Browsing History on exit)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:516"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Browser must retain history on exit.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Allow deleting browsing history on exit' to 'Disabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59707","V-46841"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F89107FA-6C08-1014-AAB0-C6F24DDDA7FD","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Prevent Deleting Web sites that the User has Visited' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy Criteria: If the value \"CleanHistory\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223127","title":"SRG-APP-000089"},"rule_version":"DTBI770-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223127r960879_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223127","discussion":"This policy prevents users from deleting the history of websites the user has visited. If you enable this policy setting, websites the user has visited will be preserved when the user clicks \"Delete\". If you disable this policy setting, websites that the user has visited will be deleted when the user clicks \"Delete\". If you do not configure this policy setting, the user will be able to select whether to delete or preserve websites the user visited when the user clicks \"Delete\".","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223127","rule_id":"SV-223127r960879","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Delete Browsing History\\Prevent Deleting Web sites that the User has Visited)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000169"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:517"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Deleting websites that the user has visited must be disallowed.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000089","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Delete Browsing History -&gt; 'Prevent Deleting Web sites that the User has Visited' to 'Enabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59713","V-46847"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8910B59-6C08-1014-94E2-BF517084B17F","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Privacy -&gt; 'Turn off InPrivate Browsing' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Privacy Criteria: If the value \"EnableInPrivateBrowsing\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223128","title":"SRG-APP-000080"},"rule_version":"DTBI780-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223128r960864_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223128","discussion":"InPrivate Browsing lets the user control whether or not Internet Explorer saves the browsing history, cookies, and other data. User control of settings is not the preferred control method. The InPrivate Browsing feature in Internet Explorer makes browser privacy easy by not storing history, cookies, temporary Internet files, or other data. If you enable this policy setting, InPrivate Browsing will be disabled. If you disable this policy setting, InPrivate Browsing will be available for use. If you do not configure this setting, InPrivate Browsing can be turned on or off through the registry.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223128","rule_id":"SV-223128r960864","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\InPrivate\\Turn off InPrivate Browsing)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000166"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:518"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"InPrivate Browsing must be disallowed.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000080","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Privacy -&gt; 'Turn off InPrivate Browsing' to 'Enabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59715","V-46849"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8910EC4-6C08-1014-8B2B-FBB6EF691B2D","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1206\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223129","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI800-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223129r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223129","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether a page may control embedded WebBrowser control via script. Scripted code hosted on sites located in this zone is more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser control is allowed. If you disable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser control is not allowed. If you do not configure this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser control can be enabled or disabled by the user. By default, script access to the WebBrowser control is only allowed in the Local Machine and Intranet Zones.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223129","rule_id":"SV-223129r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Allow scripting of Internet Explorer web browser control)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:519"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser control property must be disallowed (Internet zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59719","V-46853"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F891123A-6C08-1014-8D68-D40742846D7C","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"160A\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223130","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI810-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223130r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223130","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the local path information will be sent when uploading a file via a HTML form. If the local path information is sent, some information may be unintentionally revealed to the server. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether path information will be sent when uploading a file via a form. By default, path information will be sent.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223130","rule_id":"SV-223130r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Include local directory path when uploading files to a server)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:520"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"When uploading files to a server, the local directory path must be excluded (Internet zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.  "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59723","V-46857"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F89115AE-6C08-1014-8C57-A95572C86E49","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223131","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI815-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223131r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223131","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes when file or code installs are restricted. By default, the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will not be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you do not configure this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223131","rule_id":"SV-223131r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Notification Bar\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:541"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (Reserved).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59725","V-46859"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8911D60-6C08-1014-9FC7-9EB19B630DAB","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Prompt' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1806\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223132","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"rule_version":"DTBI820-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223132r961863_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223132","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the 'Open File - Security Warning' message appears when the user tries to open executable files or other potentially unsafe files (from an intranet file shared by using Windows Explorer, for example). If you enable this policy setting and set the drop-down box to \"Enable\", these files open without a security warning. If you set the drop-down box to \" Prompt\", a security warning appears before the files open. If you disable this policy these files do not open. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can configure how the computer handles these files.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223132","rule_id":"SV-223132r961863","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Launching programs and unsafe files)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:521"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Security Warning for unsafe files must be set to prompt (Internet zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Prompt' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59727","V-46861"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F89120F0-6C08-1014-9132-825636E0A02C","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND Criteria: If the value \"explorer.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223133","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI825-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223133r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223133","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes when file or code installs are restricted. By default, the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will not be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you do not configure this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223133","rule_id":"SV-223133r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Notification Bar\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:542"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (Explorer).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'. "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59729","V-46865"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F891247F-6C08-1014-A470-BF53B5A63CFE","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; ' Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"120b\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223134","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"rule_version":"DTBI830-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223134r961092_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223134","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the user is prompted to allow ActiveX controls to run on websites other than the website that installed the ActiveX control. If the user were to disable the setting for the zone, malicious ActiveX controls could be executed without the user's knowledge. Disabling this setting would allow the possibility for malicious ActiveX controls to be executed from non-approved domains within this zone without the user's knowledge. Enabling this setting enforces the default value and prohibits the user from changing the value. Websites should be moved into another zone if permissions need to be changed.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223134","rule_id":"SV-223134r961092","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Only allow approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:522"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"ActiveX controls without prompt property must be used in approved domains only (Internet zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59735","V-46869"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F89127ED-6C08-1014-B428-8EAB08139580","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_SECURITYBAND Criteria: If the value \"iexplore.exe\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223135","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI835-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223135r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223135","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes when file or code installs are restricted. By default, the Notification Bar is displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, the Notification Bar will not be displayed for Internet Explorer processes. If you do not configure this policy setting, the Notification Bar will be displayed for Internet Explorer processes.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223135","rule_id":"SV-223135r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Notification Bar\\Internet Explorer Processes)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:543"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes for Notification Bars must be enforced (iexplore).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features-&gt; Notification Bar-&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59745","V-46879"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8912B59-6C08-1014-A8DA-ABF5B1CCD89A","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"1409\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223136","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI840-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223136r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223136","discussion":"The Cross-Site Scripting Filter is designed to prevent users from becoming victims of unintentional information disclosure. This setting controls if the Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Filter detects and prevents cross-site script injection into websites in this zone. If you enable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be enabled for sites in this zone, and the XSS Filter will attempt to block cross-site script injections. If you disable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be disabled for sites in this zone, and Internet Explorer will permit cross-site script injections.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223136","rule_id":"SV-223136r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Turn on Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Filter must be Enabled and Enable selected)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:523"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Cross-Site Scripting Filter must be enforced (Internet zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59749","V-46883"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8912EC6-6C08-1014-9EA7-B78C47242FE1","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1206\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223137","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI850-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223137r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223137","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether a page may control embedded WebBrowser Control via script. Scripted code hosted on sites located in this zone is more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser Control is allowed. If you disable this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser Control is not allowed. If you do not configure this policy setting, script access to the WebBrowser Control can be enabled or disabled by the user. By default, script access to the WebBrowser Control is only allowed in the Local Machine and Intranet Zones.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223137","rule_id":"SV-223137r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow scripting of Internet Explorer web browser control)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:524"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser Control must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow scripting of Internet Explorer WebBrowser controls' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59751","V-46885"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8913233-6C08-1014-8341-95559B4D3991","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"160A\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223138","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI860-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223138r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223138","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the local path information will be sent when uploading a file via a HTML form. If the local path information is sent, some information may be unintentionally revealed to the server. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can choose whether path information will be sent when uploading a file via a form. By default, path information will be sent.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223138","rule_id":"SV-223138r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Include local directory path when uploading files to a server)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:525"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"When uploading files to a server, the local directory path must be excluded (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Include local path when user is uploading files to a server' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59755","V-46889"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F891359E-6C08-1014-BE5D-9153FD4A3E95","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1806\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223139","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"rule_version":"DTBI870-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223139r961863_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223139","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the 'Open File - Security Warning' message appears when the user tries to open executable files or other potentially unsafe files (from an intranet file shared by using Windows Explorer, for example). If you enable this policy setting and set the drop-down box to \"Enable\", these files open without a security warning. If you set the drop-down box to \"Prompt\", a security warning appears before the files open. If you disable this policy these files do not open. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user can configure how the computer handles these files.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223139","rule_id":"SV-223139r961863","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Launching programs and unsafe files)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:526"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Security Warning for unsafe files must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Show security warning for potentially unsafe files' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59759","V-46893"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8913910-6C08-1014-A17D-D793F95709C3","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"120b\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223140","title":"SRG-APP-000210"},"rule_version":"DTBI880-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223140r961092_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223140","discussion":"This policy setting controls whether or not the user is prompted to allow ActiveX controls to run on websites other than the website that installed the ActiveX control. If the user were to disable the setting for the zone, malicious ActiveX controls could be executed without the user's knowledge. Disabling this setting would allow the possibility for malicious ActiveX controls to be executed from non-approved domains within this zone without the user's knowledge. Enabling this setting enforces the default value and prohibits the user from changing the value. Websites should be moved into another zone if permissions need to be changed.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223140","rule_id":"SV-223140r961092","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Only allow approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001170"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:527"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"ActiveX controls without prompt property must be used in approved domains only (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000210","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Allow only approved domains to use ActiveX controls without prompt' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59761","V-46895"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8913C9E-6C08-1014-8D38-EA9B4038D4F9","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' must be 'Enabled', and 'Enable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1409\" is REG_DWORD = 0, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223141","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI890-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223141r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223141","discussion":"The Cross-Site Scripting Filter is designed to prevent users from becoming victims of unintentional information disclosure. This setting controls if the Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Filter detects and prevents cross-site script injection into websites in this zone. If you enable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be enabled for sites in this zone, and the XSS Filter will attempt to block cross-site script injections. If you disable this policy setting, the XSS Filter will be disabled for sites in this zone, and Internet Explorer will permit cross-site script injections.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223141","rule_id":"SV-223141r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Turn on Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) Filter)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:528"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Cross-Site Scripting Filter property must be enforced (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone -&gt; 'Turn on Cross-Site Scripting Filter' to 'Enabled', and select 'Enable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59763","V-46897"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8913FF7-6C08-1014-9367-86B3F0CAAE9F","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict ActiveX Install -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main\\FeatureControl\\FEATURE_RESTRICT_ACTIVEXINSTALL   Criteria: If the value \"(Reserved)\" is REG_SZ = 1, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223142","title":"SRG-APP-000112"},"rule_version":"DTBI900-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223142r960921_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223142","discussion":"Users often choose to install software such as ActiveX controls that are not permitted by their organization's security policy. Such software can pose significant security and privacy risks to networks. This policy setting enables blocking of ActiveX control installation prompts for Internet Explorer processes. If you enable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will be blocked for Internet Explorer processes. If you disable this policy setting, prompts for ActiveX control installations will not be blocked and these prompts will be displayed to users. If you do not configure this policy setting, the user's preference will be used to determine whether to block ActiveX control installations for Internet Explorer processes.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223142","rule_id":"SV-223142r960921","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Security Features\\Restrict ActiveX Install\\Internet Explorer Processes must be Enabled)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001695"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:529"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Internet Explorer Processes Restrict ActiveX Install must be enforced (Reserved).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000112","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Security Features -&gt; Restrict ActiveX Install -&gt; 'Internet Explorer Processes' to 'Enabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59769","V-46903"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8914344-6C08-1014-8AA6-9258C8D52B1E","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2103\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223143","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI910-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223143r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223143","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether script is allowed to update the status bar within the zone. A script running in the zone could cause false information to be displayed on the status bar, which could confuse the user and cause them to perform an undesirable action. If you enable this policy setting, script is allowed to update the status bar. If you disable this policy setting, script is not allowed to update the status bar. If you do not configure this policy setting, status bar updates via scripts will be disabled.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223143","rule_id":"SV-223143r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone Allow status bar updates via script must be Enabled and Disable selected)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:530"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Status bar updates via script must be disallowed (Internet zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59773","V-46907"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8914807-6C08-1014-95B0-8F7A0618C5DD","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2004\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223144","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"rule_version":"DTBI920-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223144r961863_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223144","discussion":"Unsigned components are more likely to contain malicious code and it is more difficult to determine the author of the application - therefore they should be avoided if possible. This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework components that are not signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute unsigned managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute unsigned managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute unsigned managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute unsigned managed components.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223144","rule_id":"SV-223144r961863","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:531"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Internet zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components not signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59787","V-46921"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8914C08-6C08-1014-B7AF-ACB5A99CDB4F","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2001\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223145","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"rule_version":"DTBI930-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223145r961863_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223145","discussion":"It may be possible for someone to host malicious content on a website that takes advantage of these components. This policy setting allows you to manage whether .NET Framework components that are signed with Authenticode can be executed from Internet Explorer. These components include managed controls referenced from an object tag and managed executables referenced from a link. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will execute signed managed components. If you select \"Prompt\" in the drop-down box, Internet Explorer will prompt the user to determine whether to execute signed managed components. If you disable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute signed managed components. If you do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not execute signed managed components.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223145","rule_id":"SV-223145r961863","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:532"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":".NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode must be disallowed to run (Internet zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Internet Zone 'Run .NET Framework-reliant components signed with Authenticode' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.  "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59793","V-46927"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8914F64-6C08-1014-880F-D0CF8BD90297","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow Scriptlets' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box.  Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"1209\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223146","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI940-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223146r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223146","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to manage whether scriptlets can be allowed. Scriptlets hosted on sites located in this zone are more likely to contain malicious code. If you enable this policy setting, users will be able to run scriptlets. If you disable this policy setting, users will not be able to run scriptlets. If you do not configure this policy setting, a scriptlet can be enabled or disabled by the user.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223146","rule_id":"SV-223146r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Network\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone\\Allow Scriptlets)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:533"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Scriptlets must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow Scriptlets' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59805","V-46939"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F89155CF-6C08-1014-B4CC-82A851176A14","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disable' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\4 Criteria: If the value \"2103\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223147","title":"SRG-APP-000141"},"rule_version":"DTBI950-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223147r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223147","discussion":"A script running in the zone could cause false information to be displayed on the status bar, which could confuse the user and cause an undesirable action. This policy setting allows you to manage whether script is allowed to update the status bar within the zone. If you enable this policy setting, script is allowed to update the status bar. If you disable this policy setting, script is not allowed to update the status bar. If you do not configure this policy setting, status bar updates via scripts will be disabled.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223147","rule_id":"SV-223147r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Restricted Sites Zone Allow status bar updates via script must be Enabled and Disabled selected)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:534"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Status bar updates via script must be disallowed (Restricted Sites zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer -&gt; Internet Control Panel -&gt; Security Page -&gt; Restricted Sites Zone 'Allow updates to status bar via script' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disable' from the drop-down box. "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59841","V-46975"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8915A85-6C08-1014-922A-A16D7C91FABF","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If McAfee ENS Web Control is being used, this is Not Applicable.\n\nThe policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Advanced Page 'Do not allow ActiveX controls to run in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled' must be 'Enabled'. Procedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Internet Explorer\\Main Criteria: If the value \"DisableEPMCompat\" is REG_DWORD = 1, this is not a finding.\n","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223148","title":"SRG-APP-000516"},"rule_version":"DTBI985-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223148r961863_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223148","discussion":"This setting prevents ActiveX controls from running in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled. When a user has an ActiveX control installed that is not compatible with Enhanced Protected Mode and a website attempts to load the control, Internet Explorer notifies the user and gives the option to run the website in regular Protected Mode. This policy setting disables this notification and forces all websites to run in Enhanced Protected Mode. Enhanced Protected Mode provides additional protection against malicious websites by using 64-bit processes on 64-bit versions of Windows. For computers running at least Windows 8, Enhanced Protected Mode also limits the locations Internet Explorer can read from in the registry and the file system. If you enable this policy setting, Internet Explorer will not give the user the option to disable Enhanced Protected Mode. All Protected Mode websites will run in Enhanced Protected Mode. If you disable or do not configure this policy setting, Internet Explorer notifies users and provides an option to run websites with incompatible ActiveX controls in regular Protected Mode.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223148","rule_id":"SV-223148r961863","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration/Administrative Templates/Windows Components/Internet Explorer/Internet Control Panel/Advanced Page/Do not allow ActiveX controls to run in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode )\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:556"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"When Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled, ActiveX controls must be disallowed to run in Protected Mode.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Advanced Page 'Do not allow ActiveX controls to run in Protected Mode when Enhanced Protected Mode is enabled' to 'Enabled'.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59847","V-46981"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8915E95-6C08-1014-97BB-CF3A1DC6841D","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Security Page-&gt; Internet Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows' must be 'Enabled', and 'Disabled' selected from the drop-down box. Procedure: Use the windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings\\Zones\\3 Criteria: If the value \"2709\" is REG_DWORD = 3, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-223149","title":"SRG-APP-000039"},"rule_version":"DTBI990-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-223149r1117169_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-223149","discussion":"This policy setting allows you to set options for dragging content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. If you enable this policy setting, users can drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. Users cannot change this setting. If you disable this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when both the source and destination are in different windows. Users cannot change this setting. If you do not configure this policy setting, users cannot drag content from one domain to a different domain when the source and destination are in different windows. Users can change this setting in the Internet Options dialog box.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-223149","rule_id":"SV-223149r1117169","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Computer Configuration\\Administrative Templates\\Windows Components\\Internet Explorer\\Internet Control Panel\\Security Page\\Internet Zone\\Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001414"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:547"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Dragging of content from different domains across windows must be disallowed (Internet zone).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000039","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration -&gt; Administrative Templates -&gt; Windows Components -&gt; Internet Explorer-&gt; Internet Control Panel-&gt; Security Page-&gt; Internet Zone 'Enable dragging of content from different domains across windows' to 'Enabled', and select 'Disabled' from the drop-down box.   "},{"legacy_ids":["SV-59337","V-46473"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F8916218-6C08-1014-94BA-AD2A8AA73915","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Advanced Page &gt;&gt; \"Turn off Encryption Support\" must be \"Enabled\".\n\nVerify the only option selected is \"Only use TLS 1.2\" from the drop-down box.\n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: HKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings!SecureProtocols.\n\nCriteria: If the value for \"SecureProtocols\" is not REG_DWORD = \"2048\", this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-250540","title":"SRG-APP-000416"},"rule_version":"DTBI014-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-250540r1117186_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-250540","discussion":"This parameter ensures only DOD-approved ciphers and algorithms are enabled for use by the web browser by allowing the user to turn on/off support for TLS and SSL. TLS is a protocol for protecting communications between the browser and the target server. When the browser attempts to set up a protected communication with the target server, the browser and server negotiate which protocol and version to use. The browser and server attempt to match each other's list of supported protocols and versions and pick the most preferred match.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000514, SRG-APP-000555, SRG-APP-000625, SRG-APP-000630, SRG-APP-000635","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-250540","rule_id":"SV-250540r1117186","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true ('turn off encryption support' setting is handled by Group Policy.)\nTest            :   true (TLS 1.2 must be selected for the IE option 'turn off encryption support' via Group Policy.)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-002450"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:580"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Turn off Encryption Support must be enabled.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000416","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Internet Control Panel &gt;&gt; Advanced Page &gt;&gt; \"Turn off Encryption Support\" to \"Enabled\".\n\nSelect only \"Only use TLS 1.2\" from the drop-down box."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-79219","V-64729"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F89165A2-6C08-1014-8095-B326F02DDF17","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; \"Allow fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)\" must be \"Enabled\", and \"No Sites\" selected from the drop-down box. If \"Allow fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)\" is not \"Enabled\" or any other drop-down option is selected, this is a finding. \n\nProcedure: Use the Windows Registry Editor to navigate to the following key: \n\nHKLM\\Software\\Policies\\Microsoft\\Windows\\CurrentVersion\\Internet Settings. \n\nCriteria: If the value \"EnableSSL3Fallback\" is REG_DWORD=0, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-250541","title":"SRG-APP-000416"},"rule_version":"DTBI1100-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-250541r1117186_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-250541","discussion":"This parameter ensures only DoD-approved ciphers and algorithms are enabled for use by the web browser by blocking an insecure fallback to SSL when TLS 1.0 or greater fails.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000514, SRG-APP-000555, SRG-APP-000625, SRG-APP-000630, SRG-APP-000635","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-250541","rule_id":"SV-250541r1117186","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true ('Allow Fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)' is set to 'Enabled' with 'Allow insecure fallback for:' set to 'No Sites')\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-002450"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.fso.ie:def:581"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Allow Fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer) must be disabled.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000416","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Set the policy value for Computer Configuration &gt;&gt; Administrative Templates &gt;&gt; Windows Components &gt;&gt; Internet Explorer &gt;&gt; Security Features &gt;&gt; \"Allow fallback to SSL 3.0 (Internet Explorer)\" to \"Enabled\", and select \"No Sites\" from the drop-down box.\n"},{"legacy_ids":[],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"F891695A-6C08-1014-B0A9-EC20F2C8371E","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Internet Explorer 11 is no longer supported by the vendor.\n\nIf Internet Explorer 11 is installed, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-252910","title":"SRG-APP-000456"},"rule_version":"DTBI999-IE11","reference_identifier":"4095","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-252910r1156566_rule","severity":"high","group_id_src":"V-252910","discussion":"Security flaws with software applications are discovered daily. Vendors are constantly updating and patching their products to address newly discovered security vulnerabilities. Organizations (including any contractor to the organization) are required to promptly install security-relevant software updates (e.g., patches, service packs, and hot fixes). Flaws discovered during security assessments, continuous monitoring, incident response activities, or information system error handling must also be addressed expeditiously.\n\nOrganization-defined time periods for updating security-relevant software may vary based on a variety of factors including, for example, the security category of the information system or the criticality of the update (i.e., severity of the vulnerability related to the discovered flaw).\n\nThis requirement will apply to software patch management solutions that are used to install patches across the enclave and also to applications that are not part of that patch management solution. For example, many browsers today provide the capability to install their own patch software. Patch criticality, as well as system criticality, will vary. Therefore, the tactical situations regarding the patch management process will also vary. This means the time period used must be a configurable parameter. Time frames for application of security-relevant software updates may depend on the Information Assurance Vulnerability Management (IAVM) process.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-252910","rule_id":"SV-252910r1156566","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:32\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nCriteria        :   false (All child tests must be true. (AND)) (negated)\nTest            :     true (Internet Explorer 11 is installed)\n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-002605"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IE11_V2R8_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV15-oval.xml","name":"oval:mil.disa.stig.win:def:252910"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The version of Internet Explorer running on the system must be a supported version.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000456","stig_uuid":"F87FF29B-6C08-1014-9B30-D9A31A2A24ED","fix_text":"Remove the Internet Explorer 11 application."}]},{"stig_name":"Microsoft IIS 10.0 Server Security Technical Implementation Guide","classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","release_info":"Release: 6 Benchmark Date: 05 Jan 2026","version":"3","display_name":"Microsoft IIS 10.0 Server","reference_identifier":"4052","stig_id":"IIS_10-0_Server_STIG","uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","size":42,"rules":[{"legacy_ids":["SV-109211","V-100107"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDA6942-6C09-1014-BCE9-A017CD8DEDE2","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If the server is hosting WSUS, this is Not Applicable.\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\nClick the IIS 10.0 server name.\nClick the \"Logging\" icon.\nUnder Log Event Destination, verify the \"Both log file and ETW event\" radio button is selected.\n\nIf the \"Both log file and ETW event\" radio button is not selected, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218786","title":"SRG-APP-000092-WSR-000055"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000103","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218786r1022652_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218786","discussion":"Internet Information Services (IIS) on Windows Server 2012 provides basic logging capabilities. However, because IIS takes some time to flush logs to disk, administrators do not have access to logging information in real-time. In addition, text-based log files can be difficult and time-consuming to process.\n\nIn IIS 10.0, the administrator has the option of sending logging information to Event Tracing for Windows (ETW). This option gives the administrator the ability to use standard query tools, or create custom tools, for viewing real-time logging information in ETW. This provides a significant advantage over parsing text-based log files that are not updated in real time.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000092-WSR-000055, SRG-APP-000108-WSR-000166, SRG-APP-000358-WSR-000063","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218786","rule_id":"SV-218786r1022652","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Both the log file and Event Tracing for Windows (ETW) for the IIS 10.0 web server must be enabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Webserver//system.applicationHost/sites/siteDefaults.logFile.logTargetW3C = 'File' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'File, ETW' \n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-000139","CCI-001464","CCI-001851"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.0.server:def:218786"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Both the log file and Event Tracing for Windows (ETW) for the IIS 10.0 web server must be enabled.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000092-WSR-000055","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 server name.\n\nClick the \"Logging\" icon.\n\nUnder Log Event Destination, select the \"Both log file and ETW event\" radio button.\n\nUnder the \"Actions\" pane, click \"Apply\"."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109215","V-100111"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDA70EA-6C09-1014-BE86-F9306040F1B6","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If the server is hosting WSUS, this is Not Applicable.\n\nAccess the IIS 10.0 web server IIS Manager.\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\nUnder \"IIS\", double-click the \"Logging\" icon.\nVerify the \"Format:\" under \"Log File\" is configured to \"W3C\".\nSelect \"Fields\".\nUnder \"Custom Fields\", verify the following fields have been configured:\nRequest Header &gt;&gt; Connection.\nRequest Header &gt;&gt; Warning.\nIf any of the above fields are not selected, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218788","title":"SRG-APP-000099-WSR-000061"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000110","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218788r1156543_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218788","discussion":"Web server logging capability is critical for accurate forensic analysis. Without sufficient and accurate information, a correct replay of the events cannot be determined.\n\nAscertaining the success or failure of an event is important during forensic analysis. Correctly determining the outcome will add information to the overall reconstruction of the loggable event. By determining the success or failure of the event correctly, analysis of the enterprise can be undertaken to determine if events tied to the event occurred in other areas within the enterprise.\n\nWithout sufficient information establishing the success or failure of the logged event, investigation into the cause of event is severely hindered. The success or failure also provides a means to measure the impact of an event and help authorized personnel determine the appropriate response. Log record content that may be necessary to satisfy the requirement of this control includes, but is not limited to, time stamps, source and destination IP addresses, user/process identifiers, event descriptions, application-specific events, success/fail indications, file names involved, access control, or flow control rules invoked.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218788","rule_id":"SV-218788r1156543","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false ((Custom Fields - Request Header - Connection) Access the IIS 10.0 web server IIS Manager. Click the IIS 10.0 web server name. Under IIS, double-click the Logging icon. Verify the Format: under Log File is configured to W3C. Select the Fields button. Under Custom Fields, verify the following fields have been configured: Request Header - Connection Request Header - Warning Server Variable - HTTP_CONNECTION If any of the above fields are not selected, this is a finding.)\nResult Analysis :        .  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false ((Custom Fields - Request Header - Warning) Access the IIS 10.0 web server IIS Manager. Click the IIS 10.0 web server name. Under IIS, double-click the Logging icon. Verify the Format: under Log File is configured to W3C. Select the Fields button. Under Custom Fields, verify the following fields have been configured: Request Header - Connection Request Header - Warning Server Variable - HTTP_CONNECTION If any of the above fields are not selected, this is a finding.)\nResult Analysis :        .  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   true (Site Default Logfile format must be set to W3C)\n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-000134"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.0.server:def:218788"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 web server must produce log records that contain sufficient information to establish the outcome (success or failure) of IIS 10.0 web server events.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000099-WSR-000061","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Access the IIS 10.0 web server IIS Manager.\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\nUnder \"IIS\", double-click the \"Logging\" icon.\nVerify the \"Format:\" under \"Log File\" is configured to \"W3C\".\nSelect \"Fields\".\nUnder \"Custom Fields\", click \"Add Field...\".\nFor each field being added, give a name unique to what the field is capturing.\nClick on the \"Source Type\" drop-down list and select \"Request Header\".\nClick the \"Source\" drop-down list, and select \"Connection\".\nClick \"OK\" to add.\n\nClick the \"Source Type\" drop-down list, and select \"Request Header\".\nClick the \"Source\" drop-down list, and select \"Warning\".\nClick \"OK\" to add.\nClick \"Apply\" under the \"Actions\" pane."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109217","V-100113"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDA7D7F-6C09-1014-AD18-D671824BF468","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If the server is hosting WSUS, this is Not Applicable.\n\nAccess the IIS 10.0 web server IIS Manager.\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\nUnder \"IIS\", double-click the \"Logging\" icon.\nVerify the \"Format:\" under \"Log File\" is configured to \"W3C\".\nSelect \"Fields\".\nUnder \"Standard Fields\", verify \"User Agent\", \"User Name\", and \"Referrer\" are selected.\nUnder \"Custom Fields\", verify the following field has been configured:\nRequest Header &gt;&gt; Authorization.\nResponse Header &gt;&gt; Content-Type.\nIf any of the above fields are not selected, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218789","title":"SRG-APP-000100-WSR-000064"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000111","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218789r1156546_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218789","discussion":"Web server logging capability is critical for accurate forensic analysis. Without sufficient and accurate information, a correct replay of the events cannot be determined.\n\nDetermining user accounts, processes running on behalf of the user, and running process identifiers also enable a better understanding of the overall event. User tool identification is also helpful to determine if events are related to overall user access or specific client tools.\n\nLog record content that may be necessary to satisfy the requirement of this control includes: time stamps, source and destination addresses, user/process identifiers, event descriptions, success/fail indications, file names involved, and access control or flow control rules invoked.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218789","rule_id":"SV-218789r1156546","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Site Default Logfile format must be set to W3C)\nTest            :   true ((Standard Field - User Agent) )\nTest            :   true ((User Name Field) Open the IIS 10.0 Manager. Click the IIS 10.0 web server name. Click the Logging icon. Under Format select W3C. Click Select Fields, verify at a minimum the following fields are checked: Date, Time, Client IP Address, User Name, Method, URI Query, Protocol Status, and Referrer. If not, this is a finding.)\nTest            :   true ((Referrer Field) Open the IIS 10.0 Manager. Click the IIS 10.0 web server name. Click the Logging icon. Under Format select W3C. Click Select Fields, verify at a minimum the following fields are checked: Date, Time, Client IP Address, User Name, Method, URI Query, Protocol Status, and Referrer. If not, this is a finding.)\nTest            :   false ((Custom Fields - Request Header - Authorization) )\nResult Analysis :        .  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false ((Custom Fields - Response Header - Content-Type) )\nResult Analysis :        .  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-001487"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.0.server:def:218789"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 web server must produce log records containing sufficient information to establish the identity of any user/subject or process associated with an event.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000100-WSR-000064","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Access the IIS 10.0 web server IIS Manager.\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\nUnder \"IIS\", double-click the \"Logging\" icon.\nVerify the \"Format:\" under \"Log File\" is configured to \"W3C\".\nSelect \"Fields\".\nUnder \"Standard Fields\", select \"User Agent\", \"User Name\", and \"Referrer\".\nUnder \"Custom Fields\", select the following fields:\nClick the \"Source Type\" drop-down list, and select \"Request Header\".\nClick on \"Source\" drop-down, list and select \"Authorization\".\nClick \"OK\" to add.\n\nClick the \"Source\" drop-down list, and select \"Content-Type\".\nClick the \"Source Type\" drop-down list, and select \"Response Header\".\nClick \"OK\" to add.\nClick \"OK\".\nClick \"Apply\" under the \"Actions\" pane."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109219","V-100115"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDA83D6-6C09-1014-8BD5-BA99CC8E1D4D","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"This check does not apply to service account IDs utilized by automated services necessary to process, manage, and store log files.\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\n\nClick the \"Logging\" icon.\n\nClick \"Browse\" and navigate to the directory where the log files are stored.\n\nRight-click the log file directory to review.\n\nClick \"Properties\".\n\nClick the \"Security\" tab.\n\nVerify log file access is restricted as follows. Otherwise, this is a finding.\nSYSTEM - Full Control, This folder, subfolders and files\nAdministrators - Full Control, This folder, subfolders and files\n\nNote:  A \"Web Administrators\", etc., type group that is an approved group of administrators is also allowed, and must be given \"Full Control, This folder, subfolders and files\" permissions.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218790","title":"SRG-APP-000120-WSR-000070"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000115","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218790r1067580_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218790","discussion":"A major tool in exploring the website use, attempted use, unusual conditions, and problems are the access and error logs. In the event of a security incident, these logs can provide the system administrator (SA) and the web manager with valuable information. Failure to protect log files could enable an attacker to modify the log file data or falsify events to mask an attacker's activity.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000120-WSR-000070, SRG-APP-000118-WSR-000068, SRG-APP-000118-WSR-000069","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218790","rule_id":"SV-218790r1067580","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-218790, SV-218790r1067580, SRG-APP-000120-WSR-000070)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-000164"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.0.server:questionnaire:701"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The log information from the IIS 10.0 web server must be protected from unauthorized modification or deletion.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000120-WSR-000070","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\n\nClick the \"Logging\" icon.\n\nClick \"Browse\" and navigate to the directory where the log files are stored.\n\nRight-click the log file directory to review and click \"Properties\".\n\nClick the \"Security\" tab.\n\nSet the log file permissions for the appropriate group(s).\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nSelect \"Apply\" in the \"Actions\" pane."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109221","V-100117"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDA8C5F-6C09-1014-A232-C8E89D98A045","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"The IIS 10.0 web server and website log files should be backed up by the system backup.\n\nTo determine if log files are backed up by the system backup, determine the location of the web server log files and each website's log files.\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 server name.\n\nClick the \"Logging\" icon.\n\nUnder \"Log File\" &gt;&gt; \"Directory\" obtain the path of the log file.\n\nOnce all locations are known, consult with the System Administrator to review the server's backup procedure and policy.\n\nVerify the paths of all log files are part of the system backup.\nVerify log files are backed up to an unrelated system or onto separate media on which the system the web server is running.\n\nIf the paths of all log files are not part of the system backup and/or not backed up to a separate media, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218791","title":"SRG-APP-000125-WSR-000071"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000116","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218791r960948_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218791","discussion":"Protection of log data includes ensuring log data is not accidentally lost or deleted. Backing up log records to an unrelated system, or onto separate media than the system on which the web server is running, helps to ensure the log records will be retained in the event of a catastrophic system failure.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218791","rule_id":"SV-218791r960948","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-218791, SV-218791r960948, SRG-APP-000125-WSR-000071)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-001348"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.0.server:questionnaire:901"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The log data and records from the IIS 10.0 web server must be backed up onto a different system or media.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000125-WSR-000071","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Configure system backups to include the directory paths of all IIS 10.0 web server and website log files."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109223","V-100119"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDA9144-6C09-1014-B18C-E7B3E53779E8","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Interview the System Administrator about the role of the IIS 10.0 web server.\n\nIf the IIS 10.0 web server is hosting an application, have the SA provide supporting documentation on how the application's user management is accomplished outside of the IIS 10.0 web server.\n\nIf the IIS 10.0 web server is not hosting an application, this is Not Applicable.\n\nIf the IIS web server is performing user management for hosted applications, this is a finding.\n\nIf the IIS 10.0 web server is hosting an application and the SA cannot provide supporting documentation on how the application's user management is accomplished outside of the IIS 10.0 web server, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218792","title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000015"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000117","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218792r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218792","discussion":"User management and authentication can be an essential part of any application hosted by the web server. Along with authenticating users, the user management function must perform several other tasks enterprise-wide, such as password complexity, locking users after a configurable number of failed logons, and management of temporary and emergency accounts.\n\nThe web server contains a minimal user management function, but the web server user management function does not offer enterprise-wide user management, and user management is not the primary function of the web server. User management for the hosted applications should be done through a facility built for enterprise-wide user management, such as LDAP and Active Directory.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218792","rule_id":"SV-218792r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-218792, SV-218792r960963, SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000015)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.0.server:questionnaire:1101"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 web server must not perform user management for hosted applications.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000015","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Reconfigure any hosted applications on the IIS 10.0 web server to perform user management outside the IIS 10.0 web server.\n\nDocument how the hosted application user management is accomplished."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109225","V-100121"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDA9577-6C09-1014-8D9A-C39F892EB4CB","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Click âStartâ.\n\nOpen Control Panel.\n\nClick âProgramsâ.\n\nClick âPrograms and Featuresâ.\n\nReview the installed programs. If any programs are installed other than those required for the IIS 10.0 web services, this is a finding.\n\nNote: If additional software is needed, supporting documentation must be signed by the ISSO.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218793","title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000075"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000118","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218793r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218793","discussion":"A web server can provide many features, services, and processes. Some of these may be deemed unnecessary or too unsecure to run on a production DoD system.\n\nThe web server must provide the capability to disable, uninstall, or deactivate functionality and services deemed non-essential to the web server mission or that adversely impact server performance.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218793","rule_id":"SV-218793r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-218793, SV-218793r960963, SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000075)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.0.server:questionnaire:1301"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 web server must only contain functions necessary for operation.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000075","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Remove all unapproved programs and roles from the production IIS 10.0 web server."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109227","V-100123"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDA997B-6C09-1014-96CE-B8266EB44D21","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nUnder the \"Connections\" pane on the left side of the management console, select the IIS 10.0 web server.\n\nIf, under the IIS installed features \"Application Request Routing Cache\" is not present, this is not a finding.\n\nIf, under the IIS installed features \"Application Request Routing Cache\" is present, double-click the icon to open the feature.\n\nFrom the right \"Actions\" pane under \"Proxy\", select \"Server Proxy Settings...\".\n\nIn the \"Application Request Routing\" settings window, verify whether \"Enable proxy\" is selected.\n\nIf \"Enable proxy\" is selected under the \"Application Request Routing\" settings, this is a finding.\n\nIf the server has been approved to be a Proxy server, this requirement is Not Applicable.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218794","title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000076"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000119","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218794r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218794","discussion":"A web server should be primarily a web server or a proxy server but not both, for the same reasons that other multi-use servers are not recommended. Scanning for web servers that also proxy requests into an otherwise protected network is a common attack, making the attack anonymous.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218794","rule_id":"SV-218794r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   false (Application Request Routing Cache - Proxy Enable Setting)\nTest            :   true (Application Request Routing Cache - Proxy Installation Status)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.0.server:def:218794"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 web server must not be both a website server and a proxy server.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000076","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nUnder the \"Connections\" pane on the left side of the management console, select the IIS 10.0 web server.\n\nUnder the IIS installed features, if \"Application Request Routing Cache\" is present, double-click the icon to open the feature.\n\nFrom the right \"Actions\" pane, under \"Proxy\", select \"Server Proxy Settings...\".\n\nIn the \"Application Request Routing\" settings window, remove the check from the \"Enable proxy\" check box.\n\nClick \"Apply\" in the \"Actions\" pane."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109229","V-100125"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDA9DC6-6C09-1014-B009-92C5F9D06B1E","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Navigate to the following folders:\n\ninetpub\\\nProgram Files\\Common Files\\System\\msadc\nProgram Files (x86)\\Common Files\\System\\msadc\n\nIf the folder or sub-folders contain any executable sample code, example applications, or tutorials which are not explicitly used by a production website, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218795","title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000077"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000120","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218795r960963_rule","severity":"high","group_id_src":"V-218795","discussion":"Web server documentation, sample code, example applications, and tutorials may be an exploitable threat to a web server. A production web server may only contain components that are operationally necessary (i.e., compiled code, scripts, web content, etc.). Delete all directories containing samples and any scripts used to execute the samples.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218795","rule_id":"SV-218795r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (.hlp,.htm,.asp file extensions shall not exist)\nResult Analysis :        Existence requirement is 'none_exists' and 57 collected items exist, so result is false\nTest            :   true (.hlp,.htm,.asp file extensions shall not exist)\nTest            :   true (.hlp,.htm,.asp file extensions shall not exist)\n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.0.server:def:218795"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"All IIS 10.0 web server sample code, example applications, and tutorials must be removed from a production IIS 10.0 server.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000077","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Remove any executable sample code, example applications, or tutorials which are not explicitly used by a production website."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109231","V-100127"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDAA1C9-6C09-1014-9F0A-C1AB136B2560","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Access the IIS 10.0 web server.\n\nAccess âAppsâ menu. Under âAdministrative Toolsâ, select âComputer Managementâ.\n\nIn the left pane, expand \"Local Users and Groups\" and click \"Users\".\n\nReview the local users listed in the middle pane.\n\nIf any local accounts are present and were created by features which have been uninstalled or are not used, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218796","title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000078"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000121","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218796r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218796","discussion":"Accounts used for web server features such as documentation, sample code, example applications, tutorials, utilities, and services created when the feature is not installed, become an exploitable threat to a web server.\n\nThese accounts become inactive, are not monitored through regular use, and passwords for the accounts are not created or updated. An attacker, through very little effort, can use these accounts to gain access to the web server and begin investigating ways to elevate the account privileges.\n\nThe accounts used for web server features not installed must not be created and must be deleted when these features are uninstalled.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218796","rule_id":"SV-218796r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-218796, SV-218796r960963, SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000078)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.0.server:questionnaire:1901"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The accounts created by uninstalled features (i.e., tools, utilities, specific, etc.) must be deleted from the IIS 10.0 server.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000078","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Access the IIS 10.0 web server.\n\nAccess âAppsâ menu. Under âAdministrative Toolsâ, select âComputer Managementâ.\n\nIn the left pane, expand \"Local Users and Groups\" and click \"Users\".\n\nDelete any local accounts which were created by features which have been uninstalled or are not used."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109233","V-100129"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDAA61C-6C09-1014-965E-9DDE7E15D5B1","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Consult with the System Administrator and review all of the IIS 10.0 and Operating System features installed.\n\nDetermine if any features installed are no longer necessary for operation.\n\nIf any utility programs, features, or modules are installed which are not necessary for operation, this is a finding.\n\nIf any unnecessary Operating System features are installed, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218797","title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000080"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000123","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218797r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218797","discussion":"Just as running unneeded services and protocols is a danger to the web server at the lower levels of the OSI model, running unneeded utilities and programs is a danger at the application layer of the OSI model. Office suites, development tools, and graphic editors are examples of such troublesome programs.\n\nIndividual productivity tools have no legitimate place or use on an enterprise production web server and are prone to security risks. The web server installation process must provide options allowing the installer to choose which utility programs, services, and modules are to be installed or removed. By having a process for installation and removal, the web server is guaranteed to be in a more stable and secure state than if these services and programs were installed and removed manually.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218797","rule_id":"SV-218797r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-218797, SV-218797r960963, SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000080)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.0.server:questionnaire:2101"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 web server must be reviewed on a regular basis to remove any Operating System features, utility programs, plug-ins, and modules not necessary for operation.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000080","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Remove all utility programs, Operating System features, or modules installed that are not necessary for web server operation."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109235","V-100131"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDAABE5-6C09-1014-8607-84C88EE4F820","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If the server is hosting WSUS, this is not applicable.\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\n\nUnder IIS, double-click the \"MIME Types\" icon.\n\nFrom the \"Group by:\" drop-down list, select \"Content Type\".\n\nFrom the list of extensions under \"Application\", verify MIME types for OS shell program extensions have been removed, to include at a minimum, the following extensions:\n\n.exe\n.dll\n.com\n.bat\n.csh\n\nIf any OS shell MIME types are configured, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218798","title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000081"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000124","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218798r1112381_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218798","discussion":"Controlling what a user of a hosted application can access is part of the security posture of the web server. Any time a user can access more functionality than is needed for the operation of the hosted application poses a security issue. A user with too much access can view information that is not needed for the user's job role, or the user could use the function in an unintentional manner.\n\nA MIME tells the web server the type of program, various file types, and extensions and what external utilities or programs are needed to execute the file type.\n\nA shell is a program that serves as the basic interface between the user and the operating system to ensure hosted application users do not have access to these programs. Shell programs may execute shell escapes and can perform unauthorized activities that could damage the security posture of the web server.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218798","rule_id":"SV-218798r1112381","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Open the IIS 10.0 Manager. Click the IIS 10.0 web server name. Under IIS, double-click the âMIME Typesâ icon. From the Group by: drop-down list, select Content Type. From the list of extensions under Application, verify MIME types for OS shell program extensions have been removed, to include at a minimum, the following extensions: .exe .dll .com .bat .csh If any OS shell MIME types are configured, this is a finding.)\nResult Analysis :        Collected Item did not meet the state requirement.\n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.0.server:def:218798"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 web server must have Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) that invoke OS shell programs disabled.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000081","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\n\nUnder IIS, double-click the \"MIME Types\" icon.\n\nFrom the \"Group by:\" drop-down list, select \"Content Type\".\n\nFrom the list of extensions under \"Application\", remove MIME types for OS shell program extensions, to include at a minimum, the following extensions:\n\n.exe\n.dll\n.com\n.bat\n.csh\n\nUnder the \"Actions\" pane, click \"Apply\"."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109237","V-100133"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDAB02F-6C09-1014-8E0E-FF9DF00122EC","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\n\nReview the features listed under the âIIS\" section.\n\nIf the \"WebDAV Authoring Rules\" icon exists, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218799","title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000085"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000125","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218799r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218799","discussion":"A web server can be installed with functionality that by its nature is not secure. Web Distributed Authoring (WebDAV) is an extension to the HTTP protocol which, when developed, was meant to allow users to create, change, and move documents on a server, typically a web server or web share. Allowing this functionality, development, and deployment is much easier for web authors.\n\nWebDAV is not widely used and has serious security concerns because it may allow clients to modify unauthorized files on the web server.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218799","rule_id":"SV-218799r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Verify IIS WebDAV Authoring Rules is not installed via registry test)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.0.server:def:218799"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 web server must have Web Distributed Authoring and Versioning (WebDAV) disabled.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000085","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Access Server Manager on the IIS 10.0 web server.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\n\nClick on \"Manage\".\n\nSelect \"Add Roles and Features\".\n\nClick \"Next\" in the \"Before you begin\" dialog box.\n\nSelect \"Role-based or feature-based installation\" on the \"Installation Type\" dialog box and click \"Next\".\n\nSelect the IIS 10.0 web server in the \"Server Selection\" dialog box.\n\nFrom the \"Windows Features\" dialog box, navigate to \"World Wide Web Services\" &gt;&gt; \"Common HTTP Features\".\n\nDe-select \"WebDAV Publishing\", and click \"Next\" to complete removing the WebDAV Publishing feature from the IIS 10.0 web server."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109241","V-100137"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDAB461-6C09-1014-A927-E04A30A2D3F6","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Search the system for files with either .java or .jpp extensions.\n\nIf files with .java or .jpp extensions are found, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218801","title":"SRG-APP-000206-WSR-000128"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000130","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218801r961083_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218801","discussion":"Mobile code in hosted applications allows the developer to add functionality and displays to hosted applications that are fluid, as opposed to a static web page. The data presentation becomes more appealing to the user, is easier to analyze, and is less complicated to navigate through the hosted application and data.\n\nSome mobile code technologies in use in today's applications are: Java, JavaScript, ActiveX, PDF, Postscript, Shockwave movies, Flash animations, and VBScript. The DoD has created policies that define the usage of mobile code on DoD systems. The usage restrictions and implementation guidance apply to both the selection and use of mobile code installed on organizational servers and mobile code downloaded and executed on individual workstations.\n\nSource code for a Java program is often stored in files with either .java or .jpp file extensions. From the .java and .jpp files the Java compiler produces a binary file with an extension of .class. The .java or .jpp file could therefore reveal sensitive information regarding an application's logic and permissions to resources on the server.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218801","rule_id":"SV-218801r961083","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (If files with .java or .jpp extensions are found, this is a finding.)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001166"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.0.server:def:218801"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Java software installed on a production IIS 10.0 web server must be limited to .class files and the Java Virtual Machine.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000206-WSR-000128","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Remove all files from the web server with both .java and .jpp extensions."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109243","V-100139"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDAB885-6C09-1014-95BF-B530744485BA","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Obtain a list of the user accounts with access to the system, including all local and domain accounts. \n\nReview the privileges to the web server for each account.\n\nVerify with the system administrator or the ISSO that all privileged accounts are mission essential and documented.\n\nVerify with the system administrator or the ISSO that all non-administrator access to shell scripts and operating system functions are mission essential and documented.\n\nIf undocumented privileged accounts are found, this is a finding.\n\nIf undocumented non-administrator access to shell scripts and operating system functions are found, this is a finding.\n\nIf this IIS 10 installation is supporting Microsoft Exchange, and not otherwise hosting any content, this requirement is Not Applicable.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218802","title":"SRG-APP-000211-WSR-000030"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000131","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218802r1138072_rule","severity":"high","group_id_src":"V-218802","discussion":"As a rule, accounts on a web server are to be kept to a minimum. Only administrators, web managers, developers, auditors, and web authors require accounts on the machine hosting the web server. This is in addition to the anonymous web user account. The resources to which these accounts have access must also be closely monitored and controlled. Only the SA needs access to all the systemâs capabilities, while the web administrator and associated staff require access and control of the web content and web server configuration files. The anonymous web user account must not have access to system resources as that account could then control the server.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218802","rule_id":"SV-218802r1138072","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT I, V-218802, SV-218802r1138072, SRG-APP-000211-WSR-000030)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-001082"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.0.server:questionnaire:2901"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"IIS 10.0 Web server accounts accessing the directory tree, the shell, or other operating system functions and utilities must only be administrative accounts.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000211-WSR-000030","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Ensure non-administrators are not allowed access to the directory tree, the shell, or other operating system functions and utilities.\n\nAll non-administrator access to shell scripts and operating system functions must be mission essential and documented."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109245","V-100141"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDAC01B-6C09-1014-8FFF-E35E0AE8CD97","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Review the IIS 10.0 web server configuration with the System Administrator.\n\nDetermine if the IIS 10.0 web server hosts any applications.\n\nIf the IIS 10.0 web server does not host any applications, this is Not Applicable.\n\nIf the IIS 10.0 web server is hosting Exchange, this is Not Applicable.\n\nIf the IIS 10.0 web server hosts applications, review the application's management functionality and authentication methods with the System Administrator to determine if the management of the application is accomplished with the same functions and authentication methods as the web server management.\n\nIf the IIS 10.0 web server management and the application's management functionality is not separated, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218803","title":"SRG-APP-000211-WSR-000129"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000132","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218803r1138074_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218803","discussion":"The separation of user functionality from web server management can be accomplished by moving management functions to a separate IP address or port. To further separate the management functions, separate authentication methods and certificates should be used.\n\nBy moving the management functionality, the possibility of accidental discovery of the management functions by non-privileged users during hosted application use is minimized.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218803","rule_id":"SV-218803r1138074","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-218803, SV-218803r1138074, SRG-APP-000211-WSR-000129)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-001082"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.0.server:questionnaire:3101"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 web server must separate the hosted applications from hosted web server management functionality.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000211-WSR-000129","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Develop a method to manage the hosted applications, either by moving its management functions off of the IIS 10.0 web server or by accessing the application's management via a uniquely assigned IP address."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109247","V-100143"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDAC6DB-6C09-1014-B417-A42218605621","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If ASP.NET is not installed, this is Not Applicable.\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\nUnder \"ASP.Net\", double-click the \"Session State\" icon.\nUnder \"Cookie Settings\", verify the \"Mode\" has \"Use Cookies\" selected from the drop-down list.\nIf the \"Cookie Settings\" \"Mode\" is not set to \"Use Cookies\", this is a finding.\n\nAlternative method:\nClick the site name.\nSelect \"Configuration Editor\" under the \"Management\" section.\nFrom the \"Section:\" drop-down list at the top of the configuration editor, locate \"system.web/sessionState\".\nVerify the \"cookieless\" is set to \"UseCookies\".\nIf the \"cookieless\" is not set to \"UseCookies\", this is a finding.\n\nNote: If IIS 10.0 server/site is used only for system-to-system maintenance, does not allow users to connect to interface, and is restricted to specific system IPs, this is Not Applicable.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218804","title":"SRG-APP-000223-WSR-000011"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000134","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218804r1043180_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218804","discussion":"Cookies are used to exchange data between the web server and the client. Cookies, such as a session cookie, may contain session information and user credentials used to maintain a persistent connection between the user and the hosted application since HTTP/HTTPS is a stateless protocol.\n\nUsing URI will embed the session ID as a query string in the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) request and then the URI is redirected to the originally requested URL. The changed URI request is used for the duration of the session, so no cookie is necessary.\n\nBy requiring expired session IDs to be regenerated while using URI, potential attackers have less time to capture a cookie and gain access to the Web server content.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000223-WSR-000011, SRG-APP-000220-WSR-000201","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218804","rule_id":"SV-218804r1043180","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","status":"not_applicable","ccis":["CCI-001664"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.0.server:def:218804"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 web server must use cookies to track session state.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000223-WSR-000011","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\n\nUnder \"ASP.Net\", double-click the \"Session State\" icon.\n\nUnder \"Cookie Settings\", select \"Use Cookiesâ from the \"Mode\" drop-down list.\n\nClick \"Apply\" in the \"Actions\" pane."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109249","V-100145"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDACB35-6C09-1014-9676-F9834AB3B61E","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If ASP.NET is not installed, this is Not Applicable.\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\n\nUnder the \"ASP.NET\" section, select \"Session State\".\n\nUnder \"Cookie Settings\", verify the \"Use Cookies\" mode is selected from the \"Mode:\" drop-down list.\n\nUnder \"Time-out (in minutes)\", verify a maximum of 15 minutes is entered.\n\nIf the \"Use Cookies\" mode is selected and Time-out (in minutes) is configured for \"15 minutes\" (or less), this is not a finding.\n\nAlternative method:\n\nClick the site name.\n\nSelect \"Configuration Editor\" under the \"Management\" section.\n\nFrom the \"Section:\" drop-down list at the top of the configuration editor, locate \"system.web/sessionState\".\n\nVerify the \"cookieless\" is set to \"UseCookies\".\n\nIf the \"cookieless\" is not set to \"UseCookies\", this is a finding.\n\nNote: If IIS 10.0 server/site is used only for system-to-system maintenance, does not allow users to connect to interface, and is restricted to specific system IPs, this is Not Applicable.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218805","title":"SRG-APP-000223-WSR-000145"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000135","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218805r1067583_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218805","discussion":"ASP.NET provides a session state, which is available as the HttpSessionState class, as a method of storing session-specific information that is visible only within the session. ASP.NET session state identifies requests from the same browser during a limited time window as a session and provides the ability to persist variable values for the duration of that session.\n\nWhen using the URI mode for cookie settings under session state, IIS will reject and reissue session IDs that do not have active sessions. Configuring IIS to expire session IDs and regenerate tokens gives a potential attacker less time to capture a cookie and gain access to server content.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218805","rule_id":"SV-218805r1067583","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","status":"not_applicable","ccis":["CCI-001664"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.0.server:def:218805"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 web server must accept only system-generated session identifiers.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000223-WSR-000145","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\n\nUnder the \"ASP.NET\" section, select \"Session State\".\n\nUnder \"Cookie Settings\", select the \"Use Cookies\" mode from the \"Mode:\" drop-down list.\n\nUnder \"Time-out (in minutes)\", enter a value of \"15 or less\"."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109251","V-100147"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDACF38-6C09-1014-ADD3-A063C3885FDF","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Interview the System Administrator for the IIS 10.0 web server.\n\nAsk for documentation on the disaster recovery methods tested and planned for the IIS 10.0 web server in the event of the necessity for rollback.\n\nIf documentation for a disaster recovery has not been established, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218806","title":"SRG-APP-000225-WSR-000074"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000136","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218806r961122_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218806","discussion":"Making certain that the web server has not been updated by an unauthorized user is always a concern. Adding patches, functions, and modules that are untested and not part of the baseline opens the possibility for security risks. The web server must offer, and not hinder, a method that allows for the quick and easy reinstallation of a verified and patched baseline to guarantee the production web server is up-to-date and has not been modified to add functionality or expose security risks.\n\nWhen the web server does not offer a method to roll back to a clean baseline, external methods, such as a baseline snapshot or virtualizing the web server, can be used.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218806","rule_id":"SV-218806r961122","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-218806, SV-218806r961122, SRG-APP-000225-WSR-000074)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-001190"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.0.server:questionnaire:3701"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 web server must augment re-creation to a stable and known baseline.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000225-WSR-000074","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Prepare documentation for disaster recovery methods for the IIS 10.0 web server in the event of the necessity for rollback.\n\nDocument and test the disaster recovery methods designed."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109253","V-100149"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDAD312-6C09-1014-AD03-B9515394809D","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If ASP.NET is not installed, this is Not Applicable.\n\nNote: If the IIS 10.0 web server is hosting Exchange, this is Not Applicable.\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\n\nDouble-click the \"Machine Key\" icon in the website Home Pane.\n\nVerify \"HMACSHA256\" or stronger encryption is selected for the Validation method and \"Auto\" is selected for the Encryption method.\n\nIf \"HMACSHA256\" or stronger encryption is not selected for the Validation method and/or \"Auto\" is not selected for the Encryption method, this is a finding.\n\nIf .NET is not installed, this is Not Applicable.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218807","title":"SRG-APP-000231-WSR-000144"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000137","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218807r1067586_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218807","discussion":"The Machine Key element of the ASP.NET web.config specifies the algorithm and keys that ASP.NET will use for encryption. The Machine Key feature can be managed to specify hashing and encryption settings for application services such as view state, forms authentication, membership and roles, and anonymous identification. Ensuring a strong encryption method can mitigate the risk of data tampering in crucial functional areas such as forms authentication cookies, or view state.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218807","rule_id":"SV-218807r1067586","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","status":"not_applicable","ccis":["CCI-001199"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.0.server:def:218807"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The production IIS 10.0 web server must utilize SHA2 encryption for the Machine Key.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000231-WSR-000144","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\n\nDouble-click the \"Machine Key\" icon in the web server Home Pane.\n\nSet the Validation method to \"HMACSHA256\" or stronger.\n\nSet the Encryption method to \"Auto\".\n\nClick \"Apply\" in the \"Actions\" pane."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109255","V-100151"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDAD71F-6C09-1014-9D8E-FBB31E88DA2C","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\n\nDouble-click the \"Directory Browsing\" icon.\n\nUnder the âActionsâ pane verify \"Directory Browsing\" is disabled.\n\nIf âDirectory Browsingâ is not disabled, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218808","title":"SRG-APP-000251-WSR-000157"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000138","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218808r961158_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218808","discussion":"Directory browsing allows the contents of a directory to be displayed upon request from a web client. If directory browsing is enabled for a directory in IIS, users could receive a web page listing the contents of the directory. If directory browsing is enabled, the risk of inadvertently disclosing sensitive content is increased.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218808","rule_id":"SV-218808r961158","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Verify Directory Browsing is not enabled)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001310"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.0.server:def:218808"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Directory Browsing on the IIS 10.0 web server must be disabled.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000251-WSR-000157","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\n\nDouble-click the \"Directory Browsing\" icon.\n\nUnder the \"Actions\" pane click \"Disabled\".\n\nUnder the \"Actions\" pane, click \"Apply\"."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109257","V-100153"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDADB09-6C09-1014-87CA-98248E16E449","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Access the IIS 10.0 Web Server.\n\nAccess an administrator command prompt and type \"regedit &lt;enter&gt;\" to access the server's registry.\n\nNavigate to HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\ContentIndex\\Catalogs\\.\n\nIf this key exists, then indexing is enabled. \n\nIf the key does not exist, this check is Not Applicable.\n\nReview the Catalog keys to determine if directories other than web document directories are being indexed.\n\nIf so, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218809","title":"SRG-APP-000266-WSR-000142"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000139","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218809r961167_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218809","discussion":"The indexing service can be used to facilitate a search function for websites. Enabling indexing may facilitate a directory traversal exploit and reveal unwanted information to a malicious user. Indexing must be limited to web document directories only.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218809","rule_id":"SV-218809r961167","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","status":"not_applicable","ccis":["CCI-001312"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.0.server:questionnaire:4301"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 web server Indexing must only index web content.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000266-WSR-000142","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Run MMC.\n\nAdd the Indexing Service snap-in.\n\nEdit the indexed directories to only include web document directories."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109259","V-100155"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDADF09-6C09-1014-82EF-F8512FE57A3F","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If the server is hosting WSUS, this is Not Applicable.\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\nDouble-click the \"Error Pages\" icon.\nClick any error message, and then click \"Edit Feature Setting\" from the \"Actions\" Pane. This will apply to all error messages.\n\nIf the feature setting is not set to \"Detailed errors for local requests and custom error pages for remote requests\", or \"Custom error pages\"  this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218810","title":"SRG-APP-000266-WSR-000159"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000140","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218810r1022657_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218810","discussion":"HTTP error pages contain information that could enable an attacker to gain access to an information system. Failure to prevent the sending of HTTP error pages with full information to remote requesters exposes internal configuration information to potential attackers.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218810","rule_id":"SV-218810r1022657","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   true (Webserver Error Pages - Detailed errors for local requests and custom error pages for remote requests must be selected)\nTest            :   false (Webserver Error Pages - Detailed errors for local requests and custom error pages for remote requests must be selected)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001312"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.0.server:def:218810"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Warning and error messages displayed to clients must be modified to minimize the identity of the IIS 10.0 web server, patches, loaded modules, and directory paths.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000266-WSR-000159","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\n\nDouble-click the \"Error Pages\" icon.\n\nClick any error message, and then click \"Edit Feature Setting\" from the \"Actions\" Pane. This will apply to all error messages.\n\nSet Feature Setting to \"Detailed errors for local requests and custom error pages for remote requests\" or \"Custom error pages\"."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109263","V-100159"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDAE40E-6C09-1014-9BA2-A0B087563274","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: This requirement applies to the Web Management Service. If the Web Management Service is not installed, this is Not Applicable.\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\n\nUnder \"Management\", double-click \"Management Service\".\n\nIf \"Enable remote connections\" is not selected, this is Not Applicable.\n\nIf \"Enable remote connections\" is selected, review the entries under \"IP Address Restrictions\".\n\nVerify only known, secure IP ranges are configured as \"Allow\".\n\nIf \"IP Address Restrictions\" are not configured or IP ranges configured to \"Allow\" are not restrictive enough to prevent connections from nonsecure zones, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218812","title":"SRG-APP-000315-WSR-000004"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000142","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218812r961278_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218812","discussion":"Remote access to the web server is any access that communicates through an external, non-organization-controlled network. Remote access can be used to access hosted applications or to perform management functions.\n\nA web server can be accessed remotely and must be capable of restricting access from what the DoD defines as non-secure zones. Non-secure zones are defined as any IP, subnet, or region defined as a threat to the organization. The non-secure zones must be defined for public web servers logically located in a DMZ, as well as private web servers with perimeter protection devices. By restricting access from non-secure zones through internal web server access lists, the web server can stop or slow denial of service (DoS) attacks on the web server.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218812","rule_id":"SV-218812r961278","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","status":"not_applicable","ccis":["CCI-002314"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.0.server:questionnaire:4701"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 web server must restrict inbound connections from non-secure zones.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000315-WSR-000004","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\n\nUnder \"Management\", double-click \"Management Service\".\n\nStop the Web Management Service under the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nConfigure only known, secure IP ranges as \"Allow\".\n\nSelect \"Apply\" in \"Actions\" pane.\n\nRestart the Web Management Service under the \"Actions\" pane."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109265","V-100161"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDAE940-6C09-1014-8C14-C6C433EFFCD7","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Interview the System Administrator and Web Manager.\n\nAsk for documentation for the IIS 10.0 web server administration.\n\nVerify there are documented procedures for shutting down an IIS 10.0 website in the event of an attack. The procedure should, at a minimum, provide the following steps:\n\nDetermine the respective website for the application at risk of an attack.\n\nAccess the IIS 10.0 web server IIS Manager.\n\nSelect the respective website.\n\nIn the \"Actions\" pane, under \"Manage Website\", click \"Stop\".\n\nIf necessary, stop all websites.\n\nIf necessary, stop the IIS 10.0 web server by selecting the web server in the IIS Manager.\n\nIn the \"Actions\" pane, under \"Manage Server\", click \"Stop\".\n\nIf the web server is not capable or cannot be configured to disconnect or disable remote access to the hosted applications when necessary, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218813","title":"SRG-APP-000316-WSR-000170"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000143","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218813r961281_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218813","discussion":"During an attack on the web server or any of the hosted applications, the system administrator may need to disconnect or disable access by users to stop the attack.\n\nThe web server must provide a capability to disconnect users to a hosted application without compromising other hosted applications unless deemed necessary to stop the attack. Methods to disconnect or disable connections are to stop the application service for a specified hosted application, stop the web server, or block all connections through web server access list.\n\nThe web server capabilities used to disconnect or disable users from connecting to hosted applications and the web server must be documented to make certain that, during an attack, the proper action is taken to conserve connectivity to any other hosted application if possible and to make certain log data is conserved for later forensic analysis.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218813","rule_id":"SV-218813r961281","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-218813, SV-218813r961281, SRG-APP-000316-WSR-000170)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-002322"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.0.server:questionnaire:4901"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 web server must provide the capability to immediately disconnect or disable remote access to the hosted applications.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000316-WSR-000170","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Prepare documented procedures for shutting down an IIS 10.0 website in the event of an attack.\n\nThe procedure should, at a minimum, provide the following steps:\n\nDetermine the respective website for the application at risk of an attack.\n\nAccess the IIS 10.0 web server IIS Manager.\n\nSelect the respective website. \n\nIn the \"Actions\" pane, under \"Manage Website\", click \"Stop\".\n\nIf necessary, stop all websites.\n\nIf necessary, stop the IIS 10.0 web server by selecting the web server in the IIS Manager.\n\nIn the \"Actions\" pane, under \"Manage Server\", click \"Stop\"."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109267","V-100163"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDAF041-6C09-1014-804C-A7AE7BB6F267","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Open Explorer and navigate to the inetpub directory.\n\nRight-click \"inetpub\" and select \"Properties\".\n\nClick the \"Security\" tab.\n\nVerify the permissions for the following users; if the permissions are less restrictive, this is a finding.\n\nSystem: Full control\nAdministrators: Full control\nTrustedInstaller: Full control\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES (built-in security group): Read and execute, This folder, subfolders and files\nALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES (built-in security group): Read and execute, This folder, subfolders and files\nUsers: Read and execute, list folder contents\nCREATOR OWNER: Full Control, Subfolders and files only","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218814","title":"SRG-APP-000340-WSR-000029"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000144","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218814r1067589_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218814","discussion":"This check verifies the key web server system configuration files are owned by the SA or the web administrator controlled account. These same files that control the configuration of the web server, and thus its behavior, must also be accessible by the account running the web service. If these files are altered by a malicious user, the web server would no longer be under the control of its managers and owners; properties in the web server configuration could be altered to compromise the entire server platform.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218814","rule_id":"SV-218814r1067589","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (The inetpub directory must conform to minimum file permission requirements.)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-002235"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.0.server:def:218814"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"IIS 10.0 web server system files must conform to minimum file permission requirements.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000340-WSR-000029","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Open Explorer and navigate to the inetpub directory.\n\nRight-click \"inetpub\" and select \"Properties\".\n\nClick the \"Security\" tab.\n\nSet the following permissions: \nSystem: Full control\nAdministrators: Full control\nTrustedInstaller: Full control\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES (built-in security group): Read and execute, This folder, subfolders and files\nALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES (built-in security group): Read and execute, This folder, subfolders and files\nUsers: Read and execute, list folder contents\nCREATOR OWNER: Full Control, Subfolders and files only"},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109269","V-100165"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDAF47B-6C09-1014-B36D-B8A3489C6A26","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\n\nUnder \"IIS\" double-click the \"Logging\" icon.\n\nIn the \"Logging\" configuration box, determine the \"Directory:\" to which the \"W3C\" logging is being written.\n\nConfirm with the System Administrator that the designated log path is of sufficient size to maintain the logging.\n\nUnder \"Log File Rollover\", verify \"Do not create new log files\" is not selected.\n\nVerify a schedule is configured to rollover log files on a regular basis.\n\nConsult with the System Administrator to determine if there is a documented process for moving the log files off of the IIS 10.0 web server to another logging device.\n\nIf the designated logging path device is not of sufficient space to maintain all log files, and there is not a schedule to rollover files on a regular basis, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218815","title":"SRG-APP-000357-WSR-000150"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000145","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218815r961392_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218815","discussion":"To ensure the logging mechanism used by the web server has sufficient storage capacity in which to write the logs, the logging mechanism must be able to allocate log record storage capacity.\n\nThe task of allocating log record storage capacity is usually performed during initial installation of the logging mechanism. The system administrator will usually coordinate the allocation of physical drive space with the web server administrator along with the physical location of the partition and disk. Refer to NIST SP 800-92 for specific requirements on log rotation and storage dependent on the impact of the web server.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218815","rule_id":"SV-218815r961392","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (The IIS 10.0 web server must use a logging mechanism that is configured to allocate log record storage capacity large enough to accommodate the logging requirements of the IIS 10.0 web server.e)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001849"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.0.server:def:218815"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 web server must use a logging mechanism configured to allocate log record storage capacity large enough to accommodate the logging requirements of the IIS 10.0 web server.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000357-WSR-000150","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\n\nUnder \"IIS\" double-click on the \"Logging\" icon.\n\nIf necessary, in the \"Logging\" configuration box, re-designate a log path to a location able to house the logs.\n\nUnder \"Log File Rollover\", de-select the \"Do not create new log files\" setting.\n\nConfigure a schedule to rollover log files on a regular basis."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109271","V-100167"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDAF863-6C09-1014-8962-844D23B049F8","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Right-click \"InetMgr.exe\", then click \"Properties\" from the \"Context\" menu.\n\nSelect the \"Security\" tab.\n\nReview the groups and user names.\n\nThe following accounts may have Full control privileges:\n\nTrustedInstaller\nWeb Managers\nWeb Manager designees\nCREATOR OWNER\n\nThe following accounts may have read and execute, or read permissions:\n\nNon Web Manager Administrators\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES (built-in security group)\nALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES (built-in security group)\nSYSTEM\nUsers\n\nSpecific users may be granted read and execute and read permissions.\n\nCompare the local documentation authorizing specific users, against the users observed when reviewing the groups and users.\n\nIf any other access is observed, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218816","title":"SRG-APP-000380-WSR-000072"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000147","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218816r1067591_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218816","discussion":"A web server can be modified through parameter modification, patch installation, upgrades to the web server or modules, and security parameter changes. With each of these changes, there is the potential for an adverse effect such as a DoS, web server instability, or hosted application instability.\n\nTo limit changes to the web server and limit exposure to any adverse effects from the changes, files such as the web server application files, libraries, and configuration files must have permissions and ownership set properly to only allow privileged users access.\n\nThe key web service administrative and configuration tools must only be accessible by the web server staff. All users granted this authority will be documented and approved by the ISSO. Access to the IIS Manager will be limited to authorized users and administrators.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000380-WSR-000072, SRG-APP-000435-WSR-000147, SRG-APP-000033-WSR-000169","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218816","rule_id":"SV-218816r1067591","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-218816, SV-218816r1067591, SRG-APP-000380-WSR-000072)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-000213","CCI-001813","CCI-002385"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.0.server:questionnaire:5501"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Access to web administration tools must be restricted to the web manager and the web managers designees.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000380-WSR-000072","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Restrict access to the web administration tool to only the web manager and the web managerâs designees."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109273","V-100169"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDAFC0F-6C09-1014-9D6A-C7705E636785","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Review programs installed on the OS.\n\nOpen Control Panel.\n\nOpen Programs and Features.\n\nThe following programs may be installed without any additional documentation:\n\nAdministration Pack for IIS\nIIS Search Engine Optimization Toolkit\nMicrosoft .NET Framework version 3.5 SP1 or greater\nMicrosoft Web Platform Installer version 3.x or greater\nVirtual Machine Additions\n\nReview the installed programs, if any programs are installed other than those listed above, this is a finding.\n\nNote: If additional software is needed and has supporting documentation signed by the ISSO, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218817","title":"SRG-APP-000383-WSR-000175"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000148","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218817r961470_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218817","discussion":"Web servers provide numerous processes, features, and functionalities that utilize TCP/IP ports. Some of these processes may be deemed unnecessary or too unsecure to run on a production system.\n\nThe web server must provide the capability to disable or deactivate network-related services deemed non-essential to the server mission, are too unsecure, or are prohibited by the PPSM CAL and vulnerability assessments.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218817","rule_id":"SV-218817r961470","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-218817, SV-218817r961470, SRG-APP-000383-WSR-000175)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-001762"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.0.server:questionnaire:5701"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 web server must not be running on a system providing any other role.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000383-WSR-000175","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Remove all unapproved programs and roles from the production web server."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109275","V-100171"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDAFFAD-6C09-1014-B3CA-D504230D80EA","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"If the Print Services role and the Internet Printing role are not installed, this check is Not Applicable.\n\nNavigate to the following directory:\n\n%windir%\\web\\printers\n\nIf this folder exists, this is a finding.\n\nDetermine whether Internet Printing is enabled:\n\nClick âStartâ, click âAdministrative Toolsâ, and then click âServer Managerâ.\n\nExpand the roles node, right-click âPrint Servicesâ, and then select âRemove Roles Servicesâ.\n\nIf the Internet Printing option is enabled, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218818","title":"SRG-APP-000383-WSR-000175"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000149","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218818r961470_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218818","discussion":"The use of IPP on an IIS web server allows client access to shared printers. This privileged access could allow remote code execution by increasing the web servers attack surface. Additionally, since IPP does not support SSL, it is considered a risk and will not be deployed.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218818","rule_id":"SV-218818r961470","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","status":"not_applicable","ccis":["CCI-001762"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.0.server:def:218818"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The Internet Printing Protocol (IPP) must be disabled on the IIS 10.0 web server.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000383-WSR-000175","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Click âStartâ, click âAdministrative Toolsâ, and then click âServer Managerâ.\n\nExpand the roles node, right-click âPrint Servicesâ, and then select âRemove Roles Servicesâ.\n\nIf the Internet Printing option is checked, clear the check box, click âNextâ, and then click âRemoveâ to complete the wizard."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109277","V-100173"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDB034D-6C09-1014-BCAC-B4CD19DA4535","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"If the IIS 10.0 web server is not hosting any applications, this is Not Applicable.\n\nIf the IIS 10.0 web server is hosting applications, consult with the system administrator to determine risk analysis performed when the application was written and deployed to the IIS 10.0 web server.\n\nObtain documentation on the configuration.\nVerify, at a minimum, the following tuning settings in the registry.\nAccess the IIS 10.0 web server registry.\nVerify the following keys are present and configured. The required setting depends upon the requirements of the application. \nRecommended settings are not provided as these settings must be explicitly configured to show a conscientious tuning has been made.\nNavigate to HKLM\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\HTTP\\Parameters\\\nREG_DWORD \"URIEnableCache\"\nREG_DWORD \"UriMaxUriBytes\"\nREG_DWORD \"UriScavengerPeriod\"\n\nIf explicit settings are not configured for \"URIEnableCache\", \"UriMaxUriBytes\" and \"UriScavengerPeriod\", this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218819","title":"SRG-APP-000435-WSR-000148"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000151","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218819r1022659_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218819","discussion":"A Denial of Service (DoS) can occur when the web server is overwhelmed and can no longer respond to additional requests. A web server not properly tuned may become overwhelmed and cause a DoS condition even with expected traffic from users. To avoid a DoS, the web server must be tuned to handle the expected traffic for the hosted applications.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218819","rule_id":"SV-218819r1022659","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false ((1 of 3) The IIS 10.0 web server must be tuned to handle the operational requirements of the hosted application. Regkey: URIEnableCache)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\HTTP\\Parameters\\URIEnableCache'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false ((2 of 3) The IIS 10.0 web server must be tuned to handle the operational requirements of the hosted application. Regkey: UriMaxUriBytes)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\HTTP\\Parameters\\UriMaxUriBytes'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false ((3 of 3) The IIS 10.0 web server must be tuned to handle the operational requirements of the hosted application. Regkey: UriScavengerPeriod)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\HTTP\\Parameters\\UriScavengerPeriod'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-002385"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.0.server:def:218819"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 web server must be tuned to handle the operational requirements of the hosted application.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000435-WSR-000148","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Access the IIS 10.0 web server registry.\n\nVerify the following keys are present and configured. The required setting depends upon the requirements of the application. These settings must be explicitly configured to show a conscientious tuning has been made.\n\nNavigate to HKLM\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\HTTP\\Parameters\\\n\nConfigure the following registry keys to levels to accommodate the hosted applications.\n\nCreate REG_DWORD \"URIEnableCache\"\nCreate REG_DWORD \"UriMaxUriBytes\"\nCreate REG_DWORD \"UriScavengerPeriod\""},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109279","V-100175"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDB06B3-6C09-1014-B3B1-9B545F08965A","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\n\nUnder the \"Management\" section, double-click the \"Configuration Editor\" icon.\n\nFrom the \"Section:\" drop-down list, select \"system.webServer/asp\".\n\nExpand the \"session\" section.\n\nVerify the \"keepSessionIdSecure\" is set to \"True\".\n\nIf the \"keepSessionIdSecure\" is not set to \"True\", this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218820","title":"SRG-APP-000439-WSR-000152"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000152","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218820r961632_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218820","discussion":"The HTTP protocol is a stateless protocol. To maintain a session, a session identifier is used. The session identifier is a piece of data used to identify a session and a user. If the session identifier is compromised by an attacker, the session can be hijacked. By encrypting the session identifier, the identifier becomes more difficult for an attacker to hijack, decrypt, and use before the session has expired.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218820","rule_id":"SV-218820r961632","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (The IIS 10.0 web server must have keepSessionIdSecure set to True)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-002418"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.0.server:def:218820"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"IIS 10.0 web server session IDs must be sent to the client using TLS.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000439-WSR-000152","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\n\nUnder \"Management\" section, double-click the \"Configuration Editor\" icon.\n\nFrom the \"Section:\" drop-down list, select \"system.webServer/asp\".\n\nExpand the \"session\" section.\n\nSelect \"True\" for the \"keepSessionIdSecure\" setting.\n\nSelect \"Apply\" from the \"Actions\" pane."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109281","V-100177"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDB0A5B-6C09-1014-B892-C1FE31379211","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Access the IIS 10.0 Web Server.\n\nNavigate to:\nHKLM\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\TLS 1.2\\Server\n\nVerify a REG_DWORD value of \"0\" for \"DisabledByDefault\".\nVerify a REG_DWORD value of \"1\" for \"Enabled\".\n\nNavigate to:\nHKLM\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\TLS 1.0\\Server\nHKLM\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\TLS 1.1\\Server\nHKLM\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\SSL 3.0\\Server\n\nVerify a REG_DWORD value of \"1\" for \"DisabledByDefault\".\nVerify a REG_DWORD value of \"0\" for \"Enabled\".\n\nIf any of the respective registry paths do not exist or are configured with the wrong value, this is a finding.\n\nSSL 3.0 is disabled by default in newer Operating Systems. If SSL 3.0 has a registry DWORD enabled with a value of 1, this is a finding. If this key is not present, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218821","title":"SRG-APP-000439-WSR-000156"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000153","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218821r1067596_rule","severity":"high","group_id_src":"V-218821","discussion":"TLS encryption is a required security setting for a private web server. Encryption of private information is essential to ensuring data confidentiality. If private information is not encrypted, it can be intercepted and easily read by an unauthorized party. A private web server must use a FIPS 140-2-approved TLS version, and all non-FIPS-approved SSL versions must be disabled.\n\nNIST SP 800-52 specifies the preferred configurations for government systems.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218821","rule_id":"SV-218821r1067596","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false ((TLS 1.2 DisabledByDefault set to 0) Access the IIS 10.0 Web Server. HKLM\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\TLS 1.2\\Server. Verify a REG_DWORD value of 0 for DisabledByDefault.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\TLS 1.2\\Server\\DisabledByDefault'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false ((TLS 1.2 Enabled set to 1) Access the IIS 10.0 Web Server. HKLM\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\TLS 1.2\\Server. Verify a REG_DWORD value of 1 for Enabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\TLS 1.2\\Server\\Enabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false ((TLS 1.1 Disabled) Access the IIS 10.0 Web Server. HKLM\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\TLS 1.1\\Server. Verify a REG_DWORD value of 0 for Enabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\TLS 1.1\\Server\\Enabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false ((TLS 1.1 DisabledByDefault) Access the IIS 10.0 Web Server. HKLM\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\TLS 1.1\\Server. Verify a REG_DWORD value of 1 for DisabledByDefault.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\TLS 1.1\\Server\\DisabledByDefault'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false ((TLS 1.0 Disabled) Access the IIS 10.0 Web Server. HKLM\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\TLS 1.0\\Server. Verify a REG_DWORD value of 0 for Enabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\TLS 1.0\\Server\\Enabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false ((TLS 1.0 DisabledByDefault) Access the IIS 10.0 Web Server. HKLM\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\TLS 1.0\\Server. Verify a REG_DWORD value of 1 for DisabledByDefault.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\TLS 1.0\\Server\\DisabledByDefault'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false ((SSL 3.0 Disabled) Access the IIS 10.0 Web Server. HKLM\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\SSL 3.0\\Server. Verify a REG_DWORD value of 0 for Enabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\SSL 3.0\\Server\\Enabled'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\nTest            :   false ((SSL 3.0 DisabledByDefault) Access the IIS 10.0 Web Server. HKLM\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\SSL 3.0\\Server. Verify a REG_DWORD value of 1 for DisabledByDefault.)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\SSL 3.0\\Server\\DisabledByDefault'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-002418"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.0.server:def:218821"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"An IIS 10.0 web server must maintain the confidentiality of controlled information during transmission through the use of an approved Transport Layer Security (TLS) version.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000439-WSR-000156","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Access the IIS 10.0 Web Server.\n\nNavigate to:\nHKLM\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\TLS 1.2\\Server \n\nCreate a REG_DWORD named \"DisabledByDefault\" with a value of \"0\".\nCreate a REG_DWORD named \"Enabled\" with a  value of \"1\".\n\nNavigate to:\nHKLM\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\TLS 1.0\\Server\nHKLM\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\TLS 1.1\\Server\nHKLM\\SYSTEM\\CurrentControlSet\\Control\\SecurityProviders\\SCHANNEL\\Protocols\\SSL 3.0\\Server\n\nFor each protocol:\nCreate a REG_DWORD named \"DisabledByDefault\" with a value of \"1\".\nCreate a REG_DWORD named \"Enabled\" with a  value of \"0\"."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109283","V-100179"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDB0DF9-6C09-1014-8F52-FADCB7608365","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Review the web server documentation and deployed configuration to determine which version of TLS is being used.\n\nIf the TLS version is not TLS 1.2 or higher, according to NIST SP 800-52, or if non-FIPS-approved algorithms are enabled, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218822","title":"SRG-APP-000439-WSR-000156"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000154","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218822r961632_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218822","discussion":"TLS is a required transmission protocol for a web server hosting controlled information. The use of TLS provides confidentiality of data in transit between the web server and client. FIPS 140-2-approved TLS versions must be enabled and non-FIPS-approved SSL versions must be disabled.\n\nNIST SP 800-52 defines the approved TLS versions for government applications.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218822","rule_id":"SV-218822r961632","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-218822, SV-218822r961632, SRG-APP-000439-WSR-000156)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-002418"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.0.server:questionnaire:6701"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 web server must maintain the confidentiality of controlled information during transmission through the use of an approved Transport Layer Security (TLS) version.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000439-WSR-000156","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Configure the web server to use an approved TLS version according to NIST SP 800-52 and to disable all non-approved versions."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109285","V-100181"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDB1183-6C09-1014-B159-8BEAE12F2F96","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Access the IIS 10.0 web server.\n\nAccess the \"Apps\" menu. Under \"Administrative Tools\", select \"Computer Management\".\n\nIn left pane, expand \"Local Users and Groups\" and click \"Users\".\n\nReview the local users listed in the middle pane. \n\nIf any local accounts are present and used by IIS 10.0, verify with System Administrator that default passwords have been changed.\n\nIf passwords have not been changed from the default, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218823","title":"SRG-APP-000516-WSR-000079"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000156","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218823r961863_rule","severity":"high","group_id_src":"V-218823","discussion":"During installation of the web server software, accounts are created for the web server to operate properly. The accounts installed can have either no password installed or a default password, which will be known and documented by the vendor and the user community.\n\nThe first things an attacker will try when presented with a logon screen are the default user identifiers with default passwords. Installed applications may also install accounts with no password, making the logon even easier. Once the web server is installed, the passwords for any created accounts should be changed and documented. The new passwords must meet the requirements for all passwords, i.e., upper/lower characters, numbers, special characters, time until change, reuse policy, etc.\n\nService accounts or system accounts that have no logon capability do not need to have passwords set or changed.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218823","rule_id":"SV-218823r961863","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT I, V-218823, SV-218823r961863, SRG-APP-000516-WSR-000079)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.0.server:questionnaire:6901"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"All accounts installed with the IIS 10.0 web server software and tools must have passwords assigned and default passwords changed.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516-WSR-000079","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Access the IIS 10.0 web server.\n\nAccess the \"Apps\" menu. Under Administrative Tools, select Computer Management.\n\nIn left pane, expand \"Local Users and Groups\" and click on \"Users\".\n\nChange passwords for any local accounts present that are used by IIS 10.0, then verify with System Administrator default passwords have been changed.\n\nDevelop an internal process for changing passwords on a regular basis."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109287","V-100183"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDB14DE-6C09-1014-951E-DCF4B78A9DF5","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\n\nDouble-click the \"ISAPI and CGI restrictions\" icon.\n\nClick âEdit Feature Settings\".\n\nVerify the \"Allow unspecified CGI modules\" and the \"Allow unspecified ISAPI modules\" check boxes are NOT checked.\n\nIf either or both of the \"Allow unspecified CGI modules\" and the \"Allow unspecified ISAPI modules\" check boxes are checked, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218824","title":"SRG-APP-000516-WSR-000174"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000158","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218824r961863_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218824","discussion":"By allowing unspecified file extensions to execute, the web servers attack surface is significantly increased. This increased risk can be reduced by only allowing specific ISAPI extensions or CGI extensions to run on the web server.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218824","rule_id":"SV-218824r961863","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Unspecified file extensions must not be allowed to execute on the production web server. (1 of 2))\nTest            :   true (Unspecified file extensions must not be allowed to execute on the production web server. (2 of 2))\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.0.server:def:218824"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Unspecified file extensions on a production IIS 10.0 web server must be removed.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516-WSR-000174","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\n\nDouble-click the \"ISAPI and CGI restrictions\" icon.\n\nClick \"Edit Feature Settings\".\n\nRemove the check from the \"Allow unspecified CGI modules\" and the \"Allow unspecified ISAPI modules\" check boxes.\n\nClick \"OK\"."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109289","V-100185"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDB1861-6C09-1014-9631-DAA0884AA642","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If ASP.NET is not installed, this is Not Applicable.\nNote: If the Server is hosting Microsoft SharePoint, this is Not Applicable.\nNote: If the server is hosting WSUS, this is Not Applicable.\nNote: If the server is hosting Exchange, this is Not Applicable.\nNote: If the server is public facing, this is Not Applicable.\nNote: If the website is behind a load balancer or proxy server, this is Not Applicable.\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\nDouble-click the \".NET Authorization Rules\" icon.\nEnsure \"All Users\" is set to \"Allow\", and \"Anonymous Users\" is set to \"Deny\", otherwise this is a finding.\nIf any other rules are present, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218825","title":"SRG-APP-000516-WSR-000174"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000159","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218825r1067593_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218825","discussion":"Authorization rules can be configured at the server, website, folder (including Virtual Directories), or file level. It is recommended that URL Authorization be configured to only grant access to the necessary security principals. Configuring a global Authorization rule that restricts access ensures inheritance of the settings down through the hierarchy of web directories. This will ensure access to current and future content is only granted to the appropriate principals, mitigating risk of unauthorized access. ","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218825","rule_id":"SV-218825r1067593","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","status":"not_applicable","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.0.server:def:218825"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 web server must have a global authorization rule configured to restrict access.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516-WSR-000174","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\n\nDouble-click the \".NET Authorization Rules\" icon.\n\nAlter the list as necessary to ensure \"All Users\" is set to \"Allow\" and \"Anonymous Users\" is set to \"Deny\".\n\nRemove any other line items."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109291","V-100187"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDB1BEE-6C09-1014-B000-817B78E1710A","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Access the IIS 10.0 IIS Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 server.\n\nSelect \"Configuration Editor\" under the \"Management\" section.\n\nFrom the \"Section:\" drop-down list at the top of the configuration editor, locate \"system.applicationHost/sites\".\n\nExpand \"siteDefaults\".\nExpand \"limits\".\n\nReview the results and verify the value is greater than zero for the \"maxconnections\" parameter.\n\nIf the maxconnections parameter is set to zero, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218826","title":"SRG-APP-000001-WSR-000001"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000200","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218826r960735_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218826","discussion":"Resource exhaustion can occur when an unlimited number of concurrent requests are allowed on a website, facilitating a Denial of Service (DoS) attack. Mitigating this kind of attack will include limiting the number of concurrent HTTP/HTTPS requests per IP address and may include, where feasible, limiting parameter values associated with keepalive (i.e., a parameter used to limit the amount of time a connection may be inactive).","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218826","rule_id":"SV-218826r960735","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Access the IIS 10.0 IIS Manager. Click the IIS 10.0 server. Select 'Configuration Editor' under the 'Management' section. From the 'Section:' drop-down list at the top of the configuration editor, locate 'system.applicationHost/sites'. Expand 'siteDefaults'. Expand 'limits'. Review the results and verify the value is greater than zero for the 'maxconnections' parameter. If the maxconnections parameter is set to zero, this is a finding.)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000054"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.0.server:def:218826"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 websites MaxConnections setting must be configured to limit the number of allowed simultaneous session requests.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000001-WSR-000001","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Access the IIS 10.0 IIS Manager.\n\nClick the IIS 10.0 server.\n\nSelect \"Configuration Editor\" under the \"Management\" section.\n\nFrom the \"Section:\" drop-down list at the top of the configuration editor, locate \"system.applicationHost/sites\".\n\nExpand \"siteDefaults\".\nExpand \"limits\".\n\nSet the \"maxconnections\" parameter to a value greater than zero."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109293","V-100189"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDB207E-6C09-1014-A4ED-F402559B2A33","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If the server is hosting WSUS, this is not applicable.\nNote: If the server is providing OCSP, and not otherwise hosting any content, this requirement is not applicable.\n\nAccess the IIS 10.0 Web Server.\nOpen IIS Manager.\nClick the IIS 10.0 web server name.\nOpen on Configuration Editor under Management.\nFor the Section, navigate to system.applicationHost/sites.\nExpand siteDefaults and HSTS.\nIf enabled is not set to True, this is a finding.\nIf includeSubDomains is not set to True, this is a finding.\nIf max-age is not set to a value greater than 0, this is a finding.\nIf redirectHttpToHttps is not True, this is a finding.\n\nIf the website is behind a load balancer or proxy server, and HSTS enablement is handled there, this is not applicable.\n\nIf the version of Windows Server does not natively support HSTS, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218827","title":"SRG-APP-000516-WSR-000174"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000205","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218827r1112380_rule","severity":"low","group_id_src":"V-218827","discussion":"HTTP Strict Transport Security (HSTS) ensures browsers always connect to a website over TLS. HSTS exists to remove the need for redirection configurations. HSTS relies on the browser, web server, and a public \"Allowlist\". If the browser does not support HSTS, it will be ignored.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218827","rule_id":"SV-218827r1112380","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Check that system.applicationHost/sites:siteDefaults.hsts.enabled, verify that value equals true.)\nResult Analysis :        Webserver//system.applicationHost/sites/siteDefaults.hsts.enabled = 'false' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'true' \nTest            :   false (Check that system.applicationHost/sites:siteDefaults.hsts.includeSubDomains, verify that value is set to True.)\nResult Analysis :        Webserver//system.applicationHost/sites/siteDefaults.hsts.includeSubDomains = 'false' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'true' \nTest            :   false (Check that system.applicationHost/sites:siteDefaults.hsts.max-age, verify that value is set to 1.)\nResult Analysis :        Webserver//system.applicationHost/sites/siteDefaults.hsts.max-age = '0' failed test of 'greater than' compared to '0' \nTest            :   false (Check that system.applicationHost/sites:siteDefaults.hsts.redirectHttpToHttps, verify that value is set to True. )\nResult Analysis :        Webserver//system.applicationHost/sites/siteDefaults.hsts.redirectHttpToHttps = 'false' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'true' \n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.0.server:def:218827"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 web server must enable HTTP Strict Transport Security (HSTS).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516-WSR-000174","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Using the Configuration Editor in the IIS Manager or Powershell:\nEnable HSTS.\nSet includeSubDomains to True.\nSet max-age to a value greater than 0.\nSet redirectHttpToHttps to True."},{"legacy_ids":["V-102895","SV-111857"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDB24BB-6C09-1014-B2C9-9B4C95D5987B","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Interview the System Administrator about the role of the IIS 10.0 web server.\n\nIf the IIS 10.0 web server is running SMTP relay services, have the SA provide supporting documentation on how the server is hardened. A DoD-issued certificate, and specific allowed IP address should be configured.\n\nIf the IIS web server is not running SMTP relay services, this is Not Applicable.\n\nIf the IIS web server running SMTP relay services without TLS enabled, this is a finding.\n\nIf the IIS web server running SMTP relay services is not configured to only allow a specific IP address, from the same network as the relay, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-228572","title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000075"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000160","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-228572r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-228572","discussion":"Anonymous SMTP relays are strictly prohibited. An anonymous SMTP relay can be a vector for many types of malicious activity not limited to server exploitation for the sending of SPAM mail, access to emails, phishing, DoS attacks, etc. Enabling TLS, authentication, and strictly assigning IP addresses that can communicate with the relay greatly reduce the risk of the implementation.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-228572","rule_id":"SV-228572r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-228572, SV-228572r960963, SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000075)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.0.server:questionnaire:7901"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"An IIS Server configured to be a SMTP relay must require authentication.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000075","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Configure the relay server with a specific allowed IP address, from the same network as the relay, and implement TLS."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-54431","V-41854"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDB28AD-6C09-1014-A838-F8CCC403C4BA","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If ASP.NET is not installed, this is Not Applicable.\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\nUnder the \"Connections\" pane on the left side of the management console, select the IIS 10.0 web server.\nClick the HTTP Response Headers button.\nClick to select the âX-Powered-Byâ HTTP Header.\nIf âX-Powered-Byâ has not been removed, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-241789","title":"SRG-APP-000266-WSR-000159"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000215","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-241789r1022662_rule","severity":"low","group_id_src":"V-241789","discussion":"HTTP Response Headers contain information that could enable an attacker to gain access to an information system. Failure to prevent the sending of certain HTTP Response Header information to remote requesters exposes internal configuration information to potential attackers.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-241789","rule_id":"SV-241789r1022662","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","status":"not_applicable","ccis":["CCI-001312"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.0.server:def:241789"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"ASP.NET version must be removed from the HTTP Response Header information.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000266-WSR-000159","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\nUnder the \"Connections\" pane on the left side of the management console, select the IIS 10.0 web server.\nClick the HTTP Response Headers button.\nClick to select the âX-Powered-Byâ HTTP Header.\nClick âRemoveâ in the Actions Panel.\nNote: This can be performed multiple ways, this is an example."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109223","V-100119"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"2CDB2D2E-6C09-1014-BC14-9DF182B83A82","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Open Registry Editor.\nNavigate to \"HKLM\\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\HTTP\\Parameters\"\nVerify \"DisableRequestSmugglingâ is set to \"1\".\n\nIf REG_DWORD DisableRequestSmuggling is not set to 1, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-268325","title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000015"},"rule_version":"IIST-SV-000220","reference_identifier":"4052","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-268325r1025163_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-268325","discussion":"Security scans show Request Smuggling vulnerability on IIS server.\n\nThe vulnerability allows a remote attacker to perform HTTP request smuggling attack.\n\nThe vulnerability exists due to the way that HTTP proxies (front-end) and web servers (back-end) that do not strictly adhere to RFC standards handle sequences of HTTP requests received from multiple sources. A remote attacker can send a specially crafted request to a targeted IIS Server, perform HTTP request smuggling attack and modify responses or retrieve information from another user's HTTP session.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-268325","rule_id":"SV-268325r1025163","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:02:51\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (HKLM\\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\HTTP\\Parameters key (REG_DWORD): DisableRequestSmuggling = 1)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\HTTP\\Parameters\\DisableRequestSmuggling'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Server_V3R6_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV16-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.0.server:def:268325"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The Request Smuggling filter must be enabled.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000015","stig_uuid":"2CD91C48-6C09-1014-BC39-FF2FCD02E4DA","fix_text":"Navigate to \"HKLM\\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\HTTP\\Parameters\".\nCreate REG_DWORD \"DisableRequestSmugglingâ and set it to \"1\".\n\nNote: This can be performed multiple ways; this is an example."}]},{"stig_name":"Microsoft IIS 10.0 Site Security Technical Implementation Guide","classification":"UNCLASSIFIED","release_info":"Release: 14 Benchmark Date: 05 Jan 2026","version":"2","display_name":"Microsoft IIS 10.0 Site","reference_identifier":"4051","stig_id":"IIS_10-0_Site_STIG","uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","size":43,"rules":[{"legacy_ids":["SV-109297","V-100193"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB58F14-6C09-1014-A4C3-AA7FF85D2F31","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If ASP.NET is not installed, this is Not Applicable.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\nClick the site name.\nUnder the \"ASP.NET\" section, select \"Session State\".\nUnder \"Cookie Settings\", verify the \"Use Cookies\" mode is selected from the \"Mode:\" drop-down list.\nIf the \"Use Cookies\" mode is selected, this is not a finding.\n\nAlternative method:\nClick the site name.\nSelect \"Configuration Editor\" under the \"Management\" section.\nFrom the \"Section:\" drop-down list at the top of the configuration editor, locate \"system.web/sessionState\".\nVerify the \"cookieless\" is set to \"UseCookies\".\nIf the \"cookieless\" is not set to \"UseCookies\", this is a finding.\nNote: If IIS 10.0 server/site is used only for system-to-system maintenance, does not allow users to connect to interface, and is restricted to specific system IPs, this is Not Applicable.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218736","title":"SRG-APP-000001-WSR-000002"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000202","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218736r1022669_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218736","discussion":"When the session information is stored on the client, the session ID, along with the user authorization and identity information, is sent along with each client request and is stored in either a cookie, embedded in the uniform resource locator (URL), or placed in a hidden field on the displayed form. Each of these offers advantages and disadvantages. The biggest disadvantage to all three is the hijacking of a session along with all of the user's credentials.\n\nWhen the user authorization and identity information is stored on the server in a protected and encrypted database, the communication between the client and website will only send the session identifier, and the server can then retrieve user credentials for the session when needed. If, during transmission, the session were to be hijacked, the user's credentials would not be compromised.\n\nASP.NET provides a session state, which is available as the HttpSessionState class, as a method of storing session-specific information visible only within the session. ASP.NET session state identifies requests from the same browser during a limited time window as a session and provides the ability to persist variable values for the duration of that session.\n\nWhen using the URI mode for cookie settings under session state, IIS will reject and reissue session IDs that do not have active sessions. Configuring IIS to expire session IDs and regenerate tokens gives a potential attacker less time to capture a cookie and gain access to server content.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218736","rule_id":"SV-218736r1022669","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","status":"not_applicable","ccis":["CCI-000054"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218736"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 website session state cookie settings must be configured to Use Cookies mode.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000001-WSR-000002","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server: \n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name.\n\nUnder the ASP.NET section, select \"Session State\".\n\nUnder \"Cookie Settings\", select the \"Use Cookies\" from the \"Mode:\" drop-down list.\n\nSelect \"Apply\" from the \"Actions\" pane."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109299","V-100195"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB594A2-6C09-1014-9247-B168C7AC2515","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If the server being reviewed is a public IIS 10.0 web server, this is Not Applicable.\nNote: If the server is hosting SharePoint, this is Not Applicable.\nNote: If the server is hosting WSUS, this is Not Applicable.\nNote: If SSL is installed on load balancer/proxy server through which traffic is routed to the IIS 10.0 server, and the IIS 10.0 server receives traffic from the load balancer/proxy server, the SSL requirement must be met on the load balancer/proxy server and is Not Applicable in this STIG.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\nClick the site name.\nDouble-click the \"SSL Settings\" icon.\nVerify \"Require SSL\" check box is selected.\n\nIf the \"Require SSL\" check box is not selected, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218737","title":"SRG-APP-000014-WSR-000006"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000203","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218737r1022671_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218737","discussion":"Transport Layer Security (TLS) encryption is a required security setting for a private web server. Encryption of private information is essential to ensuring data confidentiality. If private information is not encrypted, it can be intercepted and easily read by an unauthorized party. A private web server must use a FIPS 140-2-approved TLS version, and all non-FIPS-approved SSL versions must be disabled.\n\nNIST SP 800-52 specifies the preferred configurations for government systems.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218737","rule_id":"SV-218737r1022671","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   false (SSL is enabled - Click the site name. Double-click the 'SSL Settings' icon. Verify 'Require SSL is selected' If the 'Require SSL ' is not selected, this is a finding.)\nResult Analysis :        Site/Default Web Site/access/sslflags = 'None' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'Ssl' \n                : Site/soteriatest/access/sslflags = 'None' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'Ssl' \n                : Site/anothertestsite/access/sslflags = 'None' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'Ssl' \n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-000068"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218737"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"A private IIS 10.0 website must only accept Secure Socket Layer (SSL) connections.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000014-WSR-000006","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name.\n\nDouble-click the \"SSL Settings\" icon.\n\nSelect \"Require SSL\" check box.\n\nSelect \"Apply\" from the \"Actions\" pane."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109301","V-100197"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB59882-6C09-1014-B49C-A66D0F87B8AB","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If the server being reviewed is a private IIS 10.0 web server, this is Not Applicable.\nNote: If the server being reviewed is a public IIS 10.0 web server not requiring authentication, this is Not Applicable.\nNote: If the server being reviewed is hosting SharePoint, this is Not Applicable.\nNote: If the server being reviewed is hosting WSUS, this is Not Applicable.\nNote: If the server being reviewed is hosting Simple Certificate Enrollment Services (SCEP), this is Not Applicable.\nNote: If the server being reviewed is hosting Network Device Enrollment Services (NDES), this is Not Applicable.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name.\n\nDouble-click the \"SSL Settings\" icon.\n\nVerify \"Require SSL\" check box is selected.\n\nIf the \"Require SSL\" check box is not selected, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218738","title":"SRG-APP-000014-WSR-000006"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000204","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218738r1022673_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218738","discussion":"Transport Layer Security (TLS) encryption is a required security setting for a private web server. Encryption of private information is essential to ensuring data confidentiality. If private information is not encrypted, it can be intercepted and easily read by an unauthorized party. A private web server must use a FIPS 140-2-approved TLS version, and all non-FIPS-approved SSL versions must be disabled.\n\nNIST SP 800-52 specifies the preferred configurations for government systems.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218738","rule_id":"SV-218738r1022673","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (SSL is enabled - Click the site name. Double-click the 'SSL Settings' icon. Verify 'Require SSL is selected' If the 'Require SSL ' is not selected, this is a finding.)\nResult Analysis :        Site/Default Web Site/access/sslflags = 'None' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'Ssl' \n                : Site/soteriatest/access/sslflags = 'None' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'Ssl' \n                : Site/anothertestsite/access/sslflags = 'None' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'Ssl' \n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-000068"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218738"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"A public IIS 10.0 website must only accept Secure Socket Layer (SSL) connections when authentication is required.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000014-WSR-000006","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Note: If the server being reviewed is a private IIS 10.0 web server, this is Not Applicable.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name.\n\nDouble-click the \"SSL Settings\" icon.\n\nSelect \"Require SSL\" check box.\n\nSelect \"Apply\" from the \"Actions\" pane."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109303","V-100199"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB59C6E-6C09-1014-BEAC-C7810DD5DE6A","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If this server is hosting WSUS, this requirement is Not Applicable.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name.\n\nClick the \"Logging\" icon.\n\nUnder Log Event Destination, verify the \"Both log file and ETW event\" radio button is selected.\n\nIf the \"Both log file and ETW event\" radio button is not selected, this is a finding.\n\nNote: \"Microsoft-IIS-Logging/logs\" must be enabled prior to configuring this setting. More configuration information is available at:\nhttps://blogs.intelink.gov/blogs/_disairrt/?p=1317","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218739","title":"SRG-APP-000092-WSR-000055"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000206","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218739r1022675_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218739","discussion":"Internet Information Services (IIS) on Windows Server 2012 provides basic logging capabilities. However, because IIS takes some time to flush logs to disk, administrators do not have access to logging information in real-time. In addition, text-based log files can be difficult and time-consuming to process.\n\nIn IIS 10.0, the administrator has the option of sending logging information to Event Tracing for Windows (ETW). This option gives the administrator the ability to use standard query tools, or create custom tools, for viewing real-time logging information in ETW. This provides a significant advantage over parsing text-based log files that are not updated in real time.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000092-WSR-000055, SRG-APP-000108-WSR-000166","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218739","rule_id":"SV-218739r1022675","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Both the log file and Event Tracing for Windows (ETW) for each IIS 10.0 website must be enabled.)\nResult Analysis :        Site/Default Web Site/logfile.logTargetW3C = 'File' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'File, ETW' \n                : Site/soteriatest/logfile.logTargetW3C = 'File' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'File, ETW' \n                : Site/anothertestsite/logfile.logTargetW3C = 'File' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'File, ETW' \n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-000139","CCI-001464"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218739"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Both the log file and Event Tracing for Windows (ETW) for each IIS 10.0 website must be enabled.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000092-WSR-000055","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Note: \"Microsoft-IIS-Logging/logs\" must be enabled prior to configuring this setting.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name.\n\nClick the \"Logging\" icon.\n\nUnder Log Event Destination, select the \"Both log file and ETW event\" radio button.\n\nSelect \"Apply\" from the \"Actions\" pane."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109305","V-100201"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5A057-6C09-1014-B842-E0D27B3A6E2D","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Interview the System Administrator to review the configuration of the IIS 10.0 architecture and determine if inbound web traffic is passed through a proxy.\n\nIf the IIS 10.0 is receiving inbound web traffic through a proxy, the audit logs must be reviewed to determine if correct source information is being passed through by the proxy server.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name.\n\nClick the \"Logging\" icon.\n\nClick \"View log file\".\n\nWhen log file is displayed, review source IP information in log entries and verify entries do not reflect the IP address of the proxy server.\n\nIf the website is not behind a load balancer or proxy server, this is Not Applicable.\n\nIf the log entries in the log file(s) reflect the IP address of the proxy server as the source, this is a finding.\n\nIf provisions have been made to log the client IP via another field (i.e., utilizing X-Forwarded-For), this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218740","title":"SRG-APP-000098-WSR-000060"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000208","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218740r960900_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218740","discussion":"Web server logging capability is critical for accurate forensic analysis. Without sufficient and accurate information, a correct replay of the events cannot be determined. \n\nAscertaining the correct source (e.g., source IP), of the events is important during forensic analysis. Correctly determining the source of events will add information to the overall reconstruction of the loggable event. By determining the source of the event correctly, analysis of the enterprise can be undertaken to determine if events tied to the source occurred in other areas within the enterprise.\n\nA web server behind a load balancer or proxy server, when not configured correctly, will record the load balancer or proxy server as the source of every loggable event. When looking at the information forensically, this information is not helpful in the investigation of events. The web server must record with each event the client source of the event.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218740","rule_id":"SV-218740r960900","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-218740, SV-218740r960900, SRG-APP-000098-WSR-000060)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-000133"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.site:questionnaire:901"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"An IIS 10.0 website behind a load balancer or proxy server must produce log records containing the source client IP, and destination information.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000098-WSR-000060","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Access the proxy server through which inbound web traffic is passed and configure settings to pass web traffic to the IIS 10.0 web server transparently."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109307","V-100203"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5A430-6C09-1014-8360-F90C4064E4FC","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If this server is hosting WSUS, this requirement is Not Applicable.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nSelect the website being reviewed.\n\nUnder \"IIS\", double-click the \"Logging\" icon.\n\nVerify the \"Format:\" under \"Log File\" is configured to \"W3C\".\n\nSelect \"Fields\".\n\nUnder \"Custom Fields\", verify the following fields are selected:\n\nRequest Header &gt;&gt; Connection\n\nRequest Header &gt;&gt; Warning\n\nIf any of the above fields are not selected, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218741","title":"SRG-APP-000099-WSR-000061"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000209","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218741r1022677_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218741","discussion":"Web server logging capability is critical for accurate forensic analysis. Without sufficient and accurate information, a correct replay of the events cannot be determined.\n\nAscertaining the success or failure of an event is important during forensic analysis. Correctly determining the outcome will add information to the overall reconstruction of the loggable event. By determining the success or failure of the event correctly, analysis of the enterprise can be undertaken to determine if events tied to the event occurred in other areas within the enterprise.\n\nWithout sufficient information establishing the success or failure of the logged event, investigation into the cause of event is severely hindered. The success or failure also provides a means to measure the impact of an event and help authorized personnel to determine the appropriate response. Log record content that may be necessary to satisfy the requirement of this control includes, but is not limited to, time stamps, source and destination IP addresses, user/process identifiers, event descriptions, application-specific events, success/fail indications, file names involved, access control, or flow control rules invoked.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218741","rule_id":"SV-218741r1022677","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (W3C is enabled)\nTest            :   false (Request Header &gt;&gt; Connection)\nResult Analysis :        '[customFields]          maxCustomFieldLength:\"4096\"      ' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'sourceName:\"Connection\"\\s+sourceType:\"RequestHeader\"' \nTest            :   false (Request Header &gt;&gt; Warning)\nResult Analysis :        '[customFields]          maxCustomFieldLength:\"4096\"      ' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'sourceName:\"Warning\"\\s+sourceType:\"RequestHeader\"' \n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-000134"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218741"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 website must produce log records that contain sufficient information to establish the outcome (success or failure) of IIS 10.0 website events.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000099-WSR-000061","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nSelect the website being reviewed.\n\nUnder \"IIS\", double-click the \"Logging\" icon.\n\nConfigure the \"Format:\" under \"Log File\" to \"W3C\".\n\nSelect \"Fields\".\n\nUnder \"Custom Fields\", select the following fields:\n\nRequest Header &gt;&gt; Connection\n\nRequest Header &gt;&gt; Warning\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nSelect \"Apply\" from the \"Actions\" pane."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109309","V-100205"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5A7E9-6C09-1014-BCDC-D3EDFAAB0208","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If this server is hosting WSUS, this requirement is Not Applicable.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nAccess the IIS 10.0 web server IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nUnder \"IIS\", double-click the \"Logging\" icon.\n\nVerify the \"Format:\" under \"Log File\" is configured to \"W3C\".\n\nSelect \"Fields\".\n\nUnder \"Standard Fields\", verify \"User Agent\", \"User Name\", and \"Referrer\" are selected.\n\nUnder \"Custom Fields\", verify the following fields have been configured: \n\nRequest Header &gt;&gt; Authorization\n\nResponse Header &gt;&gt; Content-Type\n\nIf any of the above fields are not selected, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218742","title":"SRG-APP-000100-WSR-000064"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000210","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218742r1022679_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218742","discussion":"Web server logging capability is critical for accurate forensic analysis. Without sufficient and accurate information, a correct replay of the events cannot be determined.\n\nDetermining user accounts, processes running on behalf of the user, and running process identifiers also enable a better understanding of the overall event. User tool identification is also helpful to determine if events are related to overall user access or specific client tools.\n\nLog record content that may be necessary to satisfy the requirement of this control includes: time stamps, source and destination addresses, user/process identifiers, event descriptions, success/fail indications, file names involved, and access control or flow control rules invoked.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218742","rule_id":"SV-218742r1022679","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (W3C is enabled)\nTest            :   true (Standard Field - User Agent)\nTest            :   true (Standard Fields - User Name)\nTest            :   true (Standard Fields - Referrer)\nTest            :   false (Custom Field - Request Header &gt;&gt; Authorization)\nResult Analysis :        '[customFields]          maxCustomFieldLength:\"4096\"      ' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'sourceName:\"Authorization\"\\s+sourceType:\"RequestHeader\"' \nTest            :   false (Custom Field - Response Header &gt;&gt; Content-Type)\nResult Analysis :        '[customFields]          maxCustomFieldLength:\"4096\"      ' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'sourceName:\"Content-Type\"\\s+sourceType:\"ResponseHeader\"' \n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-001487"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218742"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 website must produce log records containing sufficient information to establish the identity of any user/subject or process associated with an event.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000100-WSR-000064","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nAccess the IIS 10.0 web server IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nSelect the website being reviewed.\n\nUnder \"IIS\", double-click the \"Logging\" icon.\n\nConfigure the \"Format:\" under \"Log File\" to \"W3C\".\n\nSelect \"Fields\".\n\nUnder \"Standard Fields\", select \"User Agent\", \"User Name\", and \"Referrer\".\n\nUnder \"Custom Fields\", select the following fields:\n\nRequest Header &gt;&gt; Authorization\n\nResponse Header &gt;&gt; Content-Type\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nSelect \"Apply\" from the \"Actions\" pane."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109311","V-100207"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5ABBE-6C09-1014-B894-AD0953748956","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If the server is hosting WSUS, this is not applicable.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick on the IIS 10.0 site.\n\nUnder IIS, double-click the âMIME Typesâ icon.\n\nFrom the \"Group by:\" drop-down list, select \"Content Type\".\n\nFrom the list of extensions under \"Application\", verify MIME types for OS shell program extensions have been removed, to include at a minimum, the following extensions:\n\n.exe\n.dll\n.com\n.bat\n.csh\n\nIf any OS shell MIME types are configured, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218743","title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000081"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000214","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218743r1156522_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218743","discussion":"Controlling what a user of a hosted application can access is part of the security posture of the web server. Any time a user can access more functionality than is needed for the operation of the hosted application poses a security issue. A user with too much access can view information that is not needed for the user's job role, or could use the function in an unintentional manner.\n\nA MIME tells the web server what type of program various file types and extensions are and what external utilities or programs are needed to execute the file type.\n\nA shell is a program that serves as the basic interface between the user and the operating system, so hosted application users must not have access to these programs. Shell programs may execute shell escapes and can then perform unauthorized activities that could damage the security posture of the web server.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218743","rule_id":"SV-218743r1156522","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Remove MIME Type: exe, dll, com, bat, csh)\nResult Analysis :        Collected Item did not meet the state requirement.\n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218743"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 website must have Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions (MIME) that invoke OS shell programs disabled.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000081","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick on the IIS 10.0 site.\n\nUnder IIS, double-click the âMIME Typesâ icon.\n\nFrom the \"Group by:\" drop-down list, select \"Content Type\".\n\nFrom the list of extensions under \"Application\", remove MIME types for OS shell program extensions, to include at a minimum, the following extensions:\n\n.exe\n.dll\n.com\n.bat\n.csh\n\nSelect \"Apply\" from the \"Actions\" pane."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109313","V-100209"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5AF44-6C09-1014-A2D6-B04A5DD53EDF","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If the server being reviewed is hosting SharePoint, this is not applicable.\n\nFor Handler Mappings, the ISSO must document and approve all allowable scripts the website allows (whitelist) and denies (blacklist). The whitelist and blacklist will be compared to the Handler Mappings in IIS 10.0. Handler Mappings at the site level take precedence over Handler Mappings at the server level.\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name under review.\n\nDouble-click \"Handler Mappings\".\n\nIf any script file extensions from the blacklist are enabled, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218744","title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000082"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000215","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218744r1135545_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218744","discussion":"IIS 10.0 will either allow or deny script execution based on file extension. The ability to control script execution is controlled through two features with IIS 10.0, Request Filtering and Handler Mappings.\n\nFor Handler Mappings, the ISSO must document and approve all allowable file extensions the website allows (whitelist) and denies (blacklist). The whitelist and blacklist will be compared to the Handler Mappings in IIS 10. Handler Mappings at the site level take precedence over Handler Mappings at the server level.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218744","rule_id":"SV-218744r1135545","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-218744, SV-218744r1135545, SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000082)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.site:questionnaire:1701"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Mappings to unused and vulnerable scripts on the IIS 10.0 website must be removed.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000082","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name under review.\n\nDouble-click \"Handler Mappings\".\n\nRemove any script file extensions listed on the black list that are enabled.\n\nSelect \"Apply\" from the \"Actions\" pane."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109315","V-100211"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5B384-6C09-1014-8A02-F32D206F99A1","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If the server being reviewed is hosting SharePoint, this is Not Applicable.\n\nFor Request Filtering, the ISSO must document and approve all allowable scripts the website allows (white list) and denies (black list). The white list and black list will be compared to the Request Filtering in IIS 10.0. Request Filtering at the site level take precedence over Request Filtering at the server level.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server: \n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name to review.\n\nDouble-click Request Filtering-&gt;File Name Extensions Tab.\n\nIf any script file extensions from the black list are not denied, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218745","title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000083"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000216","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218745r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218745","discussion":"IIS 10.0 will either allow or deny script execution based on file extension. The ability to control script execution is controlled through two features with IIS 10.0, Request Filtering and Handler Mappings.\n\nFor Request Filtering, the ISSO must document and approve all allowable file extensions the website allows (white list) and denies (black list) by the website. The white list and black list will be compared to the Request Filtering in IIS 10.0. Request Filtering at the site level take precedence over Request Filtering at the server level.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218745","rule_id":"SV-218745r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-218745, SV-218745r960963, SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000083)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.site:questionnaire:1901"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 website must have resource mappings set to disable the serving of certain file types.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000083","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server: \n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name to review.\n\nDouble-click Request Filtering-&gt;File Name Extensions Tab-&gt;Deny File Name Extension.\n\nAdd any script file extensions listed on the black list that are not listed.\n\nSelect \"Apply\" from the \"Actions\" pane."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109321","V-100217"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5B7B4-6C09-1014-A817-BBE02869515F","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If the server being reviewed is hosting SharePoint, this is Not Applicable.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\nRight-click on the site name under review.\nSelect \"Edit Bindings\".\n\nVerify there are hostname entries and unique IP addresses assigned to port 80 for HTTP and port 443 for HTTPS. Other approved and documented ports may be used.\n\nIf both hostname entries and unique IP addresses are not configured to port 80 for HTTP and port 443 for HTTPS (or other approved and documented port), this is a finding.\n\nNote: If certificate handling is performed at the Proxy/Load Balancer, this is not a finding.\n\nNote: If HTTP/Port 80 is not being used, and is not configured as above, this is not a finding.\n\nNote: If this IIS 10.0 installation is supporting Microsoft Exchange, and not otherwise hosting any content, this requirement is Not Applicable.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218748","title":"SRG-APP-000142-WSR-000089"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000219","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218748r1043177_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218748","discussion":"The web server must be configured to listen on a specified IP address and port. Without specifying an IP address and port for the web server to use, the web server will listen on all IP addresses available to the hosting server. If the web server has multiple IP addresses, i.e., a management IP address, the web server will also accept connections on the management IP address.\n\nAccessing the hosted application through an IP address normally used for non-application functions opens the possibility of user access to resources, utilities, files, ports, and protocols that are protected on the desired application IP address.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218748","rule_id":"SV-218748r1043177","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Verify there exists a hostname entries and unique IP addresses to port 80 for HTTP. )\nResult Analysis :        Site/Default Web Site/bindings = 'http/*:80:' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'http\\/[\\.0-9]+:80:\\w+' \n                : Site/soteriatest/bindings = 'http/192.168.40.167:8080:' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'http\\/[\\.0-9]+:80:\\w+' \n                : Site/anothertestsite/bindings = 'http/*:8020:' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'http\\/[\\.0-9]+:80:\\w+' \nTest            :   false (Verify there exists a hostname entries and unique IP addresses to port 443 for HTTPS. )\nResult Analysis :        Site/Default Web Site/bindings = 'http/*:80:' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'https\\/[\\.0-9]+:443:\\w+' \n                : Site/soteriatest/bindings = 'http/192.168.40.167:8080:' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'https\\/[\\.0-9]+:443:\\w+' \n                : Site/anothertestsite/bindings = 'http/*:8020:' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'https\\/[\\.0-9]+:443:\\w+' \n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-000382"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218748"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Each IIS 10.0 website must be assigned a default host header.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000142-WSR-000089","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Note: If the server being reviewed is hosting SharePoint, this is Not Applicable.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nRight-click on the site name under review.\n\nSelect \"Edit Bindings\".\n\nAssign hostname entries and unique IP addresses to port 80 for HTTP and port 443 for HTTPS. Other approved and documented ports may be used.\n\nClick \"OK\".\n\nSelect \"Apply\" from the \"Actions\" pane."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109323","V-100219"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5BB55-6C09-1014-82C0-C331D02AE781","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If the server being reviewed is a public IIS 10.0 web server, this is not applicable.\nNote: If the server being reviewed is hosting SharePoint, this is not applicable.\nNote: If the server being reviewed is hosting WSUS, this is not applicable.\nNote: If certificate handling is performed at the Proxy/Load Balancer, this is not applicable.\nNote: If the server being reviewed is hosting Simple Certificate Enrollment Services (SCEP), this is not applicable.\nNote: If the server being reviewed is hosting Network Device Enrollment Services (NDES), this is not applicable.\nNote: If the server is providing OCSP, and not otherwise hosting any content, this requirement is not applicable.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nDouble-click the \"SSL Settings\" icon.\n\nVerify the \"Clients Certificate Required\" check box is selected.\n\nIf the \"Clients Certificate Required\" check box is not selected, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218749","title":"SRG-APP-000172-WSR-000104"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000220","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218749r1111805_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218749","discussion":"A DoD private website must use PKI as an authentication mechanism for web users. Information systems residing behind web servers requiring authorization based on individual identity must use the identity provided by certificate-based authentication to support access control decisions. Not using client certificates allows an attacker unauthenticated access to private websites.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000172-WSR-000104, SRG-APP-000224-WSR-000135, SRG-APP-000427-WSR-000186","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218749","rule_id":"SV-218749r1111805","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (SslRequireCert Setting - Verify Require SSL is checked. Verify Client Certificates Required is selected. Click the site under review. Select Configuration Editor under the Management section. From the Section: drop-down list at the top of the configuration editor, locate âsystem.webServer/security/accessâ. The values for sslFlags must include ssl128. If the Require SSL is not selected, this is a finding. If the Client Certificates Required is not selected, this is a finding. If the sslFlags is not set to ssl128, this is a finding.)\nResult Analysis :        Site/Default Web Site/access/sslflags = 'None' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'SslRequireCert' \n                : Site/soteriatest/access/sslflags = 'None' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'SslRequireCert' \n                : Site/anothertestsite/access/sslflags = 'None' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'SslRequireCert' \n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-000197","CCI-001188","CCI-002470"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218749"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"A private IIS 10.0 website authentication mechanism must use client certificates to transmit session identifier to assure integrity.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000172-WSR-000104","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nDouble-click the \"SSL Settings\" icon.\n\nVerify the \"Clients Certificate Required\" check box is selected.\n\nSelect \"Apply\" from the \"Actions\" pane."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109325","V-100221"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5BEED-6C09-1014-84FE-E143EF5A2193","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Check the account used for anonymous access to the website.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nDouble-click \"Authentication\" in the IIS section of the websiteâs Home Pane.\n\nIf \"Anonymous access\" is disabled, this is Not a Finding.\n\nIf \"Anonymous access\" is enabled, click \"Anonymous Authentication\".\n\nClick \"Edit\" in the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nIf the \"Specific user\" radio button is enabled and an ID is specified in the adjacent control box, this is the ID being used for anonymous access. Note the account name.\n\nIf nothing is tied to \"Specific User\", this is Not a Finding.\n\nCheck privileged groups that may allow the anonymous account inappropriate membership:\nOpen \"Computer Management\" on the machine.\n\nExpand \"Local Users and Groups\".\n\nOpen \"Groups\".\n\nReview the members of any of the following privileged groups:\n\nAdministrators\nBackup Operators\nCertificate Services (of any designation)\nDistributed COM Users\nEvent Log Readers\nNetwork Configuration Operators\nPerformance Log Users\nPerformance Monitor Users\nPower Users\nPrint Operators\nRemote Desktop Users\nReplicator\n\nDouble-click each group and review its members.\n\nIf the IUSR account or any account noted above used for anonymous access is a member of any group with privileged access, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218750","title":"SRG-APP-000211-WSR-000031"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000221","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218750r1138073_rule","severity":"high","group_id_src":"V-218750","discussion":"Many of the security problems that occur are not the result of a user gaining access to files or data for which the user does not have permissions, but rather users are assigned incorrect permissions to unauthorized data. The files, directories, and data stored on the web server must be evaluated and a determination made concerning authorized access to information and programs on the server. Only authorized users and administrative accounts will be allowed on the host server in order to maintain the web server, applications, and review the server operations.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218750","rule_id":"SV-218750r1138073","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT I, V-218750, SV-218750r1138073, SRG-APP-000211-WSR-000031)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-001082"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.site:questionnaire:2501"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Anonymous IIS 10.0 website access accounts must be restricted.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000211-WSR-000031","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Remove the Anonymous access account from all privileged accounts and all privileged groups."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109327","V-100223"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5C27A-6C09-1014-B4C8-C652E549016B","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If ASP.NET is not installed, this is Not Applicable.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name.\n\nUnder the \"ASP.NET\" section, select \"Session State\".\n\nUnder \"Session State\" Mode Settings, verify the \"In Process\" mode is selected.\n\nIf the \"In Process\" mode is selected, this is not a finding.\n\nAlternative method:\n\nClick the site name.\n\nSelect \"Configuration Editor\" under the \"Management\" section.\n\nFrom the \"Section:\" drop-down list at the top of the configuration editor, locate \"system.web/sessionState\".\n\nVerify the \"mode\" reflects \"InProc\".\n\nIf the \"mode\" is not set to \"InProc\", this is a finding.\n\nIf the system being reviewed is part of a Web Farm, interview the System Administrator to ensure Session State Tracking is enabled via a SQL server, or other means. If Session State Tracking is enabled on the Web Farm, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218751","title":"SRG-APP-000224-WSR-000136"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000223","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218751r1043181_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218751","discussion":"Communication between a client and the web server is done using the HTTP protocol, but HTTP is a stateless protocol. To maintain a connection or session, a web server will generate a session identifier (ID) for each client session when the session is initiated. The session ID allows the web server to track a user session and, in many cases, the user, if the user previously logged into a hosted application.\n\nBy being able to guess session IDs, an attacker can easily perform a man-in-the-middle attack. To truly generate random session identifiers that cannot be reproduced, the web server session ID generator, when used twice with the same input criteria, must generate an unrelated random ID.\n\nThe session ID generator must be a FIPS 140-2-approved generator.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218751","rule_id":"SV-218751r1043181","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","status":"not_applicable","ccis":["CCI-001188"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.site:def:218751"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 website must generate unique session identifiers that cannot be reliably reproduced.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000224-WSR-000136","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name.\n\nUnder the ASP.NET section, select \"Session State\".\n\nUnder \"Session State\" Mode Settings, select the \"In Process\" mode."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109329","V-100225"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5C60C-6C09-1014-BA4F-CBFDAACA0B5A","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If this server is hosting WSUS, this requirement is not applicable.\nNote: If this IIS 10.0 installation is supporting Microsoft Exchange, and not otherwise hosting any content, this requirement is not applicable.\nNote: If this server is hosting the SharePoint Web Services site, this requirement is not applicable.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name under review.\n\nClick the \"Advanced Settings\" from the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nReview the Physical Path.\n\nIf the Path is on the same partition as the OS, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218752","title":"SRG-APP-000233-WSR-000146"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000224","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218752r1111807_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218752","discussion":"The content database is accessed by multiple anonymous users when the web server is in production. By locating the content database on the same partition as the web server system file, the risk for unauthorized access to these protected files is increased. Additionally, having the content database path on the same drive as the system folders also increases the potential for a drive space exhaustion attack.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218752","rule_id":"SV-218752r1111807","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Verify each web directory is not on boot drive)\nResult Analysis :        Collected Item did not meet the state requirement.\n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-001084"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218752"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 website document directory must be in a separate partition from the IIS 10.0 websites system files.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000233-WSR-000146","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name under review.\n\nClick the \"Advanced Settings\" from the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nChange the Physical Path to the new partition and directory location."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109331","V-100227"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5C969-6C09-1014-81B8-D8CE57829C25","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick on the site name.\n\nDouble-click the \"Request Filtering\" icon.\n\nClick \"Edit Feature Settings\" in the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nIf the \"maxUrl\" value is not set to \"4096\" or less, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218753","title":"SRG-APP-000246-WSR-000149"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000225","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218753r961152_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218753","discussion":"Request filtering replaces URLScan in IIS, enabling administrators to create a more granular rule set with which to allow or reject inbound web content. By setting limits on web requests, it helps to ensure availability of web services and may also help mitigate the risk of buffer overflow type attacks. The MaxURL Request Filter limits the number of bytes the server will accept in a URL.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218753","rule_id":"SV-218753r961152","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (The web-site Request Filtering maxUrl value must be 4096 or less)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001094"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218753"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 website must be configured to limit the maxURL.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000246-WSR-000149","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nClick the site name under review.\n\nDouble-click the \"Request Filtering\" icon.\n\nClick \"Edit Feature Settings\" in the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nSet the \"maxURL\" value to \"4096\" or less."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109333","V-100229"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5CCBC-6C09-1014-9F72-BAFCF84F39A9","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick on the site name.\n\nDouble-click the \"Request Filtering\" icon.\n\nClick \"Edit Feature Settings\" in the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nIf the \"maxAllowedContentLength\" value is not explicitly set to \"2147483647\" or less or a length documented and approved by the ISSO, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218754","title":"SRG-APP-000246-WSR-000149"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000226","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218754r1156525_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218754","discussion":"By setting limits on web requests, it ensures availability of web services and mitigates the risk of buffer overflow type attacks. The maxAllowedContentLength Request Filter limits the number of bytes the server will accept in a request.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218754","rule_id":"SV-218754r1156525","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (The web-site Request Filtering maxAllowedContentLength value must be 2147483647 or less)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001094"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218754"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 website must be configured to limit the size of web requests.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000246-WSR-000149","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name under review.\n\nDouble-click the \"Request Filtering\" icon.\n\nClick \"Edit Feature Settings\" in the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nSet the \"maxAllowedContentLength\" value to \"2147483647\" or less."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109335","V-100231"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5D00B-6C09-1014-B694-E939956CD064","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name.\n\nDouble-click the \"Request Filtering\" icon.\n\nClick âEdit Feature Settingsâ in the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nIf the \"Maximum Query String\" value is not set to \"2048\" or less, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218755","title":"SRG-APP-000246-WSR-000149"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000227","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218755r961152_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218755","discussion":"Setting limits on web requests helps to ensure availability of web services and may also help mitigate the risk of buffer overflow type attacks. The Maximum Query String Request Filter describes the upper limit on allowable query string lengths. Upon exceeding the configured value, IIS will generate a Status Code 404.15.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218755","rule_id":"SV-218755r961152","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (The web-site Request Filtering maxQueryString value must be 2048 or less)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001094"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218755"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 websites Maximum Query String limit must be configured.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000246-WSR-000149","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name under review.\n\nDouble-click the \"Request Filtering\" icon.\n\nClick \"Edit Feature Settings\" in the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nSet the \"Maximum Query String\" value to \"2048\" or less."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109337","V-100233"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5D35A-6C09-1014-BBAF-EC4A98E731D8","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name.\n\nDouble-click the \"Request Filtering\" icon.\n\nClick \"Edit Feature Settings\" in the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nIf the \"Allow high-bit characters\" check box is checked, this is a finding.\n\nNote: If this IIS 10.0 installation is supporting Microsoft Exchange, and not otherwise hosting any content, this requirement is Not Applicable.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218756","title":"SRG-APP-000246-WSR-000149"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000228","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218756r961152_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218756","discussion":"Setting limits on web requests ensures availability of web services and mitigates the risk of buffer overflow type attacks. The allow high-bit characters Request Filter enables rejection of requests containing non-ASCII characters.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218756","rule_id":"SV-218756r961152","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (The web-site must not allow non-ASCII characters in URLs.)\nResult Analysis :        Site/Default Web Site/requestfiltering/allowhighbitcharacters = 'true' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'false' \n                : Site/soteriatest/requestfiltering/allowhighbitcharacters = 'true' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'false' \n                : Site/anothertestsite/requestfiltering/allowhighbitcharacters = 'true' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'false' \n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-001094"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218756"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Non-ASCII characters in URLs must be prohibited by any IIS 10.0 website.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000246-WSR-000149","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name under review.\n\nDouble-click the \"Request Filtering\" icon.\n\nClick \"Edit Feature Settings\" in the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nUncheck the \"Allow high-bit characters\" check box."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109339","V-100235"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5D6CC-6C09-1014-BA8E-F8978A074B99","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If the server being reviewed is hosting SharePoint, this is Not Applicable.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name.\n\nDouble-click the \"Request Filtering\" icon.\n\nClick \"Edit Feature Settings\" in the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nIf the \"Allow double escaping\" check box is checked, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218757","title":"SRG-APP-000246-WSR-000149"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000229","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218757r961152_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218757","discussion":"Request filtering enables administrators to create a more granular rule set with which to allow or reject inbound web content. Setting limits on web requests ensures availability of web services and mitigates the risk of buffer overflow type attacks. When the \"Allow double escaping\" option is disabled, it prevents attacks that rely on double-encoded requests.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218757","rule_id":"SV-218757r961152","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (The web-site Request Filtering Allow double escaping must not be enabled)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001094"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218757"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Double encoded URL requests must be prohibited by any IIS 10.0 website.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000246-WSR-000149","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name under review.\n\nDouble-click the \"Request Filtering\" icon.\n\nClick \"Edit Feature Settings\" in the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nUncheck the \"Allow double escaping\" check box."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109341","V-100237"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5DA2E-6C09-1014-8A4F-B8B0FBAC73DD","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If the server being reviewed is hosting SharePoint, this is Not Applicable.\n\nNote: If the server being reviewed is hosting Network Device Enrollment Services (NDES), this is Not Applicable.\n\nNote: If the server being reviewed is hosting Azure DevOps (ADO), this is Not Applicable.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name.\n\nDouble-click the \"Request Filtering\" icon.\n\nClick \"Edit Feature Settings\" in the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nIf the \"Allow unlisted file name extensions\" check box is checked, this is a finding.\n\nNote: If this IIS 10.0 installation is supporting Microsoft Exchange, and not otherwise hosting any content, this requirement is Not Applicable.\n\nNote: If this IIS 10.0 installation is supporting Splunk, this requirement is Not Applicable.\n\nNote: If this IIS 10.0 installation is supporting WSUS, this requirement is Not Applicable.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218758","title":"SRG-APP-000246-WSR-000149"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000230","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218758r1156527_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218758","discussion":"Request filtering enables administrators to create a more granular rule set to allow or reject inbound web content. Setting limits on web requests helps to ensure availability of web services and may also help mitigate the risk of buffer overflow type attacks. The allow unlisted property of the \"File Extensions Request\" filter enables rejection of requests containing specific file extensions not defined in the \"File Extensions\" filter. Tripping this filter will cause IIS to generate a Status Code 404.7.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218758","rule_id":"SV-218758r1156527","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (The web-site Request Filtering Allow unlisted file extensions must not be enabled)\nResult Analysis :        Site/Default Web Site/requestfiltering/fileExtensions.allowUnlisted = 'true' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'false' \n                : Site/soteriatest/requestfiltering/fileExtensions.allowUnlisted = 'true' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'false' \n                : Site/anothertestsite/requestfiltering/fileExtensions.allowUnlisted = 'true' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'false' \n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-001094"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218758"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Unlisted file extensions in URL requests must be filtered by any IIS 10.0 website.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000246-WSR-000149","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name under review.\n\nDouble-click the \"Request Filtering\" icon.\n\nClick \"Edit Feature Settings\" in the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nUncheck the \"Allow unlisted file extensions\" check box."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109343","V-100239"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5DD79-6C09-1014-9123-F545366B2F6D","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nClick the Site.\n\nDouble-click the \"Directory Browsing\" icon.\n\nIf \"Directory Browsing\" is not installed, this is Not Applicable.\n\nUnder the \"Actions\" pane, verify \"Directory Browsing\" is \"Disabled\".\n\nIf \"Directory Browsing\" is not \"Disabled\", this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218759","title":"SRG-APP-000251-WSR-000157"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000231","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218759r961158_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218759","discussion":"Directory browsing allows the contents of a directory to be displayed upon request from a web client. If directory browsing is enabled for a directory in IIS, users could receive a web page listing the contents of the directory. If directory browsing is enabled the risk of inadvertently disclosing sensitive content is increased.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218759","rule_id":"SV-218759r961158","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (The web-site Directory Browsing must not be enabled)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001310"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218759"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Directory Browsing on the IIS 10.0 website must be disabled.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000251-WSR-000157","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the Site.\n\nDouble-click the \"Directory Browsing\" icon.\n\nUnder the \"Actions\" pane, click \"Disabled\"."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109345","V-100241"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5E0D7-6C09-1014-88CC-8BCF35B18C86","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If this server is hosting WSUS, this requirement is Not Applicable.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name under review.\n\nDouble-click the \"Error Pages\" icon.\n\nClick each error message and click \"Edit Feature\" setting from the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nIf any error message is not set to \"Detailed errors for local requests and custom error pages for remote requests\" or \"Custom error pages\", this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218760","title":"SRG-APP-000266-WSR-000159"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000233","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218760r1022690_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218760","discussion":"HTTP error pages contain information that could enable an attacker to gain access to an information system. Failure to prevent the sending of HTTP error pages with full information to remote requesters exposes internal configuration information to potential attackers.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218760","rule_id":"SV-218760r1022690","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (One or more child tests must be true. (OR))\nTest            :   true (Site error message is not set to Detailed errors for local requests and custom error pages for remote requests)\nTest            :   false (Site error message is not set to Detailed errors for local requests and custom error pages for remote requests)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001312"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218760"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Warning and error messages displayed to clients must be modified to minimize the identity of the IIS 10.0 website, patches, loaded modules, and directory paths.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000266-WSR-000159","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name under review.\n\nDouble-click the \"Error Pages\" icon.\n\nClick each error message and click \"Edit Feature\" Setting from the \"Actions\" pane; set each error message to \"Detailed errors for local requests and custom error pages for remote requests\" or \"Custom error pages\"."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109347","V-100243"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5E41C-6C09-1014-B210-AEFF39C25F74","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If the server being reviewed is hosting SharePoint, this is Not Applicable.\nNote: If the \".NET feature\" is not installed, this check is Not Applicable.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name under review.\n\nDouble-click \".NET Compilation\".\n\nScroll down to the \"Behavior\" section and verify the value for \"Debug\" is set to \"False\".\n\nIf the \"Debug\" value is not set to \"False\", this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218761","title":"SRG-APP-000266-WSR-000160"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000234","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218761r961167_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218761","discussion":"Setting compilation debug to false ensures detailed error information does not inadvertently display during live application usage, mitigating the risk of application information being displayed to users.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218761","rule_id":"SV-218761r961167","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Debug must be turned off on a production website.)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-001312"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218761"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Debugging and trace information used to diagnose the IIS 10.0 website must be disabled.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000266-WSR-000160","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name under review.\n\nDouble-click \".NET Compilation\".\n\nScroll down to the \"Behavior\" section and set the value for \"Debug\" to \"False\"."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109349","V-100245"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5E76E-6C09-1014-A775-D10D48B65E66","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"If this IIS 10.0 installation is supporting Microsoft Exchange, and not otherwise hosting any content, this requirement is Not Applicable.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\nClick the Application Pools.\nHighlight an Application Pool to review and click \"Advanced Settings\" in the \"Actions\" pane.\nScroll down to the \"Process Model\" section and verify the value for \"Idle Time-out\" is not \"0\".\n\nIf the \"Idle Time-out\" is set to \"0\", this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218762","title":"SRG-APP-000295-WSR-000012"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000235","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218762r1043182_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218762","discussion":"The idle time-out attribute controls the amount of time a worker process will remain idle before it shuts down. A worker process is idle if it is not processing requests and no new requests are received.\n\nThe purpose of this attribute is to conserve system resources; the default value for idle time-out is 20 minutes.\n\nBy default, the World Wide Web (WWW) service establishes an overlapped recycle, in which the worker process to be shut down is kept running until after a new worker process is started.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218762","rule_id":"SV-218762r1043182","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (The Idle Timeout monitor.)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-002361"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218762"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The Idle Time-out monitor for each IIS 10.0 website must be enabled.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000295-WSR-000012","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the Application Pools.\n\nHighlight an Application Pool to review and click \"Advanced Settings\" in the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nScroll down to the \"Process Model\" section and set the value for \"Idle Time-out\" to something other than \"0\". \"20\" or less is recommended if the amount of RAM on the system is limited."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109351","V-100247"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5EAB7-6C09-1014-8DE5-88F8402F15E7","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name.\n\nSelect \"Configuration Editor\" under the \"Management\" section.\n\nFrom the \"Section:\" drop-down list at the top of the configuration editor, locate \"system.web/sessionState\".\n\nVerify the \"timeout\" is set to \"00:15:00 or lessâ.\n\nIf \"timeout\" is not set to \"00:15:00 or lessâ, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218763","title":"SRG-APP-000295-WSR-000134"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000236","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218763r1043182_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218763","discussion":"Leaving sessions open indefinitely is a major security risk. An attacker can easily use an already authenticated session to access the hosted application as the previously authenticated user. By closing sessions after a set period of inactivity, the web server can make certain that those sessions that are not closed through the user logging out of an application are eventually closed.\n\nAcceptable values are 5 minutes for high-value applications, 10 minutes for medium-value applications, and 15 minutes for low-value applications.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218763","rule_id":"SV-218763r1043182","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Website Configuration setting system.web/sessionState timeout must be equal to or less than 15.)\nResult Analysis :        Site/Default Web Site/system.web/sessionState/timeout = '20' failed test of 'less than or equal' compared to '15' \n                : Site/soteriatest/system.web/sessionState/timeout = '20' failed test of 'less than or equal' compared to '15' \n                : Site/anothertestsite/system.web/sessionState/timeout = '20' failed test of 'less than or equal' compared to '15' \n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-002361"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218763"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 websites connectionTimeout setting must be explicitly configured to disconnect an idle session.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000295-WSR-000134","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name.\n\nSelect \"Configuration Editor\" under the \"Management\" section.\n\nFrom the \"Section:\" drop-down list at the top of the configuration editor, locate \"system.web/sessionState\". \n\nSet the \"timeout\" to \"00:15:00 or lessâ.\n\nIn the \"Actions\" pane, click \"Apply\"."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109353","V-100249"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5EE27-6C09-1014-B82C-CC45A0CA7E93","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Interview the System Administrator and Web Manager.\n\nAsk for documentation for the IIS 10.0 web server administration.\n\nVerify there are documented procedures for shutting down an IIS 10.0 website in the event of an attack. The procedure should, at a minimum, provide the following steps:\n\nDetermine the respective website for the application at risk of an attack.\n\nAccess the IIS 10.0 web server IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nSelect the respective website.\n\nIn the \"Actions\" pane, under \"Manage Website\", click \"Stop\".\n\nIf necessary, stop all websites.\n\nIf necessary, stop the IIS 10.0 web server by selecting the web server in the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nIn the \"Actions\" pane, under \"Manage Server\", click \"Stop\".\n\nIf there are not documented procedures with, at a minimum, the mentioned steps for stopping a website, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218764","title":"SRG-APP-000316-WSR-000170"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000237","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218764r961281_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218764","discussion":"During an attack on the web server or any of the hosted applications, the system administrator may need to disconnect or disable access by users to stop the attack.\n\nThe web server must provide a capability to disconnect users to a hosted application without compromising other hosted applications unless deemed necessary to stop the attack. Methods to disconnect or disable connections are to stop the application service for a specified hosted application, stop the web server, or block all connections through web server access list.\n\nThe web server capabilities used to disconnect or disable users from connecting to hosted applications and the web server must be documented to make certain that during an attack, the proper action is taken to conserve connectivity to any other hosted application if possible and to make certain log data is conserved for later forensic analysis.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218764","rule_id":"SV-218764r961281","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-218764, SV-218764r961281, SRG-APP-000316-WSR-000170)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-002322"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.site:questionnaire:5301"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 website must provide the capability to immediately disconnect or disable remote access to the hosted applications.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000316-WSR-000170","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Prepare documented procedures for shutting down an IIS 10.0 website in the event of an attack. The procedure should, at a minimum, provide the following steps:\n\nDetermine the respective website for the application at risk of an attack.\n\nAccess the IIS 10.0 web server IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nSelect the respective website.\n\nIn the \"Actions\" pane, under \"Manage Website\", click \"Stop\".\n\nIf necessary, stop all websites.\n\nIf necessary, stop the IIS 10.0 web server by selecting the web server in the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nIn the \"Actions\" pane, under \"Manage Server\", click \"Stop\"."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109355","V-100251"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5F18B-6C09-1014-8C43-C2D7374D6E44","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nAccess the IIS 10.0 web server IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nUnder \"IIS\" double-click on the \"Logging\" icon.\n\nIn the \"Logging\" configuration box, determine the \"Directory:\" to which the \"W3C\" logging is being written.\n\nConfirm with the System Administrator that the designated log path is of sufficient size to maintain the logging.\n\nUnder \"Log File Rollover\", verify \"Do not create new log files\" is not selected.\n\nVerify a schedule is configured to rollover log files on a regular basis.\n\nConsult with the System Administrator to determine if there is a documented process for moving the log files off of the IIS 10.0 web server to another logging device.\n\nIf the designated logging path device is not of sufficient space to maintain all log files and there is not a schedule to rollover files on a regular basis, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218765","title":"SRG-APP-000357-WSR-000150"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000238","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218765r961392_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218765","discussion":"To make certain the logging mechanism used by the web server has sufficient storage capacity in which to write the logs, the logging mechanism must be able to allocate log record storage capacity.\n\nThe task of allocating log record storage capacity is usually performed during initial installation of the logging mechanism. The system administrator will usually coordinate the allocation of physical drive space with the web server administrator along with the physical location of the partition and disk. Refer to NIST SP 800-92 for specific requirements on log rotation and storage dependent on the impact of the web server.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218765","rule_id":"SV-218765r961392","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-218765, SV-218765r961392, SRG-APP-000357-WSR-000150)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-001849"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.site:questionnaire:5501"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 website must use a logging mechanism configured to allocate log record storage capacity large enough to accommodate the logging requirements of the IIS 10.0 website.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000357-WSR-000150","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nUnder \"IIS\" double-click on the \"Logging\" icon.\n\nIf necessary, in the \"Logging\" configuration box, redesignate a log path to a location able to house the logs.\n\nUnder \"Log File Rollover\", deselect the \"Do not create new log files\" setting.\n\nConfigure a schedule to rollover log files on a regular basis."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109357","V-100253"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5F4F3-6C09-1014-942D-89AD1987F84D","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If the server is providing OCSP, and not otherwise hosting any content, this requirement is not applicable.\n\nReview the website to determine if HTTP and HTTPs (e.g., 80 and 443) are used in accordance with those ports and services registered and approved for use by the DOD PPSM. Any variation in PPS will be documented, registered, and approved by the PPSM.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name under review.\n\nIn the \"Action\" Pane, click \"Bindings\".\n\nReview the ports and protocols. If unknown ports or protocols are used, then this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218766","title":"SRG-APP-000383-WSR-000175"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000239","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218766r1111809_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218766","discussion":"Web servers provide numerous processes, features, and functionalities that use TCP/IP ports. Some of these processes may be deemed unnecessary or too unsecure to run on a production system.\n\nThe web server must provide the capability to disable or deactivate network-related services deemed to be non-essential to the server mission, too unsecure, or prohibited by the PPSM CAL and vulnerability assessments.\n\nFailure to comply with DoD ports, protocols, and services (PPS) requirements can result in compromise of enclave boundary protections and/or functionality of the AIS.\n\nThe ISSM will ensure web servers are configured to use only authorized PPS in accordance with the Network Infrastructure STIG, DoD Instruction 8551.1, PPSM, and the associated PPS Assurance Category Assignments List.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218766","rule_id":"SV-218766r1111809","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-218766, SV-218766r1111809, SRG-APP-000383-WSR-000175)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-001762"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.site:questionnaire:5701"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 websites must use ports, protocols, and services according to Ports, Protocols, and Services Management (PPSM) guidelines.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000383-WSR-000175","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name under review.\n\nIn the \"Action\" Pane, click \"Bindings\".\n\nEdit to change an existing binding and set the correct ports and protocol."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109359","V-100255"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5F835-6C09-1014-B90C-9D4A278130A1","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If the server being reviewed is hosting WSUS, this is not applicable.\nNote: If the server is providing OCSP, and not otherwise hosting any content, this requirement is not applicable.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name under review.\n\nClick \"Bindings\" in the \"Action\" Pane.\n\nClick the \"HTTPS type\" from the box.\n\nClick \"Edit\".\n\nClick \"View\" and then review and verify the certificate path.\n\nIf the list of CAs in the trust hierarchy does not lead to the DOD PKI Root CA, DOD-approved external certificate authority (ECA), or DOD-approved external partner, this is a finding.\n\nIf HTTPS is not an available type under site bindings, this is a finding.\n\nIf HTTPS is not an available type under site bindings, and the Web Server ONLY communicates directly with a load balancer/proxy server with IP address and Domain Restrictions in place, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218767","title":"SRG-APP-000427-WSR-000186"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000241","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218767r1111811_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218767","discussion":"The use of a DOD PKI certificate ensures clients the private website they are connecting to is legitimate, and is an essential part of the DOD defense-in-depth strategy.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218767","rule_id":"SV-218767r1111811","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-218767, SV-218767r1111811, SRG-APP-000427-WSR-000186)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-002470"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.site:questionnaire:5901"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 website must only accept client certificates issued by DOD PKI or DOD-approved PKI Certification Authorities (CAs).","group_title":"SRG-APP-000427-WSR-000186","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"To add DOD Certificates to the Server, if not already present:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the Server name.\n\nDouble-click \"Server Certificates\".\n\nClick \"Import\" under the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nBrowse to the DOD certificate location, select it, and click \"OK\".\n\nRemove any non-DOD certificates if present.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server to bind the certificates to the site:\n\nClick on the site needing the certificate.\n\nSelect \"Bindings\" under the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nClick on the binding needing a certificate and select \"Edit\", or add a site binding for HTTPS.\n\nAssign the certificate to the website by choosing it under the \"SSL Certificate\" drop-down and clicking \"OK\"."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109361","V-100257"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB5FBAA-6C09-1014-B905-F72B3CDBDD39","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Notes: \n- If SSL is installed on load balancer/proxy server through which traffic is routed to the IIS 10.0 server, and the IIS 10.0 server receives traffic from the load balancer/proxy server, the SSL requirement must be met on the load balancer/proxy server. In this case, this requirement is not applicable.\n- If this is a public-facing web server, this requirement is not applicable.\n- If this server is hosting WSUS, this requirement is not applicable.\n- If the server being reviewed is hosting SharePoint, this is not applicable.\n- If the server being reviewed is hosting Simple Certificate Enrollment Services (SCEP), this is not applicable.\n- If the server being reviewed is hosting Network Device Enrollment Services (NDES), this is not applicable.\n- If the server is providing OCSP, and not otherwise hosting any content, this requirement is not applicable.\n- If the server is providing CRL, and not otherwise hosting any content, this requirement is not applicable.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nDouble-click the \"SSL Settings\" icon under the \"IIS\" section.\n\nVerify \"Require SSL\" is checked.\n\nVerify \"Client Certificates Required\" is selected.\n\nClick the site under review.\n\nSelect \"Configuration Editor\" under the \"Management\" section.\n\nFrom the \"Section:\" drop-down list at the top of the configuration editor, locate \"system.webServer/security/access\".\n\nThe value for \"sslFlags\" set must include \"ssl128\".\n\nIf the \"Require SSL\" is not selected, this is a finding.\n\nIf the \"Client Certificates Required\" is not selected, this is a finding. Note: \"Client Certificates Required\" can be considered Not Applicable in a Single Sign On (SSO) scenario where client certificates are no longer processed locally.\n\nIf the \"sslFlags\" is not set to \"ssl128\", this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218768","title":"SRG-APP-000429-WSR-000113"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000242","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218768r1156529_rule","severity":"high","group_id_src":"V-218768","discussion":"TLS encryption is a required security setting for a private web server. Encryption of private information is essential to ensuring data confidentiality. If private information is not encrypted, it can be intercepted and easily read by an unauthorized party. A private web server must use a FIPS 140-2/140-3 approved TLS version, and all non-FIPS-approved SSL versions must be disabled.\n\nNIST SP 800-52 specifies the preferred configurations for government systems.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218768","rule_id":"SV-218768r1156529","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (SSL128 is enabled - Verify Require SSL is checked. Verify Client Certificates Required is selected. Click the site under review. Select Configuration Editor under the Management section. From the Section: drop-down list at the top of the configuration editor, locate âsystem.webServer/security/accessâ. The values for sslFlags must include ssl128. If the Require SSL is not selected, this is a finding. If the Client Certificates Required is not selected, this is a finding. If the sslFlags is not set to ssl128, this is a finding.)\nResult Analysis :        Site/Default Web Site/access/sslflags = 'None' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'Ssl128' \n                : Site/soteriatest/access/sslflags = 'None' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'Ssl128' \n                : Site/anothertestsite/access/sslflags = 'None' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'Ssl128' \nTest            :   false (SslRequireCert Setting - Verify Require SSL is checked. Verify Client Certificates Required is selected. Click the site under review. Select Configuration Editor under the Management section. From the Section: drop-down list at the top of the configuration editor, locate âsystem.webServer/security/accessâ. The values for sslFlags must include ssl128. If the Require SSL is not selected, this is a finding. If the Client Certificates Required is not selected, this is a finding. If the sslFlags is not set to ssl128, this is a finding.)\nResult Analysis :        Site/Default Web Site/access/sslflags = 'None' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'SslRequireCert' \n                : Site/soteriatest/access/sslflags = 'None' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'SslRequireCert' \n                : Site/anothertestsite/access/sslflags = 'None' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'SslRequireCert' \nTest            :   false (SSL is enabled - Click the site name. Double-click the 'SSL Settings' icon. Verify 'Require SSL is selected' If the 'Require SSL ' is not selected, this is a finding.)\nResult Analysis :        Site/Default Web Site/access/sslflags = 'None' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'Ssl' \n                : Site/soteriatest/access/sslflags = 'None' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'Ssl' \n                : Site/anothertestsite/access/sslflags = 'None' failed test of 'pattern match' compared to 'Ssl' \n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-002476"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218768"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 private website must employ cryptographic mechanisms (TLS) and require client certificates.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000429-WSR-000113","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nDouble-click the \"SSL Settings\" icon under the \"IIS\" section.\n\nSelect the \"Require SSL\" setting.\n\nSelect the \"Client Certificates Required\" setting.\n\nClick \"Apply\" in the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nClick the site under review.\n\nSelect \"Configuration Editor\" under the \"Management\" section.\n\nFrom the \"Section:\" drop-down list at the top of the configuration editor, locate \"system.webServer/security/access\".\n\nClick on the drop-down list for \"sslFlags\".\n\nSelect the \"Ssl128\" check box.\n\nClick \"Apply\" in the \"Actions\" pane."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109363","V-100259"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB60082-6C09-1014-800D-D48677E9F4AE","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nAccess the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nSelect the website being reviewed.\n\nUnder \"Management\" section, double-click the \"Configuration Editor\" icon.\n\nFrom the \"Section:\" drop-down list, select \"system.webServer/asp\".\n\nExpand the \"session\" section.\n\nVerify the \"keepSessionIdSecure\" is set to \"True\".\n\nIf the \"keepSessionIdSecure\" is not set to \"True\", this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218769","title":"SRG-APP-000439-WSR-000152"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000244","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218769r961632_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218769","discussion":"The HTTP protocol is a stateless protocol. To maintain a session, a session identifier is used. The session identifier is a piece of data used to identify a session and a user. If the session identifier is compromised by an attacker, the session can be hijacked. By encrypting the session identifier, the identifier becomes more difficult for an attacker to hijack, decrypt, and use before the session has expired.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218769","rule_id":"SV-218769r961632","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (Website system.webServer/asp sessions.keepSessionIdSecure setting)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-002418"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218769"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"IIS 10.0 website session IDs must be sent to the client using TLS.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000439-WSR-000152","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nAccess the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nSelect the website being reviewed.\n\nUnder \"Management\" section, double-click the \"Configuration Editor\" icon.\n\nFrom the \"Section:\" drop-down list, select \"system.webServer/asp\".\n\nExpand the \"session\" section.\n\nSelect \"True\" for the \"keepSessionIdSecure\" setting.\n\nSelect \"Apply\" from the \"Actions\" pane."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109365","V-100261"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB6051C-6C09-1014-9E10-BFC49E77F11A","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If the server being reviewed is a public IIS 10.0 web server, this is not applicable.\nNote: If the server being reviewed is hosting SharePoint, this is not applicable.\nNote: If the server being reviewed is hosting WSUS, this is not applicable.\nNote: If SSL is installed on load balancer/proxy server through which traffic is routed to the IIS 10.0 server, and the IIS 10.0 server receives traffic from the load balancer/proxy server, the SSL requirement must be met on the load balancer/proxy server.\nNote: If the server is providing OCSP, and not otherwise hosting any content, this requirement is not applicable.\n\nFollow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nAccess the IIS 10.0 Manager.\nUnder the \"Management\" section, double-click the \"Configuration Editor\" icon.\nFrom the \"Section:\" drop-down list, select \"system.web/httpCookies\".\nVerify the \"require SSL\" is set to \"True\".\n\nFrom the \"Section:\" drop-down list, select \"system.web/sessionState\".\nVerify the \"compressionEnabled\" is set to \"False\".\n\nIf both the \"system.web/httpCookies:require SSL\" is set to \"True\" and the \"system.web/sessionState:compressionEnabled\" is set to \"False\", this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218770","title":"SRG-APP-000439-WSR-000154"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000246","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218770r1111816_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218770","discussion":"A cookie can be read by client-side scripts easily if cookie properties are not set properly. By allowing cookies to be read by the client-side scripts, information such as session identifiers could be compromised and used by an attacker who intercepts the cookie. Setting cookie properties (i.e., HttpOnly property) to disallow client-side scripts from reading cookies better protects the information inside the cookie.\n\nSatisfies: SRG-APP-000439-WSR-000154, SRG-APP-000439-SSR-000155, SRG-APP-000439-WSR-000153","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218770","rule_id":"SV-218770r1111816","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Get the Require SSL setting from system.web/httpCookies for each website.)\nResult Analysis :        Site/Default Web Site/system.web/httpCookies/requireSSL = 'false' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'true' \n                : Site/soteriatest/system.web/httpCookies/requireSSL = 'false' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'true' \n                : Site/anothertestsite/system.web/httpCookies/requireSSL = 'false' failed test of 'equals' compared to 'true' \nTest            :   true (get the compressionEnabled setting from system.web/sessionState for each website.)\n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-002418"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218770"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Cookies exchanged between the IIS 10.0 website and the client must have cookie properties set to prohibit client-side scripts from reading the cookie data.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000439-WSR-000154","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Follow the procedures below for each site hosted on the IIS 10.0 web server:\n\nAccess the IIS 10.0 Manager.\nUnder \"Management\" section, double-click the \"Configuration Editor\" icon.\nFrom the \"Section:\" drop-down list, select \"system.web/httpCookies\".\nSet the \"require SSL\" to \"True\".\n\nFrom the \"Section:\" drop-down list, select \"system.web/sessionState\".\nSet the \"compressionEnabled\" to \"False\".\n\nSelect \"Apply\" from the \"Actions\" pane."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109367","V-100263"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB60887-6C09-1014-92E3-882C1DB1BB9A","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If the IIS Application Pool is hosting Microsoft SharePoint, this is Not Applicable.\n\nIf this IIS 10.0 installation is supporting Microsoft Exchange, and not otherwise hosting any content, this requirement is Not Applicable.\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick \"Application Pools\".\n\nIn the list of Application Pools, review the \"Applications\" column and verify unique application pools for each website.\n\nIf any Application Pools are being used for more than one website, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218771","title":"SRG-APP-000516-WSR-000174"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000251","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218771r961863_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218771","discussion":"Application pools isolate sites and applications to address reliability, availability, and security issues. Sites and applications may be grouped according to configurations, although each site will be associated with a unique application pool.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218771","rule_id":"SV-218771r961863","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (The IIS 10.0 website must have a unique application pool.)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218771"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The IIS 10.0 website must have a unique application pool.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516-WSR-000174","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the site name under review.\n\nAssign a unique application pool to each website."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109369","V-100265"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB60C02-6C09-1014-8F46-DA626ECB4020","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If the IIS Application Pool is hosting Microsoft SharePoint, this is Not Applicable.\nNote: If this server is hosting WSUS, this requirement is Not Applicable.\nNote: If this IIS 10.0 installation is supporting Microsoft Exchange, and not otherwise hosting any content, this requirement is Not Applicable.\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nPerform for each Application Pool.\n\nClick \"Application Pools\".\n\nHighlight an Application Pool and click \"Advanced Settings\" in the \"Action\" Pane.\n\nScroll down to the \"Recycling section\" and verify the value for \"Request Limit\" is set to a value other than \"0\".\n\nIf the \"Request Limit\" is set to a value of \"0\", this is a finding.\n\nIf the system must require \"Request Limit\" to be set to \"0\", it is documented and approved by the ISSO, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218772","title":"SRG-APP-000516-WSR-000174"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000252","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218772r1022694_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218772","discussion":"IIS application pools can be periodically recycled to avoid unstable states possibly leading to application crashes, hangs, or memory leaks. By default, application pool recycling is overlapped, which means the worker process to be shut down is kept running until after a new worker process is started. After a new worker process starts, new requests are passed to it. The old worker process shuts down after it finishes processing its existing requests, or after a configured time-out, whichever comes first. This way of recycling ensures uninterrupted service to clients.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218772","rule_id":"SV-218772r1022694","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (The maximum number of requests an application pool can process for each IIS 10.0 website must be explicitly set)\nResult Analysis :        Apppool/DefaultAppPool/recycling.periodicRestart.requests = '0' failed test of 'greater than' compared to '0' \n                : Apppool/soteriatest/recycling.periodicRestart.requests = '0' failed test of 'greater than' compared to '0' \n                : Apppool/anothertestsite/recycling.periodicRestart.requests = '0' failed test of 'greater than' compared to '0' \n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218772"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The maximum number of requests an application pool can process for each IIS 10.0 website must be explicitly set.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516-WSR-000174","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick \"Application Pools\".\n\nHighlight an Application Pool and click \"Advanced Settings\" in the \"Action\" Pane.\n\nScroll down to the \"Recycling section\" and set the value for \"Request Limit\" to greater than \"0\".\n\nClick \"OK\"."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109375","V-100271"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB60F63-6C09-1014-B332-918B1A45ABB1","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If the IIS Application Pool is hosting Microsoft SharePoint, this is Not Applicable.\nNote: If the IIS Application Pool is hosting Microsoft Exchange and not otherwise hosting any content, this is Not Applicable.\nNote: If this server is hosting WSUS, this requirement is Not Applicable.\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nExpand \"Application Pools\".\n\nPerform the following for each Application Pool:\n\nHighlight an Application Pool and click \"Recycling\" in the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nIn the Recycling Conditions window, verify at least one condition is checked as desired by the organization (e.g., Regular Time Intervals, Scheduled Time).\n\nIf no conditions are checked, this is a finding.\n\nClick \"Next\".\n\nIn the Recycling Events to Log window, verify at minimum the Recycling Events are selected that correspond to the conditions defined in the previous step (e.g., Regular Time Intervals, Scheduled Time).\n\nIf no events are selected, this is a finding.\n\nClick \"Cancel\".","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218775","title":"SRG-APP-000516-WSR-000174"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000255","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218775r1022696_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218775","discussion":"Application pools can be periodically recycled to avoid unstable states possibly leading to application crashes, hangs, or memory leaks.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218775","rule_id":"SV-218775r1022696","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true ((Regular time interval option) The application pool for each IIS 10.0 website must have a recycle time explicitly set.)\nTest            :   true ((Specific time option) The application pool for each IIS 10.0 website must have a recycle time explicitly set.)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218775"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The application pool for each IIS 10.0 website must have a recycle time explicitly set.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516-WSR-000174","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick the \"Application Pools\".\n\nPerform the following for each Application Pool:\n\nHighlight an Application Pool and click \"Recycling\" in the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nIn the Recycling Conditions window, select at least one means to recycle the Application Pool (e.g., Regular Time Intervals, Scheduled Time).\n\nClick \"Next\".\n\nIn the Recycling Events to Log window, select at minimum both the events that match the conditions from the previous step (e.g., Regular Time Intervals, Scheduled Time).\n\nClick \"Finish\"."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109379","V-100275"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB612B7-6C09-1014-BF24-C4C090F81167","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If the IIS Application Pool is hosting Microsoft SharePoint, this is Not Applicable.\n\nIf this IIS 10.0 installation is supporting Microsoft Exchange, and not otherwise hosting any content, this requirement is Not Applicable.\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick \"Application Pools\".\n\nPerform the following for each Application Pool:\n\nHighlight an Application Pool to review and click \"Advanced Settings\" in the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nScroll down to the \"Rapid Fail Protection\" section and verify the value for \"Enabled\" is set to \"True\".\n\nIf the \"Rapid Fail Protection:Enabled\" is not set to \"True\", this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218777","title":"SRG-APP-000516-WSR-000174"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000258","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218777r961863_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218777","discussion":"Rapid fail protection is a feature that interrogates the health of worker processes associated with websites and web applications. It can be configured to perform a number of actions such as shutting down and restarting worker processes that have reached failure thresholds. By not setting rapid fail protection, the web server could become unstable in the event of a worker process crash potentially leaving the web server unusable.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218777","rule_id":"SV-218777r961863","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (An application poolâs rapid fail protection must be enabled.)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218777"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The application pools rapid fail protection for each IIS 10.0 website must be enabled.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516-WSR-000174","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick \"Application Pools\".\n\nPerform the following for each Application Pool:\n\nHighlight an Application Pool to review and click \"Advanced Settings\" in the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nScroll down to the \"Rapid Fail Protection\" section and set the value for \"Enabled\" to \"True\".\n\nClick \"OK\"."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109381","V-100277"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB616C8-6C09-1014-AB62-E8C9BAB8C42F","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If the IIS Application Pool is hosting Microsoft SharePoint, this is Not Applicable.\n\nIf this IIS 10.0 installation is supporting Microsoft Exchange, and not otherwise hosting any content, this requirement is Not Applicable.\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick \"Application Pools\".\n\nPerform the following for each Application Pool:\n\nHighlight an Application Pool to review and click \"Advanced Settings\" in the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nScroll down to the \"Rapid Fail Protection\" section and verify the value for \"Failure Interval\" is set to \"5\".\n\nIf the \"Failure Interval\" is not set to \"5\" or less, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218778","title":"SRG-APP-000516-WSR-000174"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000259","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218778r961863_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218778","discussion":"Windows Process Activation Service (WAS) manages application pool configuration and may flag a worker process as unhealthy and shut it down. The rapid fail protection must be set to a suitable value. A lack of response from the worker process might mean the worker process does not have a thread to respond to the ping request, or that it is hanging for some other reason. The ping interval and ping response time may need adjustment to gain access to timely information about application pool health without triggering false, unhealthy conditions.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218778","rule_id":"SV-218778r961863","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: passRule Result     : Pass\nCriteria        : true (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   true (An application poolâs rapid fail protection value for Failure Interval is set to 5. If the Failure Interval is not set to 5 or less, this is a finding)\n","status":"not_a_finding","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218778"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The application pools rapid fail protection settings for each IIS 10.0 website must be managed.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516-WSR-000174","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Open the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nClick \"Application Pools\".\n\nPerform the following for each Application Pool:\n\nHighlight an Application Pool to review and click \"Advanced Settings\" in the \"Actions\" pane.\n\nScroll down to the \"Rapid Fail Protection\" section and set the value for \"Failure Interval\" to \"5\" or less.\n\nClick \"OK\"."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109383","V-100279"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB61C5D-6C09-1014-90DB-95F7D97C3FA9","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Determine whether scripts are used on the web server for the target website. Common file extensions include, but are not limited to: .cgi, .pl, .vbs, .class, .c, .php, and .asp. \n\nAll interactive programs must be placed in unique designated folders based on CGI or ASP script type. For modular and/or third-party applications, it is permissible to have script files in multiple folders.\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nRight-click the IIS 10.0 web site name and select \"Explore\".\n\nSearch for the listed script extensions. Each script type must be in its unique designated folder.\n\nIf scripts are not segregated from web content and in their own unique folders, this is a finding.\n\nIf the website does not utilize CGI, this finding is Not Applicable.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218779","title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000087"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000261","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218779r1022698_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218779","discussion":"CGI and ASP scripts represent one of the most common and exploitable means of compromising a web server. All CGI and ASP program files must be segregated into their own unique folder to simplify the protection of these files. ASP scripts must be placed into a unique folder only containing other ASP scripts. JAVA and other technology-specific scripts must also be placed into their own unique folders. The placement of CGI, ASP, or equivalent scripts to special folders gives the Web Manager or the System Administrator (SA) control over what goes into those folders and to facilitate access control at the folder level.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218779","rule_id":"SV-218779r1022698","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-218779, SV-218779r1022698, SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000087)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.site:questionnaire:7701"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Interactive scripts on the IIS 10.0 web server must be located in unique and designated folders.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000087","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"All interactive programs must be placed in unique designated folders based on CGI or ASP script type.\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nRight-click the IIS 10.0 web server name and select \"Explore\".\n\nSearch for the listed script extensions.\n\nMove each script type to its unique designated folder.\n\nSet the permissions to the scripts folders as follows:\n\nAdministrators: FULL\nTrustedInstaller: FULL\nSYSTEM: FULL\nApplicationPoolId:READ\nCustom Service Account: READ\nUsers: READ \nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES: READ"},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109385","V-100281"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB6201E-6C09-1014-9282-836C5F2FB6C2","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Determine whether scripts are used on the web server for the subject website. Common file extensions include, but are not limited to: .cgi, .pl, .vb, .class, .c, .php, and .asp.\n\nIf the website does not utilize CGI, this finding is Not Applicable.\n\nAll interactive programs must have restrictive permissions.\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nRight-click the IIS 10.0 web site name and select \"Explore\".\n\nSearch for the listed script extensions.\n\nReview the permissions to the CGI scripts and verify only the permissions listed, or more restrictive permissions are assigned.\n\nAdministrators: FULL\nWeb Administrators: FULL\nTrustedInstaller: FULL\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES: Read\nALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES: Read\nSYSTEM: FULL\nApplicationPoolId: READ\nCustom Service Account: READ\nUsers: READ\n\nIf the permissions are less restrictive than listed above, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218780","title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000087"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000262","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218780r960963_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218780","discussion":"CGI is a programming standard for interfacing external applications with information servers, such as HTTP or web servers. CGI, represented by all upper case letters, should not be confused with the .cgi file extension. The .cgi file extension does represent a CGI script, but CGI scripts may be written in a number of programming languages (e.g., PERL, C, PHP, and JavaScript), each having their own unique file extension.\n\nThe use of CGI scripts represent one of the most common and exploitable means of compromising a web server. By definition, CGI scripts are executable by the operating system of the host server. While access control is provided via the web service, the execution of CGI programs is not limited unless the System Administrator (SA) or the Web Manager takes specific measures. CGI programs can access and alter data files, launch other programs, and use the network.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218780","rule_id":"SV-218780r960963","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-218780, SV-218780r960963, SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000087)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.site:questionnaire:7901"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Interactive scripts on the IIS 10.0 web server must have restrictive access controls.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000087","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Determine whether scripts are used on the web server for the subject website. Common file extensions include, but are not limited to: .cgi, .pl, .vb, .class, .c, .php, and .asp.\n\nIf the website does not utilize CGI, this finding is NA.\n\nAll interactive programs must have restrictive permissions.\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nRight-click the IIS 10.0 web server name and select \"Explore\".\n\nSearch for the listed script extensions.\n\nSet the permissions to the CGI scripts as follows:\n\nAdministrators: FULL\nWeb Administrators: FULL\nTrustedInstaller: FULL\nALL APPLICATION PACKAGES: Read\nALL RESTRICTED APPLICATION PACKAGES: Read\nSYSTEM: FULL\nApplicationPoolId: READ\nCustom Service Account: READ\nUsers: READ"},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109387","V-100283"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB62382-6C09-1014-A547-B3AFEB5035EA","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"If the website does not utilize CGI, this finding is Not Applicable.\n\nOpen the IIS 10.0 Manager.\n\nRight-click the IIS 10.0 web site name and select \"Explore\".\n\nSearch for the listed script extensions\n\nSearch for the following files: *.bak, *.old, *.temp, *.tmp, *.backup, or âcopy of...â.\n\nIf files with these extensions are found, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218781","title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000087"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000263","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218781r1022700_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218781","discussion":"Copies of backup files will not execute on the server, but they can be read by the anonymous user if special precautions are not taken. Such backup copies contain the same sensitive information as the actual script being executed and, as such, are useful to malicious users. Techniques and systems exist today to search web servers for such files and are able to exploit the information contained in them.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218781","rule_id":"SV-218781r1022700","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: notapplicableRule Result     : Not Applicable\n","status":"not_applicable","ccis":["CCI-000381"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:218781"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"Backup interactive scripts on the IIS 10.0 server must be removed.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000141-WSR-000087","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Remove the backup files from the production web server."},{"legacy_ids":["SV-109389","V-100285"],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB627ED-6C09-1014-9BFF-B3CAAA8A527F","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: This requirement is only applicable for private DOD websites.\nNote: If the server being reviewed is hosting WSUS, this is not applicable.\n\nIf a banner is required, the following banner page must be in place: \n\nâYou are accessing a U.S. Government (USG) Information System (IS) that is provided for USG-authorized use only. \n\nBy using this IS (which includes any device attached to this IS), you consent to the following conditions: \n\n-The USG routinely intercepts and monitors communications on this IS for purposes including, but not limited to, penetration testing, COMSEC monitoring, network operations and defense, personnel misconduct (PM), law enforcement (LE), and counterintelligence (CI) investigations. \n\n- At any time, the USG may inspect and seize data stored on this IS. \n\n- Communications using, or data stored on, this IS are not private, are subject to routine monitoring, interception, and search, and may be disclosed or used for any USG-authorized purpose. \n\n- This IS includes security measures (e.g., authentication and access controls) to protect USG interestsânot for your personal benefit or privacy. \n\n- Notwithstanding the above, using this IS does not constitute consent to PM, LE or CI investigative searching or monitoring of the content of privileged communications, or work product, related to personal representation or services by attorneys, psychotherapists, or clergy, and their assistants. Such communications and work product are private and confidential. See User Agreement for details.â \n\nOR \n\nIf your system cannot meet the character limits to store this amount of text in the banner, the following is another option for the warning banner: \n\n\"I've read &amp; consent to terms in IS user agreem't.\" \n\nNOTE: While DoDI 8500.01 does not contain a copy of the banner to be used, it does point to the RMF Knowledge Service for a copy of the required text. It is also noted that the banner is to be displayed only once when the individual enters the site and not for each page. \n\nIf the access-controlled website does not display this banner page before entry, this is a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-218782","title":"SRG-APP-000516-WSR-000174"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000264","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-218782r1111818_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-218782","discussion":"A consent banner will be in place to inform prospective entrants the website they are about to enter is a DoD website and their activity is subject to monitoring. The document, DoDI 8500.01, establishes the policy on the use of DoD information systems. It requires the use of a standard Notice and Consent Banner and standard text to be included in user agreements. The requirement for the banner is for websites with security and access controls. These are restricted and not publicly accessible. If the website does not require authentication/authorization for use, then the banner does not need to be present. A manual check of the document root directory for a banner page file (such as banner.html) or navigation to the website via a browser can be used to confirm the information provided from interviewing the web staff.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-218782","rule_id":"SV-218782r1111818","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: notcheckedCriteria        : NOT_TESTED (All child tests must be true.)\nTest            :   NOT_TESTED (CAT II, V-218782, SV-218782r1111818, SRG-APP-000516-WSR-000174)\n","status":"not_reviewed","ccis":["CCI-000366"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-ocil.xml","name":"ocil:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.10.site:questionnaire:8301"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"The required DoD banner page must be displayed to authenticated users accessing a DoD private website.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000516-WSR-000174","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Configure a DoD private website to display the required DoD banner page when authentication is required for user access."},{"legacy_ids":[],"weight":"10.0","uuid":"3EB62B88-6C09-1014-882D-CD643C41658E","comments":null,"ia_controls":"","check_content":"Note: If the server is hosting WSUS, this is not applicable.\n\nOpen Registry Editor.\n\nNavigate to \"HKLM\\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\HTTP\\Parameters\".\n\nVerify \"DisableServerHeaderâ is set to \"2\".\n\nIf REG_DWORD DisableServerHeader is not set to \"2\", this is a finding.\n\nIf the system administrator can show that Server Version information has been removed via other means, such as using a rewrite outbound rule, this is not a finding.","classification":"Unclassified","group_tree":{"id":"V-278953","title":"SRG-APP-000266-WSR-000159"},"rule_version":"IIST-SI-000270","reference_identifier":"4051","documentable":"false","rule_id_src":"SV-278953r1135550_rule","severity":"medium","group_id_src":"V-278953","discussion":"HTTP Response Headers contain information that could enable an attacker to gain access to an information system. Failure to prevent the sending of certain HTTP Response Header information to remote requesters exposes internal configuration information to potential attackers.","potential_impacts":"","group_id":"V-278953","rule_id":"SV-278953r1135550","security_override_guidance":"","finding_details":"Tool: cpe:/a:niwc:scc:5.14\nTime         : 2026-03-16T12:04:17\nResult: failRule Result     : Fail\nCriteria        : false (All child tests must be true. (AND))\nTest            :   false (Verify DisableServerHeader is set to 2)\nResult Analysis :        Registry Name Not found: 'HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\HTTP\\Parameters\\DisableServerHeader'.  Existence requirement is 'at_least_one_exists' and no items were collected, so result is false.\n","status":"open","ccis":["CCI-001312"],"third_party_tools":"","responsibility":"","mitigation_control":"","mitigations":"","check_content_ref":{"href":"U_MS_IIS_10-0_Site_V2R14_STIG_SCAP_1-4_Benchmark-enhancedV17-oval2.xml","name":"oval:navy.navwar.niwcatlantic.scc.ms.iis.10.site:def:278953"},"false_positives":"","rule_title":"HTTPAPI Server version must be removed from the HTTP Response Header information.","group_title":"SRG-APP-000266-WSR-000159","stig_uuid":"3EB42554-6C09-1014-9E18-CE5A3FE9E688","fix_text":"Navigate to \"HKLM\\System\\CurrentControlSet\\Services\\HTTP\\Parameters\".\n\nCreate REG_DWORD \"DisableServerHeaderâ and set it to \"2\".\n\nNote: This can be performed multiple ways; this is an example."}]}],"title":"SCC Generated CKLB at: 2026-03-16T12:04:36"}